WEBVTT

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:31.920
The second book of Moses, called Exodus

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:38.300
Now these are the names of the children of Israel which came into Egypt, every man and

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:47.020
his household came with Jacob. Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah, Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,

00:00:47.660 --> 00:00:54.300
Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. And all the souls that came out of the loins of Jacob

00:00:54.300 --> 00:01:01.540
were seventy souls, for Joseph was in Egypt already. And Joseph died, and all his brethren,

00:01:01.820 --> 00:01:08.080
and all that generation. And the children of Israel were fruitful, and increased abundantly,

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:15.120
and multiplied, and waxed exceeding mighty, and the land was filled with them. Now there

00:01:15.120 --> 00:01:22.440
arose up a new king over Egypt which knew not Joseph. And he said unto his people, Behold

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:28.240
the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we. Come on, let us deal

00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:33.660
wisely with them, lest they multiply, and it come to pass that when there falleth out

00:01:33.660 --> 00:01:40.000
any war they join also unto our enemies, and fight against us, and so get them up out of

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:46.260
the land. Therefore they did set over them task-masters to afflict them with their burdens,

00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:55.240
and they built for Pharaoh treasure cities, Pitham, and Ramses. But the more they afflicted

00:01:55.240 --> 00:02:00.400
them the more they multiplied, and grew, and they were grieved because of the children

00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:06.420
of Israel. And the Egyptians made the children of Israel to serve with rigor, and they made

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:12.040
their lives bitter with hard bondage, in mortar, and in brick, and in all manner of service

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:19.200
in the field. All their service wherein they made them serve was with rigor. And the king

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:24.220
of Egypt spake to the Hebrew midwives, of which the name of the one was Shifra, and

00:02:24.220 --> 00:02:30.000
the name of the other Pua. And he said, When ye do the office of a midwife to the Hebrew

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:36.300
women, and see them upon the stools, if it be a son, then ye shall kill him, but if it

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:42.760
be a daughter, then she shall live. But the midwives feared God, and did not as the king

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:49.320
of Egypt commanded them, but saved the men-children alive. And the king of Egypt called for the

00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:54.380
midwives, and said unto them, Why have ye done this thing, and have saved the men-children

00:02:54.380 --> 00:03:00.920
alive? And the midwives said unto Pharaoh, Because the Hebrew women are not as the Egyptian

00:03:00.920 --> 00:03:07.300
women, for they are lively, and are delivered ere the midwives come in unto them. Therefore

00:03:07.300 --> 00:03:12.780
God dealt well with the midwives, and the people multiplied, and waxed very mighty.

00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:20.220
And it came to pass, because the midwives feared God, that he made them houses. And

00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:25.940
Pharaoh charged all his people, saying, Every son that is born ye shall cast into the river,

00:03:25.940 --> 00:03:28.560
and every daughter ye shall save alive.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:37.460
And there went a man of the house of Levi, and took to wife a daughter of Levi. And the

00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:43.020
woman conceived, and bare a son. And when she saw him, that he was a goodly child, she

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:49.220
hid him three months. And when she could not longer hide him, she took for him an ark of

00:03:49.220 --> 00:03:54.980
bulrushes, and daubed it with slime, and with pitch, and put the child therein, and she

00:03:54.980 --> 00:04:01.180
laid it in the flags by the river's bank. And his sister stood afar off to wit what

00:04:01.180 --> 00:04:07.180
would be done to him. And the daughter of Pharaoh came down to wash herself at the river,

00:04:07.460 --> 00:04:12.900
and her maidens walked along by the river's side, and when she saw the ark among the flags

00:04:12.900 --> 00:04:19.260
she sent her maid to fetch it. And when she had opened it she saw the child, and behold

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:25.480
the babe wept. And she had compassion on him, and said, This is one of the Hebrews' children.

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:31.520
Then said his sister to Pharaoh's daughter, Shall I go, and call to thee a nurse of the

00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:36.960
Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for thee? And Pharaoh's daughter said to her,

00:04:37.060 --> 00:04:43.740
Go. And the maid went, and called the child's mother. And Pharaoh's daughter said unto her,

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:49.660
Take this child away, and nurse it for me, and I will give thee thy wages. And the woman

00:04:49.660 --> 00:04:55.840
took the child, and nursed it. And the child grew, and she brought him unto Pharaoh's daughter,

00:04:56.180 --> 00:05:02.100
and he became her son. And she called his name Moses, and she said, Because I drew him

00:05:02.100 --> 00:05:08.460
out of the water. And it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out

00:05:09.140 --> 00:05:15.360
and looked on their burdens, and he spied an Egyptian smiting in Hebrew one of his brethren.

00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:21.660
And he looked this way and that way, and when he saw that there was no man, he slew the

00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:28.340
Egyptian and hid him in the sand. And when he went out the second day, behold two men

00:05:28.340 --> 00:05:34.000
of the Hebrews strove together, and he said to him that did the wrong, Wherefore smitest

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:40.960
thou thy fellow? And he said, Whom made thee a prince and a judge over us? Intendest thou

00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:47.660
to kill me, as thou killest the Egyptian? And Moses feared, and said, Surely this thing

00:05:47.660 --> 00:05:54.480
is known. Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses, but Moses fled from

00:05:54.480 --> 00:06:01.140
the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian, and he sat down by a well. Now

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:06.160
the priest of Midian had seven daughters, and they came and drew water, and filled the

00:06:06.160 --> 00:06:11.900
troughs to water their father's flock. And the shepherds came and drove them away, but

00:06:11.900 --> 00:06:18.100
Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock. And when they came to rule their

00:06:18.100 --> 00:06:24.460
father, he said, How is it that ye are come so soon to-day? And they said, An Egyptian

00:06:24.460 --> 00:06:29.620
delivered us out of the hand of the shepherds, and also drew water enough for us, and watered

00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:35.400
their flock. And he said unto his daughters, And where is he? Why is it that ye have left

00:06:35.400 --> 00:06:41.320
the man? Call him, that he may eat bread. And Moses was content to dwell with the man,

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:48.360
and he gave Moses Zipporah his daughter. And she bare him a son, and he called his name

00:06:48.360 --> 00:06:55.660
Gershom, for he said, I have been a stranger in a strange land. And it came to pass in

00:06:55.660 --> 00:07:01.020
the process of time that the king of Egypt died, and the children of Israel sighed by

00:07:01.020 --> 00:07:06.440
reason of the bondage, and they cried, and their cry came up unto God by reason of the

00:07:06.440 --> 00:07:12.400
bondage. And God heard their groaning, and God remembered his covenant with Abraham,

00:07:12.620 --> 00:07:19.120
with Isaac, and with Jacob. And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God had respect

00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:20.100
unto them.

00:07:23.220 --> 00:07:29.160
Now Moses kept the flock of Jethro, his father-in-law, the priest of Midian, and he led the flock

00:07:29.160 --> 00:07:35.920
to the back side of the desert, and came to the mountain of God, even to Horeb. And the

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:41.220
angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a flame of fire out of the midst of a bush, and he

00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:48.700
looked, and behold, the bush burned with fire, and the bush was not consumed. And Moses said,

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:56.060
I will now turn aside and see this great sight, why the bush is not burnt. And when the Lord

00:07:56.060 --> 00:08:01.360
saw that he turned aside to see, God called unto him out of the midst of the bush, and

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:10.420
said, Moses, Moses! And he said, Here am I! And he said, Draw not nigh hither, put off

00:08:10.420 --> 00:08:17.480
thy shoes from off thy feet, for the place where I'll now standest is holy ground. Moreover,

00:08:17.480 --> 00:08:24.000
he said, I am the God of thy father, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:29.540
of Jacob. And Moses hid his face, for he was afraid to look upon God.

00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:35.560
And the Lord said, I have surely seen the affliction of my people which are in Egypt,

00:08:35.920 --> 00:08:41.740
and have heard their cry by reason of their task-masters, for I know their sorrows, and

00:08:41.740 --> 00:08:46.460
I am come down to deliver them out of the hand of the Egyptians, and to bring them up

00:08:46.460 --> 00:08:53.480
out of that land, unto a good land, at a large, unto a land flowing with milk and honey, unto

00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:58.740
the place of the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Perizzites, and

00:08:58.740 --> 00:09:05.320
the Hivites, and the Jebusites. Now therefore behold the cry of the children of Israel is

00:09:05.320 --> 00:09:12.080
come unto me, and I have also seen the oppression wherewith the Egyptians oppressed them. Come

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:17.440
now therefore, and I will send thee unto Pharaoh, that thou mayest bring forth my people,

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.060
the children of Israel, out of Egypt.

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:27.200
And Moses said unto God, Who am I, that I should go unto Pharaoh, and that I should

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:33.420
bring forth the children of Israel out of Egypt? And he said, Certainly I will be with

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:38.860
thee, and this shall be a token unto thee, that I have sent thee. When thou hast brought

00:09:38.860 --> 00:09:43.160
forth the people out of Egypt, ye shall serve God upon this mountain.

00:09:44.100 --> 00:09:49.480
And Moses said unto God, Behold, when I come unto the children of Israel, and shall say

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:55.020
unto them, The God of your fathers hath sent me unto you, and they shall say to me, What

00:09:55.020 --> 00:10:03.000
is his name? What shall I say unto them? And God said unto Moses, I am that I am. And

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:09.520
he said, Thus shalt thou say unto the children of Israel, I am, hath sent me unto you.

00:10:10.340 --> 00:10:16.320
And God said moreover unto Moses, Thus shalt thou say unto the children of Israel, The

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:22.580
Lord God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, hath

00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:29.100
sent me unto you. This is my name for ever, and this is my memorial unto all generations.

00:10:30.040 --> 00:10:36.340
Go, and gather the elders of Israel together, and say unto them, The Lord God of your fathers,

00:10:36.760 --> 00:10:43.200
the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared unto me, saying, I have surely visited

00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:49.200
you and seen that which has done to you in Egypt. And I have said, I will bring you up

00:10:49.200 --> 00:10:54.420
out of the affliction of Egypt, unto the land of the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the

00:10:54.420 --> 00:11:00.540
Samarites, and the Perizzites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, unto a land flowing with

00:11:00.540 --> 00:11:06.620
milk and honey. And they shall hearken to thy voice, and thou shalt come, thou and the

00:11:06.620 --> 00:11:12.420
elders of Israel, unto the King of Egypt, and ye shall say unto him, The Lord God of

00:11:12.420 --> 00:11:18.340
the Hebrews hath met with us. And now let us go, we beseech thee, three days journey

00:11:18.340 --> 00:11:22.520
into the wilderness, though it may sacrifice to the Lord our God.

00:11:23.420 --> 00:11:29.180
And I am sure that the King of Egypt will not let you go, no, not by a mighty hand.

00:11:29.860 --> 00:11:34.980
And I will stretch out my hand, and smite Egypt with all my wonders which I will do

00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:41.440
in the midst thereof, and after that he will let you go. And I will give this people favor

00:11:41.440 --> 00:11:46.860
in the sight of the Egyptians, and it shall come to pass that when ye go ye shall not

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:52.380
go empty. But every woman shall borrow of her neighbor, and of her that sojourneth in

00:11:52.380 --> 00:11:58.600
her house, jewels of silver, and jewels of gold, and raiment, and ye shall put them upon

00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:02.820
your sons and upon your daughters, and ye shall spoil the Egyptians.

00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:12.700
And Moses answered and said, But behold, they will not believe me, nor hearken unto my voice,

00:12:12.700 --> 00:12:19.020
for they will say, The Lord hath not appeared unto thee. And the Lord said unto him, What

00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:26.280
is that in thine hand? And he said, A rod. And he said, Cast it on the ground. And he

00:12:26.280 --> 00:12:32.680
cast it on the ground, and it became a serpent, and Moses fled from before it. And the Lord

00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:38.660
said unto Moses, Put forth thine hand, and take it by the tail. And he put forth his

00:12:38.660 --> 00:12:44.440
hand, and caught it, and it became a rod in his hand. That they may believe that the Lord

00:12:44.440 --> 00:12:49.800
God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob hath

00:12:49.800 --> 00:12:56.340
appeared unto thee. And the Lord said furthermore unto him, Put now thine hand into thy bosom.

00:12:56.760 --> 00:13:02.100
And he put his hand into his bosom. And when he took it out, behold, his hand was leprous

00:13:02.100 --> 00:13:08.660
as snow. And he said, Put thine hand into thy bosom again. And he put his hand into

00:13:08.660 --> 00:13:13.980
his bosom again, and plucked it out of his bosom, and behold, it was turned again as

00:13:13.980 --> 00:13:20.340
his other flesh. And it shall come to pass, if they will not believe thee, neither hearken

00:13:20.340 --> 00:13:24.900
to the voice of the first sign, that they will believe the voice of the latter sign.

00:13:25.340 --> 00:13:30.760
And it shall come to pass, if they will not believe also these two signs, neither hearken

00:13:30.760 --> 00:13:35.780
unto thy voice, that thou shalt take of the water of the river, and pour it upon the

00:13:35.780 --> 00:13:41.300
dry land, and the water which thou takest out of the river shall become blood upon the

00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:48.740
dry land. And Moses said unto the Lord, O my Lord, I am not eloquent, neither hew to

00:13:48.740 --> 00:13:55.440
for, nor since thou hast spoken unto thy servant, but I am slow of speech, and of a slow tongue.

00:13:56.140 --> 00:14:02.380
And the Lord said unto him, Who hath made man's mouth, or who maketh the dumb, or deaf,

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:08.780
or the seeing, or the blind? Have not I the Lord? Now therefore go, and I will be with

00:14:08.780 --> 00:14:15.680
thy mouth, and teach thee what thou shalt say. And he said, O my Lord, send, I pray,

00:14:15.760 --> 00:14:21.180
thee, by the hand of him whom thou wilt send. And the anger of the Lord was kindled against

00:14:21.180 --> 00:14:27.380
Moses, and he said, Is not Aaron the Levite thy brother? I know that he can speak well,

00:14:27.720 --> 00:14:33.340
and also, behold, he cometh forth to meet thee, and when he seeth thee, he will be glad

00:14:33.340 --> 00:14:39.020
in his heart. And thou shalt speak unto him, and put words in his mouth, and I will be

00:14:39.020 --> 00:14:44.580
with thy mouth, and with his mouth, and will teach you what ye shall do. And he shall be

00:14:44.580 --> 00:14:50.020
thy spokesman unto the people, and he shall be, even he shall be to thee, instead of a

00:14:50.020 --> 00:14:56.080
mouth, and thou shalt be to him, instead of God. And thou shalt take this rod in thine

00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:58.700
hand, wherewith thou shalt do signs.

00:14:59.900 --> 00:15:05.720
And Moses went and returned to Jethro his father-in-law, and said unto him, Let me go,

00:15:05.860 --> 00:15:10.900
I pray thee, and return unto my brethren, which are in Egypt, and see whether they be

00:15:10.900 --> 00:15:18.500
yet alive. And Jethro said to Moses, Go in peace. And the Lord said unto Moses in Midian,

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:25.820
Go, return into Egypt, for all the men are dead which sought thy life. And Moses took

00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:31.360
his wife and his sons, and set them upon an ass, and he returned to the land of Egypt,

00:15:31.780 --> 00:15:38.740
and Moses took the rod of God in his hand. And the Lord said unto Moses, When thou goest

00:15:38.740 --> 00:15:44.840
to return into Egypt, see that thou do all those wonders before Pharaoh which I have put

00:15:44.840 --> 00:15:51.800
in thine hand. But I will harden his heart, that he shall not let the people go. And

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:58.380
thou shalt say unto Pharaoh, Thus saith the Lord, Israel is my son, even my firstborn.

00:15:58.880 --> 00:16:04.860
And I say unto thee, Let my son go, that he may serve me. And if thou refuse to let him

00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:09.640
go, behold, I will slay thy son, even thy firstborn.

00:16:10.560 --> 00:16:15.920
And it came to pass, by the way, in the inn, that the Lord met him, and sought to kill

00:16:15.920 --> 00:16:23.440
him. Then Zipporah took a sharp stone, and cut off the foreskin of her son, and cast

00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:30.260
it at his feet, and said, Surely a bloody husband art thou to me. So he let him go,

00:16:30.540 --> 00:16:35.220
then she said, A bloody husband thou art, because of the circumcision.

00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:42.500
And the Lord said to Aaron, Go into the wilderness to meet Moses. And he went, and met him in

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:48.900
the mount of God, and kissed him. And Moses told Aaron all the words of the Lord who had

00:16:48.900 --> 00:16:54.880
sent him, and all the signs which he had commanded him. And Moses and Aaron went, and gathered

00:16:54.880 --> 00:17:00.100
together all the elders of the children of Israel. And Aaron spake all the words which

00:17:00.100 --> 00:17:05.820
the Lord had spoken unto Moses, and did the signs and the sight of the people. And the

00:17:05.820 --> 00:17:10.500
people believed, that when they heard that the Lord had visited the children of Israel,

00:17:10.840 --> 00:17:16.360
and that he had looked upon their affliction, then they bowed their heads, and worshipped.

00:17:19.140 --> 00:17:25.940
And afterward Moses and Aaron went in, and told Pharaoh, Thus saith the Lord God of Israel,

00:17:25.940 --> 00:17:30.560
Let my people go, that they may hold a feast unto me in the wilderness.

00:17:31.600 --> 00:17:38.440
And Pharaoh said, Who is the Lord that I should obey his voice to let Israel go? I know not

00:17:38.440 --> 00:17:41.380
the Lord, neither will I let Israel go.

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:47.700
And they said, The God of the Hebrews hath met with us. Let us go, we pray thee, three

00:17:47.700 --> 00:17:53.760
days' journey into the desert, and sacrifice unto the Lord our God, lest he fall upon us

00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:56.020
with pestilence or with the sword.

00:17:57.040 --> 00:18:02.620
And the King of Egypt said unto them, Wherefore do ye, Moses and Aaron, let the people from

00:18:02.620 --> 00:18:05.440
their works? Get you unto your burdens.

00:18:06.220 --> 00:18:11.860
And Pharaoh said, Behold, the people of the land now are many, and ye make them rest from

00:18:11.860 --> 00:18:12.620
their burdens.

00:18:13.620 --> 00:18:19.300
And Pharaoh commanded the same day the task-masters of the people and their officers, saying,

00:18:19.300 --> 00:18:25.340
Ye shall no more give the people straw to make brick, as heretofore. Let them go and

00:18:25.340 --> 00:18:30.720
gather straw for themselves. And the tail of the bricks, which they did make heretofore,

00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:36.860
ye shall lay upon them. Ye shall not diminish aught thereof, for they be idle. Therefore

00:18:36.860 --> 00:18:40.680
they cry, saying, Let us go and sacrifice to our God.

00:18:41.580 --> 00:18:47.080
Let their more work be laid upon the men that they may labor therein, and let them not regard

00:18:47.080 --> 00:18:48.120
vain words.

00:18:49.580 --> 00:18:54.520
And the task-masters of the people went out and their officers, and they spake to the

00:18:54.520 --> 00:19:01.220
people, saying, Thus saith Pharaoh, I will not give you straw. Go ye, get you straw,

00:19:01.380 --> 00:19:05.940
where you can find it. Yet not aught of your work shall be diminished.

00:19:06.960 --> 00:19:11.860
So the people were scattered abroad throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble instead

00:19:11.860 --> 00:19:18.340
of straw. And the task-masters hasted them, saying, Fulfill your works, your daily tasks,

00:19:18.620 --> 00:19:23.780
as when there was straw. And the officers of the children of Israel, which Pharaoh's

00:19:23.780 --> 00:19:29.320
task-masters had set over them, were beaten, and demanded, Wherefore have ye not fulfilled

00:19:29.320 --> 00:19:34.040
your task in making brick, both yesterday and to-day, as heretofore?

00:19:35.120 --> 00:19:40.460
Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried unto Pharaoh, saying, Wherefore

00:19:40.460 --> 00:19:45.800
dealest thou thus with thy servants? There is no straw given unto thy servants, and

00:19:45.800 --> 00:19:51.080
they say to us, Make brick, and behold, thy servants are beaten, but the fault is in thine

00:19:51.080 --> 00:19:51.940
own people.

00:19:52.740 --> 00:19:59.320
But he said, Ye are idle, ye are idle, therefore ye say, Let us go and do sacrifice to the

00:19:59.320 --> 00:20:05.620
Lord. Go therefore now and work, for there shall no straw be given you, yet shall ye

00:20:05.620 --> 00:20:06.960
deliver the tale of bricks.

00:20:07.720 --> 00:20:12.860
And the officers of the children of Israel did see that they were in evil case, after

00:20:12.860 --> 00:20:17.340
it was said, Ye shall not diminish aught from your bricks of your daily task.

00:20:18.420 --> 00:20:23.000
And they met Moses and Aaron, who stood in the way, as they came forth from Pharaoh.

00:20:23.560 --> 00:20:29.260
And they said unto them, The Lord look upon you and judge, because ye have made our savor

00:20:29.260 --> 00:20:34.680
to be abhorred in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of his servants, to put a sword

00:20:34.680 --> 00:20:36.460
in their hand to slay us.

00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:42.700
And Moses returned unto the Lord, and said, Lord, wherefore hast thou so evil and treated

00:20:42.700 --> 00:20:48.460
this people? Why is it that thou hast sent me? For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:53.840
thy name, he hath done evil to this people, neither hast thou delivered thy people at

00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:54.320
all.

00:20:57.820 --> 00:21:03.840
Then the Lord said unto Moses, Now shalt thou see what I will do to Pharaoh, for with a

00:21:03.840 --> 00:21:09.120
strong hand shall he let them go, and with a strong hand shall he drive them out of his

00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:09.520
land.

00:21:10.360 --> 00:21:16.720
And God spake unto Moses, and said unto him, I am the Lord. And I appeared unto Abraham,

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:23.540
unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, by the name of God Almighty, but by my name Jehovah was I

00:21:23.540 --> 00:21:29.380
not known to them. And I have also established my covenant with them, to give them the land

00:21:29.380 --> 00:21:35.560
of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, wherein they were strangers. And I have also heard

00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:40.600
the groaning of the children of Israel, whom the Egyptians keep in bondage, and I have

00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:46.880
remembered my covenant. Wherefore say unto the children of Israel, I am the Lord, and

00:21:46.880 --> 00:21:51.480
I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will rid you out of

00:21:51.480 --> 00:21:56.760
their bondage, and I will redeem you with a stretched out arm, and with great judgments,

00:21:57.320 --> 00:22:02.980
and I will take you to me for a people, and I will be to you a God, and ye shall know

00:22:02.980 --> 00:22:08.300
that I am the Lord your God, which bringeth you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.

00:22:09.080 --> 00:22:14.140
And I will bring you in unto the land concerning the which I did swear to give it to Abraham,

00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:20.000
to Isaac, and to Jacob, and I will give it you for an heritage. I am the Lord.

00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:27.360
And Moses spake so unto the children of Israel, but they hearken not unto Moses for anguish

00:22:27.360 --> 00:22:34.840
of spirit, and for cruel bondage. And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Go in, speak

00:22:34.840 --> 00:22:40.860
unto Pharaoh, King of Egypt, that he let the children of Israel go out of his land. And

00:22:40.860 --> 00:22:45.840
Moses spake before the Lord, saying, Behold, the children of Israel have not hearkened

00:22:45.840 --> 00:22:52.660
unto me. How then shall Pharaoh hear me, who am of uncircumcised lips? And the Lord spake

00:22:52.660 --> 00:22:57.680
unto Moses, and unto Aaron, and gave them a charge unto the children of Israel, and

00:22:57.680 --> 00:23:02.760
unto Pharaoh, King of Egypt, to bring the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt.

00:23:04.240 --> 00:23:09.800
These be the heads of their fathers' houses, the sons of Reuben, the firstborn of Israel,

00:23:10.440 --> 00:23:17.180
Hanukkah, and Palu, Hezran, and Carmi. These be the families of Reuben. And the sons of

00:23:17.180 --> 00:23:24.720
Simeon, Jemuel, and Jamin, and Ohad, and Jaqen, and Zohar, and Sheul, the son of a Canaanitish

00:23:24.720 --> 00:23:31.460
woman. These are the families of Simeon. And these are the names of the sons of Levi according

00:23:31.460 --> 00:23:38.300
to their generations, Gershon, and Kohath, and Mirari. And the years of the life of Levi

00:23:38.300 --> 00:23:46.360
were 130 and 7 years. The sons of Gershon, Libni, and Shimei, according to their families.

00:23:47.080 --> 00:23:53.580
And the sons of Kohath, Amram, and Izhar, and Hebron, and Uziol. And the years of the

00:23:53.580 --> 00:24:02.260
life of Kohath were 130 and 3 years. And the sons of Mirari, Mehalai, and Mushai. These

00:24:02.260 --> 00:24:08.660
are the families of Levi according to their generations. And Amram took Jacobed, his father's

00:24:08.660 --> 00:24:14.420
sister, to wife, and she bared him Aaron and Moses. And the years of the life of Amram

00:24:14.420 --> 00:24:24.160
were 130 and 7 years. And the sons of Izhar, Korah, and Nefeg, and Zikrai. And the sons

00:24:24.160 --> 00:24:31.480
of Uziol, Maishael, and Elzaphan, and Zithrai. And Aaron took him Elishaba, daughter of

00:24:31.480 --> 00:24:40.940
Minadab, sister of Neishan, to wife. And she bared him Nadab, and Abihu, Eliezer, and Ithamar.

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:48.840
And the sons of Korah, Aser, and Alkena, and Abiasif. These are the families of the Korheites.

00:24:49.760 --> 00:24:55.240
And Eliezer, Aaron's son, took him one of the daughters of Putiel to wife. And she bared

00:24:55.240 --> 00:25:00.600
him Phinehas. These are the heads of the fathers of the Levites according to their families.

00:25:01.860 --> 00:25:07.080
These are that Aaron and Moses to whom the Lord said, Bring out the children of Israel

00:25:07.080 --> 00:25:12.520
from the land of Egypt according to their armies. These are they which spake to Pharaoh,

00:25:12.640 --> 00:25:18.440
King of Egypt, to bring out the children of Israel from Egypt. These are that Moses and

00:25:18.440 --> 00:25:24.500
Aaron. And it came to pass on the day when the Lord spake unto Moses in the land of Egypt

00:25:24.500 --> 00:25:30.600
that the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, I am the Lord, speak thou unto Pharaoh, King

00:25:30.600 --> 00:25:37.620
of Egypt, all that I say unto thee. And Moses said before the Lord, Behold, I am of uncircumcised

00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:41.520
lips, and how shall Pharaoh hearken unto me?

00:26:13.480 --> 00:26:19.600
And the LORD said unto Moses, See, I have made thee a god to Pharaoh, and Aaron thy

00:26:19.600 --> 00:26:25.320
brother shall be thy prophet. Thou shalt speak all that I command thee, and Aaron thy brother

00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:30.920
shall speak unto Pharaoh, that he send the children of Israel out of his land. And I

00:26:30.920 --> 00:26:36.040
will harden Pharaoh's heart, and multiply my signs and my wonders in the land of Egypt.

00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:42.840
But Pharaoh shall not hearken unto you, that I may lay my hand upon Egypt, and bring forth

00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:48.360
mine armies, and my people, the children of Israel, out of the land of Egypt, by great

00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:54.440
judgments. And the Egyptians shall know that I am the LORD, when I stretch forth mine hand

00:26:54.440 --> 00:27:00.480
upon Egypt, and bring out the children of Israel from among them. And Moses and Aaron

00:27:00.480 --> 00:27:06.880
did as the LORD commanded them, so did they. And Moses was fourscore years old, and Aaron

00:27:06.880 --> 00:27:13.240
fourscore and three years old, when they spake unto Pharaoh. And the LORD spake unto Moses

00:27:13.240 --> 00:27:19.340
and unto Aaron, saying, When Pharaoh shall speak unto you, saying, Show a miracle for

00:27:19.340 --> 00:27:25.740
you, then thou shalt say unto Aaron, Take thy rod, and cast it before Pharaoh, and it

00:27:25.740 --> 00:27:31.780
will become a serpent. And Moses and Aaron went in unto Pharaoh, and they did so as the

00:27:31.780 --> 00:27:37.440
LORD had commanded, and Aaron cast down his rod before Pharaoh and before his servants,

00:27:37.760 --> 00:27:44.340
and it became a serpent. Then Pharaoh also called the wise men and the sorcerers. Now

00:27:44.340 --> 00:27:50.220
the magicians of Egypt they also did in like manner with their enchantments. For they cast

00:27:50.220 --> 00:27:57.660
down every man his rod, and they became serpents, but Aaron's rod swallowed up their rods. And

00:27:57.660 --> 00:28:03.720
he hardened Pharaoh's heart that he hearkened not unto them as the LORD had said. And the

00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:10.520
LORD said unto Moses, Pharaoh's heart is hardened, he refuseth to let the people go. Get thee

00:28:10.520 --> 00:28:20.200
unto Pharaoh in the morning, lo, he goeth out unto the water, and thou shalt stand by the

00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:26.460
serpent, shalt thou take in thine hand. And thou shalt say unto him, The LORD, God of

00:28:26.460 --> 00:28:32.120
the Hebrews, hath sent me unto thee, saying, Let my people go, that they may serve me in

00:28:32.120 --> 00:28:38.820
the wilderness, and behold, hitherto thou wouldest not here. Thus saith the LORD, In

00:28:38.820 --> 00:28:44.240
this thou shalt know that I am the LORD. Behold, I will smite with the rod that is in mine

00:28:44.240 --> 00:28:49.860
hand upon the waters which are in the river, and they shall be turned to blood. And the

00:28:49.860 --> 00:28:54.800
fish that is in the river shall die, and the river shall stink, and the Egyptians shall

00:28:54.800 --> 00:29:01.480
loathe to drink of the water of the river. And the LORD spake unto Moses, Say unto Aaron,

00:29:01.720 --> 00:29:07.440
Take thy rod, and stretch out thine hand upon the waters of Egypt, upon their streams, upon

00:29:07.440 --> 00:29:13.200
their rivers, and upon their ponds, and upon all their pools of water, that they may become

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:18.440
blood, and that there may be blood throughout all the land of Egypt, both in vessels of

00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:25.940
wood and in vessels of stone. And Moses and Aaron did so as the LORD commanded, and he

00:29:25.940 --> 00:29:30.700
lifted up the rod and smote the waters that were in the river in the sight of Pharaoh

00:29:30.700 --> 00:29:35.820
and in the sight of his servants, and all the waters that were in the river were turned

00:29:35.820 --> 00:29:41.820
to blood. And the fish that was in the river died, and the river stank, and the Egyptians

00:29:41.820 --> 00:29:46.520
could not drink of the water of the river, and there was blood throughout all the land

00:29:46.520 --> 00:29:52.420
of Egypt. And the magicians of Egypt did so with their enchantments, and Pharaoh's heart

00:29:52.420 --> 00:29:58.920
was hardened, neither did he hearken unto them, as the LORD had said. And Pharaoh turned

00:29:58.920 --> 00:30:05.440
and went into his house, neither did he set his heart to this also. And all the Egyptians

00:30:05.440 --> 00:30:10.080
digged round about the river for water to drink, for they could not drink of the water

00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:15.940
of the river. And seven days were fulfilled after that the LORD had smitten the river.

00:30:17.180 --> 00:30:21.780
And the LORD spake unto Moses, Go unto Pharaoh,

00:30:22.020 --> 00:30:27.900
and say unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Let my people go, that they may serve me. And

00:30:27.900 --> 00:30:33.800
if thou refuse to let them go, behold, I will smite all thy borders with frogs, and the

00:30:33.800 --> 00:30:38.760
river shall bring forth frogs abundantly, which shall go up and come into thine house

00:30:38.760 --> 00:30:44.580
and into thy bed-chamber, and upon thy bed, and into the house of thy servants, and upon

00:30:44.580 --> 00:30:49.760
thy people, and into thine ovens, and into thy kneading-troughs. And the frogs shall

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:54.380
come up both on thee, and upon thy people, and upon all thy servants.

00:30:55.520 --> 00:31:01.360
And the LORD spake unto Moses, Say unto Aaron, Stretch forth thine hand with thy rod over

00:31:01.360 --> 00:31:07.040
the streams, over the rivers, and over the ponds, and cause frogs to come up upon the

00:31:07.040 --> 00:31:13.080
land of Egypt. And Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt, and the frogs

00:31:13.080 --> 00:31:18.860
came up, and covered the land of Egypt. And the magicians did so with their enchantments,

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:25.320
and brought up frogs upon the land of Egypt. Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron, and

00:31:25.320 --> 00:31:30.860
said, Entreat the LORD, that he may take away the frogs from me, and from my people, and

00:31:30.860 --> 00:31:34.460
I will let the people go, that they may do sacrifice unto the LORD.

00:31:35.560 --> 00:31:41.840
And Moses said unto Pharaoh, Glory over me! when shall I entreat for thee, and for thy

00:31:41.840 --> 00:31:47.100
servants, and for thy people, to destroy the frogs from thee and thy houses, that they

00:31:47.100 --> 00:31:54.180
may remain in the river only? And he said, To-morrow. And he said, Be it according to

00:31:54.180 --> 00:32:00.180
thy word, that thou mayest know that there is none like unto the LORD our God. And the

00:32:00.180 --> 00:32:04.820
frogs shall depart from thee, and from thy houses, and from thy servants, and from thy

00:32:04.820 --> 00:32:10.980
people, they shall remain in the river only. And Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh,

00:32:11.400 --> 00:32:15.840
and Moses cried unto the LORD because of the frogs which he had brought against Pharaoh.

00:32:16.820 --> 00:32:21.560
And the LORD did according to the word of Moses, and the frogs died out of the houses,

00:32:21.920 --> 00:32:26.960
out of the villages, and out of the fields. And they gathered them together upon heaps,

00:32:26.960 --> 00:32:33.040
and the land stank. But when Pharaoh saw that there was respite, he hardened his heart,

00:32:33.280 --> 00:32:39.860
and hearkened not unto them, as the LORD had said. And the LORD said unto Moses, Say unto

00:32:39.860 --> 00:32:45.160
Aaron, Stretch out thy rod, and smite the dust of the land, that it may become lice

00:32:45.160 --> 00:32:50.840
throughout all the land of Egypt. And they did so, for Aaron stretched out his hand with

00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:57.120
his rod, and smote the dust of the earth, and it became lice in man, and in beast, all

00:32:57.120 --> 00:33:02.440
the dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt. And the magicians did

00:33:02.440 --> 00:33:07.760
so with their enchantments to bring forth lice, but they could not, so there were lice

00:33:07.760 --> 00:33:14.500
upon man and upon beast. Then the magicians said unto Pharaoh, This is the finger of God.

00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:20.080
And Pharaoh's heart was hardened, and he hearkened not unto them, as the LORD had said.

00:33:21.440 --> 00:33:27.060
And the LORD said unto Moses, Rise up early in the morning, and stand before Pharaoh,

00:33:27.720 --> 00:33:33.960
lo he cometh forth to the water, and say unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Let my people go,

00:33:34.080 --> 00:33:40.040
that they may serve me. Else, if thou wilt not let my people go, behold, I will send

00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:46.200
swarms of flies upon thee, and upon thy servants, and upon thy people, and into thy houses,

00:33:46.860 --> 00:33:52.820
and the houses of the Egyptians shall be full of swarms of flies, and also the ground whereon

00:33:52.820 --> 00:33:58.860
they are. And I will sever in that day the land of Goshen, in which my people dwell,

00:33:59.160 --> 00:34:04.620
that no swarms of flies shall be there, to the end thou mayest know that I am the LORD

00:34:04.620 --> 00:34:10.280
in the midst of the earth. And I will put a division between my people and thy people,

00:34:10.600 --> 00:34:16.940
to-morrow shall this sign be. And the LORD did so, and there came a grievous swarm of

00:34:16.940 --> 00:34:21.820
flies into the house of Pharaoh, and into his servants' houses, and into all the land

00:34:21.820 --> 00:34:28.060
of Egypt, the land was corrupted by reason of the swarm of flies. And Pharaoh called

00:34:28.060 --> 00:34:35.900
Aaron, and said, Go ye, sacrifice to your God in the land. And Moses said, It is not

00:34:35.900 --> 00:34:41.220
meet so to do, for we shall sacrifice the abomination of the Egyptians to the LORD our

00:34:41.220 --> 00:34:47.420
God. Lo, shall we sacrifice the abomination of the Egyptians before their eyes, and will

00:34:47.420 --> 00:34:53.340
they not stone us? We will go three days' journey into the wilderness, and sacrifice

00:34:53.340 --> 00:34:59.540
to the LORD our God, as he shall command us. And Pharaoh said, I will let you go, that

00:34:59.540 --> 00:35:04.880
ye may sacrifice to the LORD your God in the wilderness, only ye shall not go very far

00:35:04.880 --> 00:35:12.140
away. Entreat for me. And Moses said, Behold, I go out from thee, and I will entreat the

00:35:12.140 --> 00:35:17.660
LORD that the swarms of flies may depart from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people

00:35:17.660 --> 00:35:24.140
tomorrow. But let not Pharaoh deal deceitfully any more in not letting the people go to sacrifice

00:35:24.140 --> 00:35:31.100
to the LORD. And Moses went out from Pharaoh, and entreated the LORD. And the LORD did according

00:35:31.100 --> 00:35:36.380
to the word of Moses, and he removed the swarms of flies from Pharaoh, from his servants,

00:35:36.640 --> 00:35:43.020
and from his people. There remained not one. And Pharaoh heartened his heart at this time

00:35:43.020 --> 00:35:46.100
also. Neither would he let the people go.

00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:55.120
Then the LORD said unto Moses, Go in unto Pharaoh, and tell him, Thus saith the LORD,

00:35:55.160 --> 00:36:01.360
God of the Hebrews, Let my people go, that they may serve me. For if thou refuse to let

00:36:01.360 --> 00:36:06.980
them go, and wilt hold them still, behold, the hand of the LORD is upon thy cattle which

00:36:06.980 --> 00:36:13.500
is in the field, upon the horses, upon the asses, upon the camels, upon the oxen, and

00:36:13.500 --> 00:36:19.660
upon the sheep, there shall be a very grievous moraine. And the LORD shall sever between

00:36:19.660 --> 00:36:24.900
the cattle of Israel and the cattle of Egypt, and there shall nothing die of all that is

00:36:24.900 --> 00:36:31.740
the childrens of Israel. And the LORD appointed a set time, saying, Tomorrow the LORD shall

00:36:31.740 --> 00:36:37.360
do this thing in the land. And the LORD did that thing on the morrow, and all the cattle

00:36:37.360 --> 00:36:44.480
of Egypt died, but of the cattle of the children of Israel died not one. And Pharaoh sent,

00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:50.200
and behold, there was not one of the cattle of the Israelites dead. And the heart of Pharaoh

00:36:50.200 --> 00:36:53.340
was hardened, and he did not let the people go.

00:36:54.680 --> 00:37:00.160
And the LORD said unto Moses and unto Aaron, Take to you handfuls of ashes of the furnace,

00:37:00.160 --> 00:37:06.200
and let Moses sprinkle it toward the heaven in the sight of Pharaoh. And it shall become

00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:11.620
small dust in all the land of Egypt, and shall be a boil breaking forth with blains upon

00:37:11.620 --> 00:37:18.080
man and upon beast throughout all the land of Egypt. And they took ashes of the furnace

00:37:18.080 --> 00:37:24.200
and stood before Pharaoh, and Moses sprinkled it up toward heaven, and it became a boil

00:37:24.200 --> 00:37:30.980
breaking forth with blains upon man and upon beast. And the magicians could not stand before

00:37:30.980 --> 00:37:36.940
Moses because of the boils, for the boil was upon the magicians and upon all the Egyptians.

00:37:38.020 --> 00:37:42.840
And the LORD hardened the heart of Pharaoh, and he harkened not unto them as the LORD

00:37:42.840 --> 00:37:48.720
had spoken unto Moses. And the LORD said unto Moses, Rise up early

00:37:48.720 --> 00:37:54.520
in the morning, and stand before Pharaoh, and say unto him, Thus saith the LORD God

00:37:54.520 --> 00:38:00.900
of the Hebrews, Let my people go that they may serve me. For I will at this time send

00:38:00.900 --> 00:38:06.860
all my plagues upon thine heart, and upon thy servants, and upon thy people, that thou

00:38:06.860 --> 00:38:12.560
mayest know that there is none like me in all the earth. For now I will stretch out

00:38:12.560 --> 00:38:18.340
my hand that I may smite thee and thy people with pestilence, and thou shalt be cut off

00:38:18.340 --> 00:38:24.380
from the earth. And in very deed for this cause have I raised thee up, for to show in

00:38:24.380 --> 00:38:31.280
thee my power, and that my name may be declared throughout all the earth. As yet exaltest

00:38:31.280 --> 00:38:37.480
thou thyself against my people, that thou wilt not let them go? Behold, to-morrow, about

00:38:37.480 --> 00:38:43.300
this time, I will cause it to rain a very grievous hail, such as hath not been in Egypt

00:38:43.300 --> 00:38:46.380
since the foundation thereof even until now.

00:38:47.740 --> 00:38:53.140
Send therefore now, and gather thy cattle, and all that thou hast in the field, for upon

00:38:53.140 --> 00:38:57.860
every man and beast which shall be found in the field, and shall not be brought home,

00:38:58.320 --> 00:39:04.120
the hail shall come down upon them, and they shall die. He that feared the word of the

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:09.080
LORD among the servants of Pharaoh, made his servants and his cattle flee into the houses.

00:39:09.680 --> 00:39:14.920
And he that regarded not the word of the LORD left his servants and his cattle in the field.

00:39:16.220 --> 00:39:21.280
And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch forth thine hand toward heaven, that there may be

00:39:21.280 --> 00:39:27.420
hail in all the land of Egypt, upon man and upon beast, and upon every herb of the field

00:39:27.420 --> 00:39:33.580
throughout the land of Egypt. And Moses stretched forth his rod toward heaven, and the LORD

00:39:33.580 --> 00:39:39.240
sent thunder and hail, and the fire ran along upon the ground, and the LORD rained hail

00:39:39.240 --> 00:39:45.460
upon the land of Egypt. So there was hail and fire mingled with the hail, very grievous,

00:39:45.820 --> 00:39:51.640
such as there was none like it in all the land of Egypt since it became a nation. And

00:39:51.640 --> 00:39:55.980
the hail smote throughout all the land of Egypt all that was in the field, both man

00:39:55.980 --> 00:40:01.840
and beast. And the hail smote every herb of the field, and break every tree of the field.

00:40:01.840 --> 00:40:06.940
Only in the land of Goshen, where the children of Israel were, was there no hail.

00:40:08.240 --> 00:40:14.040
And Pharaoh sent and called for Moses and Aaron, and said unto them, I have sinned this time,

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:20.820
the LORD is righteous, and I and my people are wicked. Entreat the LORD, for it is enough

00:40:20.820 --> 00:40:25.940
that there be no more mighty thunderings and hail, and I will let you go, and ye shall

00:40:25.940 --> 00:40:32.780
no longer. And Moses said unto him, As soon as I am gone out of the city, I will spread

00:40:32.780 --> 00:40:38.340
abroad my hands unto the LORD, and the thunder shall cease, neither shall there be any more

00:40:38.340 --> 00:40:45.060
hail, that thou mayest know how that the earth is the LORD's. But as for thee and thy servants,

00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:51.480
I know that ye will not yet fear the LORD God. And the flax and the barley was smitten,

00:40:51.480 --> 00:40:57.920
for the barley was in the ear, and the flax was bald. But the wheat and the rye were not

00:40:57.920 --> 00:41:03.700
smitten, for they were not grown up. And Moses went out of the city from Pharaoh,

00:41:04.160 --> 00:41:09.380
and spread abroad his hands unto the LORD, and the thunders and hails ceased, and the

00:41:09.380 --> 00:41:15.080
rain was not poured upon the earth. And when Pharaoh saw that the rain and the hail and

00:41:15.080 --> 00:41:20.820
the thunders were ceased, he sinned yet more, and hardened his heart, he and his servants.

00:41:21.620 --> 00:41:26.520
And the heart of Pharaoh was hardened, neither would he let the children of Israel go,

00:41:31.560 --> 00:41:36.920
And the LORD said unto Moses, Go in unto Pharaoh, for I have hardened his heart,

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:42.940
and the heart of his servants, that I might show these my signs before him, and that thou

00:41:42.940 --> 00:41:49.080
mayest tell in the ears of thy son, and of thy son's son, what things I have wrought in Egypt,

00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:54.320
and my signs which I have done among them, that ye may know how that I am the LORD.

00:41:55.380 --> 00:42:01.440
And Moses and Aaron came in unto Pharaoh, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD God of the

00:42:01.440 --> 00:42:07.580
Hebrews, How long wilt thou refuse to humble thyself before me? Let my people go, that they

00:42:07.580 --> 00:42:14.220
may serve me. Else if thou refuse to let my people go, behold, to-morrow will I bring the

00:42:14.220 --> 00:42:20.240
locusts into thy coast, and they shall cover the face of the earth that one cannot be able to see

00:42:20.240 --> 00:42:25.600
the earth, and they shall eat the residue of that which is escaped, which remaineth unto you from

00:42:25.600 --> 00:42:31.740
the hail, and shall eat every tree which groweth for you out of the field. And they shall fill

00:42:31.740 --> 00:42:37.940
thy houses, and the houses of all thy servants, and the houses of all the Egyptians, which neither

00:42:37.940 --> 00:42:43.420
thy fathers nor thy fathers' fathers have seen since the day that they were upon the earth,

00:42:43.420 --> 00:42:50.480
unto this day. And he turned himself, and went out from Pharaoh. And Pharaoh's servants said unto

00:42:50.480 --> 00:42:56.780
him, How long shall this man be a snare unto us? Let the men go, that they may serve the LORD their

00:42:56.780 --> 00:43:04.320
God. Knowest thou not yet that Egypt is destroyed? And Moses and Aaron were brought again unto Pharaoh,

00:43:04.700 --> 00:43:10.380
and he said unto them, Go, serve the LORD your God. But who are they that shall go?

00:43:10.940 --> 00:43:16.480
And Moses said, We will go with our young, and with our old, with our sons, and with our daughters,

00:43:16.860 --> 00:43:21.980
with our flocks, and with our herds will we go. For we must hold a feast unto the LORD.

00:43:22.640 --> 00:43:28.080
And he said unto them, Let the LORD be so with you, as I will let you go, and your little ones.

00:43:28.540 --> 00:43:35.560
Look to it, for evil is before you. Not so. Go now ye that are men, and serve the LORD.

00:43:35.560 --> 00:43:40.160
For that ye did desire. And they were driven out from Pharaoh's presence.

00:43:41.360 --> 00:43:47.040
And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand over the land of Egypt for the locusts,

00:43:47.060 --> 00:43:52.540
that they may come up upon the land of Egypt, and eat every herb of the land, even all that the

00:43:52.540 --> 00:43:59.160
hail hath left. And Moses stretched forth his rod over the land of Egypt, and the LORD brought an

00:43:59.160 --> 00:44:05.540
east wind upon the land all that day, and all that night. And when it was morning the east wind

00:44:05.540 --> 00:44:12.000
brought the locusts. And the locusts went up over all the land of Egypt, and rested on all the

00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:18.640
coasts of Egypt. Very grievous were they. Before them there were no such locusts as they. Neither

00:44:18.640 --> 00:44:24.250
after them shall be such. For they covered the face of the whole earth, so that the land was

00:44:24.250 --> 00:44:30.370
darkened. And they did eat every herb of the land, and all the fruit of the trees which the hail had

00:44:30.370 --> 00:44:35.850
left. And there remained not any green thing in the trees, or in the herbs of the field,

00:44:36.110 --> 00:44:42.630
through all the land of Egypt. Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron in haste, and he said,

00:44:42.930 --> 00:44:48.990
I have sinned against the LORD your God, and against you. Now therefore forgive, I pray thee,

00:44:49.550 --> 00:44:55.530
only this once, and entreat the LORD your God, that he may take away from me this death only.

00:44:56.430 --> 00:45:02.730
And he went out from Pharaoh, and entreated the LORD. And the LORD turned a mighty strong west

00:45:02.730 --> 00:45:09.310
wind, which took away the locusts, and cast them into the Red Sea. There remained not one locust

00:45:09.310 --> 00:45:15.670
in all the coasts of Egypt. But the LORD hardened Pharaoh's heart, so that he would not let the

00:45:15.670 --> 00:45:22.490
children of Israel go. And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand toward heaven,

00:45:22.930 --> 00:45:29.350
that there may be darkness over the land of Egypt, even darkness which may be felt. And Moses

00:45:29.350 --> 00:45:35.630
stretched forth his hand toward heaven, and there was a thick darkness in all the land of Egypt three

00:45:35.630 --> 00:45:42.730
days. They saw not one another, neither rose any from his place, for three days. But all the children

00:45:42.730 --> 00:45:49.610
of Israel had light in their dwellings. And Pharaoh called unto Moses, and said, Go ye,

00:45:49.770 --> 00:45:56.310
serve the LORD, only let your flocks and your herds be stayed, let your little ones also go with you.

00:45:56.950 --> 00:46:03.350
And Moses said, Thou must give us also sacrifices and burnt offerings, that we may sacrifice unto

00:46:03.350 --> 00:46:09.710
the LORD our God. Our cattle also shall go with us, there shall not an hoof be left behind,

00:46:09.710 --> 00:46:16.190
for thereof must we take to serve the LORD our God. And we know not with what we must serve the

00:46:16.190 --> 00:46:22.970
LORD until we come thither. But the LORD hardened Pharaoh's heart, and he would not let them go.

00:46:24.110 --> 00:46:30.270
And Pharaoh said unto him, Get thee from me, take heed thyself, see my face no more,

00:46:30.670 --> 00:46:37.770
for in that day thou seest my face, thou shalt die. And Moses said, Thou hast spoken well,

00:46:37.770 --> 00:46:40.470
I will see thy face again no more.

00:46:42.090 --> 00:46:45.150
And the LORD said unto Moses,

00:46:45.490 --> 00:46:52.030
Yet will I bring one plague more upon Pharaoh and upon Egypt. Afterwards he will let you go hence.

00:46:52.430 --> 00:46:56.810
When he shall let you go, he shall surely thrust you out hence altogether.

00:46:58.230 --> 00:47:02.470
Speak now in the ears of the people, and let every man borrow of his neighbor,

00:47:02.690 --> 00:47:06.990
and every woman of her neighbor, jewels of silver and jewels of gold.

00:47:07.770 --> 00:47:14.030
And the LORD gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians. Moreover the man Moses was very

00:47:14.030 --> 00:47:19.530
great in the land of Egypt, in the sight of Pharaoh's servants, and in the sight of the people.

00:47:20.470 --> 00:47:26.430
And Moses said, Thus saith the LORD, About midnight will I go out into the midst of Egypt,

00:47:27.010 --> 00:47:32.110
and all the first born in the land of Egypt shall die, from the first born of Pharaoh that

00:47:32.110 --> 00:47:37.470
sitteth upon his throne, even unto the first born of the maid-servant that is behind the mill,

00:47:37.770 --> 00:47:44.290
and all the first born of beasts. And there shall be a great cry throughout all the land of Egypt,

00:47:44.630 --> 00:47:51.110
such as there was none like it, nor shall be like it any more. But against any of the children of

00:47:51.110 --> 00:47:57.910
Israel shall not a dog move his tongue against man or beast, that ye may know how that the LORD

00:47:57.910 --> 00:48:04.590
doth put a difference between the Egyptians and Israel. And all these thy servants shall come down

00:48:04.590 --> 00:48:10.770
unto me, and bow down themselves unto me, saying, Get thee out, and all the people that follow thee,

00:48:11.150 --> 00:48:16.370
and after that I will go out. And he went out from Pharaoh in a great anger.

00:48:17.430 --> 00:48:23.370
And the LORD said unto Moses, Pharaoh shall not hearken unto you, that my wonders may be multiplied

00:48:23.370 --> 00:48:29.770
in the land of Egypt. And Moses and Aaron did all these wonders before Pharaoh, and the LORD

00:48:29.770 --> 00:48:35.650
hardened Pharaoh's heart, so that he would not let the children of Israel go out of his hand.

00:49:07.910 --> 00:49:13.730
And the Lord spake unto Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, saying, This month shall

00:49:13.730 --> 00:49:18.210
be unto you the beginning of months, it shall be the first month of the year to you.

00:49:19.370 --> 00:49:24.450
Speak ye unto all the congregation of Israel, saying, In the tenth day of this month they

00:49:24.450 --> 00:49:29.650
shall take to them every man a lamb, according to the house of their fathers, a lamb for

00:49:29.650 --> 00:49:30.290
an house.

00:49:30.850 --> 00:49:35.630
And if the household be too little for the lamb, let him and his neighbour next unto

00:49:35.630 --> 00:49:40.850
his house take it according to the number of the souls, every man according to his eating

00:49:40.850 --> 00:49:42.750
shall make your account for the lamb.

00:49:43.670 --> 00:49:48.650
Your lamb shall be without blemish a male of the first year, ye shall take it out from

00:49:48.650 --> 00:49:53.690
the sheep or from the goats, and ye shall keep it up until the fourteenth day of the

00:49:53.690 --> 00:49:58.310
same month, and the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill it in the

00:49:58.310 --> 00:49:58.710
evening.

00:49:59.370 --> 00:50:04.130
And they shall take up the blood and strike it on the two side-posts and on the upper

00:50:04.130 --> 00:50:07.370
door-post of the houses wherein they shall eat it.

00:50:08.070 --> 00:50:13.450
And they shall eat the flesh in that night, roast with fire and unleavened bread, and

00:50:13.450 --> 00:50:15.550
with bitter herbs they shall eat it.

00:50:16.270 --> 00:50:22.410
Eat not of it raw nor sodden at all with water, but roast with fire, his head with his legs

00:50:22.410 --> 00:50:24.290
and with the pertenance thereof.

00:50:25.130 --> 00:50:29.710
And ye shall let nothing of it remain until the morning, and that which remaineth of it

00:50:29.710 --> 00:50:32.030
until the morning ye shall burn with fire.

00:50:32.770 --> 00:50:37.970
And thus shall ye eat it, with your loins girded, your shoes on your feet, and your

00:50:37.970 --> 00:50:42.610
staff in your hand, and ye shall eat it in haste, it is the Lord's Passover.

00:50:43.790 --> 00:50:48.670
For I will pass through the land of Egypt this night, and will smite all the first born

00:50:48.670 --> 00:50:54.630
in the land of Egypt, both man and beast, and against all the gods of Egypt I will execute

00:50:54.630 --> 00:50:55.110
judgment.

00:50:55.470 --> 00:50:56.730
I am the Lord.

00:50:56.730 --> 00:51:02.490
And the blood shall be to you for a token upon the houses where ye are, and when I see

00:51:02.490 --> 00:51:08.050
the blood I will pass over you, and the plague shall not be upon you to destroy you when

00:51:08.050 --> 00:51:09.850
I smite the land of Egypt.

00:51:10.830 --> 00:51:16.350
And this day shall be unto you for a memorial, and ye shall keep it a feast to the Lord throughout

00:51:16.350 --> 00:51:20.890
your generations, ye shall keep it a feast by an ordinance for ever.

00:51:21.910 --> 00:51:27.450
Seven days shall ye eat unleavened bread, even the first day ye shall put away leaven

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:33.130
out of your houses, for whosoever eateth leavened bread from the first day until the seventh

00:51:33.130 --> 00:51:36.530
day, that soul shall be cut off from Israel.

00:51:37.450 --> 00:51:42.630
And in the first day there shall be an holy convocation, and in the seventh day there

00:51:42.630 --> 00:51:44.750
shall be an holy convocation to you.

00:51:45.110 --> 00:51:50.870
No matter of work shall be done in them save that which every man must eat, that only may

00:51:50.870 --> 00:51:51.890
be done of you.

00:51:52.790 --> 00:51:58.450
And ye shall observe the feast of unleavened bread, for in this selfsame day have I brought

00:51:58.450 --> 00:52:04.330
your armies out of the land of Egypt, therefore shall ye observe this day in your generations

00:52:04.330 --> 00:52:06.370
by an ordinance for ever.

00:52:07.730 --> 00:52:12.430
In the first month on the fourteenth day of the month at even ye shall eat unleavened

00:52:12.430 --> 00:52:15.870
bread until the one and twentieth day of the month at even.

00:52:16.670 --> 00:52:22.310
Seven days shall there be no leaven found in your houses, for whosoever eateth that

00:52:22.310 --> 00:52:27.730
which is leavened, even that soul shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether

00:52:27.730 --> 00:52:30.250
he be a stranger or born in the land.

00:52:31.150 --> 00:52:36.550
Ye shall eat nothing leavened, and all your habitations shall ye eat unleavened bread.

00:52:38.650 --> 00:52:44.470
Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said unto them, Draw out and take you

00:52:44.470 --> 00:52:47.870
a lamb according to your families and kill the Passover.

00:52:48.790 --> 00:52:53.970
And ye shall take a bunch of hyssop and dip it in the blood that is in the basin and strike

00:52:53.970 --> 00:52:59.350
the lintel and the two side-posts with the blood that is in the basin, and none of you

00:52:59.350 --> 00:53:02.350
shall go out at the door of his house until the morning.

00:53:03.250 --> 00:53:08.490
For the Lord will pass through to smite the Egyptians, and when he seeth the blood upon

00:53:08.490 --> 00:53:14.450
the lintel and on the two side-posts the Lord will pass over the door and will not suffer

00:53:14.450 --> 00:53:18.150
the destroyer to come in unto your houses to smite you.

00:53:18.710 --> 00:53:23.830
And ye shall observe this thing for an ordinance to thee and to thy sons for ever.

00:53:24.810 --> 00:53:29.810
And it shall come to pass when ye become to the land which the Lord will give you according

00:53:29.810 --> 00:53:33.130
as he hath promised that ye shall keep this service.

00:53:33.710 --> 00:53:39.210
And it shall come to pass when your children shall say unto you, What mean ye by this service,

00:53:39.510 --> 00:53:45.210
that ye shall say, It is the sacrifice of the Lord's Passover who passed over the houses

00:53:45.210 --> 00:53:50.730
of the children of Israel in Egypt when he smote the Egyptians and delivered our houses.

00:53:51.410 --> 00:53:53.850
And the people bowed the head and worshipped.

00:53:54.690 --> 00:53:59.550
And the children of Israel went away and did as the Lord had commanded Moses and Aaron,

00:53:59.870 --> 00:54:00.970
so did they.

00:54:02.170 --> 00:54:07.710
And it came to pass that at midnight the Lord smote all the first born in the land of Egypt

00:54:07.710 --> 00:54:13.070
from the first born of Pharaoh that sat on his throne under the first born of the captive

00:54:13.070 --> 00:54:16.670
that was in the dungeon and all the first born of cattle.

00:54:17.930 --> 00:54:23.870
And Pharaoh rose up in the night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians, and there

00:54:23.870 --> 00:54:29.130
was a great cry in Egypt, for there was not a house where there was not one dead.

00:54:30.130 --> 00:54:36.090
And he called for Moses and Aaron by night and said, Rise up and get you forth from among

00:54:36.090 --> 00:54:42.010
my people, both ye and the children of Israel, and go, serve the Lord, as ye have said.

00:54:42.750 --> 00:54:49.090
Also take your flocks and your herds, as ye have said, and be gone, and bless me also.

00:54:50.190 --> 00:54:54.730
And the Egyptians were urgent upon the people that they might send them out of the land

00:54:54.730 --> 00:54:58.250
in haste, for they said, We be all dead men.

00:54:58.910 --> 00:55:03.190
And the people took their dough before it was leavened, their kneading troughs being

00:55:03.190 --> 00:55:08.690
bound up and their clothes upon their shoulders. And the children of Israel did according to

00:55:08.690 --> 00:55:14.230
the word of Moses, and they borrowed of the Egyptians jewels of silver and jewels of gold

00:55:14.230 --> 00:55:19.830
and raiment. And the Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that

00:55:19.830 --> 00:55:24.610
they lent unto them such things as they required, and they spoiled the Egyptians.

00:55:26.250 --> 00:55:31.710
And the children of Israel journeyed from Ramesses to Succoth, about six hundred thousand

00:55:31.710 --> 00:55:38.330
on foot that were men, beside children. And a mixed multitude went up also with them,

00:55:38.550 --> 00:55:44.810
and flocks and herds, even very much cattle. And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough

00:55:44.810 --> 00:55:49.650
which they brought forth out of Egypt, for it was not leavened, because they were thrust

00:55:49.650 --> 00:55:54.670
out of Egypt and could not tarry, neither had they prepared for themselves any victual.

00:55:55.990 --> 00:56:00.790
Now the sojourning of the children of Israel who dwelt in Egypt was four hundred and thirty

00:56:00.790 --> 00:56:07.070
years. And it came to pass at the end of the four hundred and thirty years, even the selfsame

00:56:07.070 --> 00:56:12.110
day had came to pass, that all the hosts of the Lord went out from the land of Egypt.

00:56:13.030 --> 00:56:17.370
It is a night to be much observed unto the Lord for bringing them out from the land of

00:56:17.370 --> 00:56:22.510
Egypt. This is that night of the Lord to be observed of all the children of Israel in

00:56:22.510 --> 00:56:23.470
their generations.

00:56:24.330 --> 00:56:29.690
And the Lord said unto Moses and Aaron, This is the ordinance of the Passover. There shall

00:56:29.690 --> 00:56:34.930
no stranger eat thereof, but every man's servant that has bought for money, when thou hast

00:56:34.930 --> 00:56:40.890
circumcised him, then shall he eat thereof. A foreigner and an hired servant shall not

00:56:40.890 --> 00:56:46.830
eat thereof. In one house shall it be eaten, thou shalt not carry forth aught of the flesh

00:56:46.830 --> 00:56:52.730
abroad out of the house, neither shall ye break a bone thereof. All the congregation

00:56:52.730 --> 00:56:58.150
of Israel shall keep it. And when a stranger shall sojourn with thee, and will keep the

00:56:58.150 --> 00:57:03.630
Passover to the Lord, let all his meals be circumcised, and then let him come near and

00:57:03.630 --> 00:57:09.510
keep it, and he shall be as one that is born in the land, for no uncircumcised person shall

00:57:09.510 --> 00:57:16.190
eat thereof. One law shall be to him that is home-born, and unto the stranger that sojourneth

00:57:16.190 --> 00:57:16.950
among you.

00:57:17.970 --> 00:57:23.550
Thus did all the children of Israel, as the Lord commanded Moses and Aaron, so did they.

00:57:24.250 --> 00:57:28.830
And it came to pass the selfsame day that the Lord did bring the children of Israel

00:57:28.830 --> 00:57:31.410
out of the land of Egypt by their armies.

00:57:35.270 --> 00:57:41.670
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Sanctify unto me all the first born, whatsoever openeth

00:57:41.670 --> 00:57:48.470
the womb among the children of Israel, both of man and of beast, it is mine. And Moses

00:57:48.470 --> 00:57:53.670
said unto the people, Remember this day in which ye came out from Egypt out of the house

00:57:53.670 --> 00:57:59.050
of bondage, for by strength of hand the Lord brought you out from this place, there shall

00:57:59.050 --> 00:58:00.710
no leavened bread be eaten.

00:58:01.930 --> 00:58:04.950
This day came ye out in the month Abib.

00:58:06.470 --> 00:58:10.410
And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, and

00:58:10.410 --> 00:58:15.670
the Hittites, and the Amorites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, which he swear unto thy

00:58:15.670 --> 00:58:21.230
fathers to give thee a land flowing with milk and honey, that thou shalt keep this service

00:58:21.230 --> 00:58:22.090
in this month.

00:58:23.210 --> 00:58:27.810
Seven days thou shalt eat unleavened bread, and in the seventh day shall be a feast to

00:58:27.810 --> 00:58:28.330
the Lord.

00:58:29.430 --> 00:58:33.930
Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days, and there shall no leavened bread be seen

00:58:33.930 --> 00:58:37.870
with thee, neither shall there be leaven seen with thee in all thy quarters.

00:58:38.970 --> 00:58:44.210
And thou shalt show thy son in that day, saying, This is done because of that which the Lord

00:58:44.210 --> 00:58:46.730
did unto me when I came forth out of Egypt.

00:58:47.670 --> 00:58:52.590
And it shall be for a sign unto thee upon thine hand, and for a memorial between thine

00:58:52.590 --> 00:58:58.290
eyes, that the Lord's law may be in thy mouth, for with a strong hand hath the Lord brought

00:58:58.290 --> 00:58:59.430
thee out of Egypt.

00:59:00.310 --> 00:59:04.150
Thou shalt therefore keep this ordinance in his season from year to year.

00:59:05.050 --> 00:59:13.750
And it shall be when the Lord shall bring thee into the land of the Canaanites, as he

00:59:13.750 --> 00:59:19.030
shalt set apart unto the Lord all that openeth the matrix, and every firstling that cometh

00:59:19.030 --> 00:59:23.130
of a beast which thou hast, the males shall be the Lord's.

00:59:23.590 --> 00:59:29.130
And every firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with a lamb, and if thou wilt not redeem it,

00:59:29.190 --> 00:59:33.830
then thou shalt break his neck, and all the firstborn of man among thy children shalt

00:59:33.830 --> 00:59:34.490
thou redeem.

00:59:35.370 --> 00:59:40.550
And it shall be when thy son asketh thee in time to come, saying, What is this?

00:59:40.550 --> 00:59:45.950
that thou shalt say unto him, By strength of hand the Lord brought us out of Egypt from

00:59:45.950 --> 00:59:47.390
the house of bondage.

00:59:47.930 --> 00:59:53.670
And it came to pass when Pharaoh would hardly let us go, that the Lord slew all the firstborn

00:59:53.670 --> 00:59:58.270
in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man and the firstborn of beast.

00:59:58.790 --> 01:00:04.610
Therefore I sacrificed to the Lord all that openeth the matrix, being males, but all the

01:00:04.610 --> 01:00:06.730
firstborn of my children I redeem.

01:00:07.490 --> 01:00:12.850
And it shall be for a token upon thine hand, and for frontlets between thine eyes, for

01:00:12.850 --> 01:00:16.110
by strength of hand the Lord brought us forth out of Egypt.

01:00:17.450 --> 01:00:22.190
And it came to pass when Pharaoh had let the people go, that God led them not through the

01:00:22.190 --> 01:00:27.770
way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near, for God said, Lest per adventure

01:00:27.770 --> 01:00:31.530
the people repent when they see war, and they return to Egypt.

01:00:32.080 --> 01:00:36.990
But God led the people about through the way of the wilderness of the Red Sea, and the

01:00:36.990 --> 01:00:40.490
children of Israel went up harnessed out of the land of Egypt.

01:00:41.590 --> 01:00:46.150
And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for he had straightly sworn the children of

01:00:46.150 --> 01:00:51.830
Israel, saying, God will surely visit you, and ye shall carry up my bones away hence

01:00:51.830 --> 01:00:52.650
with you.

01:00:53.870 --> 01:00:58.730
And they took their journey from Succoth and encamped in ethom in the edge of the wilderness.

01:00:59.270 --> 01:01:04.470
And the Lord went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud to lead them the way, and

01:01:04.470 --> 01:01:09.430
by night in a pillar of fire to give them light, to go by day and night.

01:01:09.930 --> 01:01:15.150
He took not away the pillar of the cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from

01:01:15.150 --> 01:01:16.250
before the people.

01:01:18.910 --> 01:01:24.630
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Speak unto the children of Israel that they turn

01:01:24.630 --> 01:01:30.790
and encamp forphi-hyrath between Migdal and the sea over against Baal-Ziphon.

01:01:30.950 --> 01:01:33.210
Before it shall ye encamp by the sea.

01:01:33.830 --> 01:01:38.930
For Pharaoh will say of the children of Israel, They are entangled in the land, the wilderness

01:01:38.930 --> 01:01:40.150
hath shut them in.

01:01:40.730 --> 01:01:45.870
And I will harden Pharaoh's heart that he shall follow after them, and I will be honored

01:01:45.870 --> 01:01:51.670
upon Pharaoh and upon all his host that the Egyptians may know that I am the Lord.

01:01:52.190 --> 01:01:53.290
And they did so.

01:01:54.590 --> 01:01:59.330
And it was told the King of Egypt that the people fled, and the heart of Pharaoh and

01:01:59.330 --> 01:02:04.430
of his servants was turned against the people, and they said, Why have we done this, that

01:02:04.430 --> 01:02:06.870
we have let Israel go from serving us?

01:02:07.650 --> 01:02:13.290
And he made ready his chariot and took his people with him, and he took six hundred chosen

01:02:13.290 --> 01:02:17.850
chariots and all the chariots of Egypt and captains over every one of them.

01:02:18.350 --> 01:02:23.650
And the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh, King of Egypt, and he pursued after the children

01:02:23.650 --> 01:02:27.690
of Israel, and the children of Israel went out with a high hand.

01:02:28.730 --> 01:02:34.470
But the Egyptians pursued after them all the horses and chariots of Pharaoh and his horsemen

01:02:34.470 --> 01:02:41.470
and his army, and overtook them encamping by the sea beside Piah-hyrath before Baal-Ziphon.

01:02:42.470 --> 01:02:47.210
And when Pharaoh drew nigh the children of Israel lifted up their eyes, and behold the

01:02:47.210 --> 01:02:52.490
Egyptians marched after them, and they were sore afraid, and the children of Israel cried

01:02:52.490 --> 01:02:53.810
out unto the Lord.

01:02:54.610 --> 01:02:59.990
And they said unto Moses, Because there were no graves in Egypt, hast thou taken us away

01:02:59.990 --> 01:03:01.410
to die in the wilderness?

01:03:02.050 --> 01:03:06.270
Wherefore hast thou dealt thus with us to carry us forth out of Egypt?

01:03:07.090 --> 01:03:12.190
Is not this the word that we did tell thee in Egypt, saying, Let us alone that we may

01:03:12.850 --> 01:03:18.790
for it had been better for us to serve the Egyptians than that we should die in the wilderness?

01:03:19.970 --> 01:03:26.030
And Moses said unto the people, Fear ye not, stand still, and see the salvation of the

01:03:26.030 --> 01:03:31.630
Lord which he will show to you to-day, for the Egyptians whom ye have seen to-day ye

01:03:31.630 --> 01:03:34.150
shall see them again no more for ever.

01:03:34.750 --> 01:03:38.390
The Lord shall fight for you, and ye shall hold your peace.

01:03:39.270 --> 01:03:44.950
And the Lord said unto Moses, Wherefore cryest thou unto me, Speak unto the children of

01:03:44.950 --> 01:03:50.310
Israel that they go forward, but lift thou up thy rod, and stretch out thine hand over

01:03:50.310 --> 01:03:55.530
the sea, and divide it, and the children of Israel shall go on dry ground through the

01:03:55.530 --> 01:03:56.590
midst of the sea.

01:03:57.250 --> 01:04:02.610
And I, behold I, will harden the hearts of the Egyptians, and they shall follow them,

01:04:02.610 --> 01:04:08.350
and I will get me honor upon Pharaoh, and upon all his host, upon his chariots, and

01:04:08.350 --> 01:04:09.470
upon his horsemen.

01:04:10.310 --> 01:04:15.510
And the Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I have gotten me honor upon Pharaoh,

01:04:15.850 --> 01:04:18.690
upon his chariots, and upon his horsemen.

01:04:20.090 --> 01:04:25.250
And the angel of God which went before the camp of Israel removed and went behind them,

01:04:25.530 --> 01:04:29.710
and the pillar of the cloud went from before their face and stood behind them.

01:04:29.710 --> 01:04:35.250
And it came between the cap of the Egyptians and the cap of Israel, and it was a cloud

01:04:35.250 --> 01:04:41.150
in darkness to them, but it gave light by night to these, so that the one came not near

01:04:41.150 --> 01:04:42.750
the other all the night.

01:04:43.790 --> 01:04:49.010
And Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and the Lord caused the sea to go back

01:04:49.010 --> 01:04:55.050
by a strong east wind all that night, and made the sea dry land, and the waters were

01:04:55.050 --> 01:04:55.510
divided.

01:04:56.250 --> 01:05:01.710
And the children of Israel went into the midst of the sea upon the dry ground, and the waters

01:05:01.710 --> 01:05:05.070
were a wall unto them on their right hand and on their left.

01:05:05.870 --> 01:05:11.270
And the Egyptians pursued and went in after them to the midst of the sea, even all Pharaoh's

01:05:11.270 --> 01:05:13.910
horses, his chariots, and his horsemen.

01:05:14.790 --> 01:05:19.570
And it came to pass that in the morning watch the Lord looked unto the host of the Egyptians

01:05:19.570 --> 01:05:24.970
through the pillar of fire and of the cloud, and troubled the host of the Egyptians, and

01:05:24.970 --> 01:05:30.370
took off their chariot wheels that they draved them heavily, so that the Egyptians said,

01:05:30.710 --> 01:05:35.970
Let us flee from the face of Israel, for the Lord fighteth for them against the Egyptians.

01:05:37.090 --> 01:05:42.370
And the Lord said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand over the sea, that the waters may

01:05:42.370 --> 01:05:47.270
come again upon the Egyptians, and upon their chariots, and upon their horsemen.

01:05:48.250 --> 01:05:53.070
And Moses stretched forth his hand over the sea, and the sea returned to his strength

01:05:53.070 --> 01:05:58.370
when the morning appeared, and the Egyptians fled against it, and the Lord overthrew the

01:05:58.370 --> 01:06:00.350
Egyptians in the midst of the sea.

01:06:01.410 --> 01:06:06.670
And the waters returned and covered the chariots, and the horsemen, and all the host of Pharaoh

01:06:06.670 --> 01:06:11.770
that came into the sea after them, there remained not so much as one of them.

01:06:12.510 --> 01:06:17.530
But the children of Israel walked upon dry land in the midst of the sea, and the waters

01:06:17.530 --> 01:06:20.830
were a wall unto them on their right hand and on their left.

01:06:21.670 --> 01:06:27.290
Thus the Lord saved Israel that day out of the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel saw

01:06:27.290 --> 01:06:29.990
the Egyptians dead upon the seashore.

01:06:30.910 --> 01:06:36.210
And Israel saw that great work which the Lord did upon the Egyptians, and the people feared

01:06:36.210 --> 01:06:39.850
the Lord and believed the Lord and His servant Moses.

01:06:44.010 --> 01:06:49.190
Then sang Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the Lord, and spake, saying,

01:06:49.190 --> 01:06:53.490
I will sing unto the Lord, for he hath triumphed gloriously.

01:06:53.890 --> 01:06:56.950
The horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.

01:06:58.170 --> 01:07:02.210
The Lord is my strength and song, and he has become my salvation.

01:07:02.790 --> 01:07:09.210
He is my God, and I will prepare him and habitation, my Father's God, and I will exalt him.

01:07:10.030 --> 01:07:13.430
The Lord is a man of war, the Lord is his name.

01:07:14.590 --> 01:07:17.890
Pharaoh's chariots and his host hath he cast into the sea.

01:07:18.350 --> 01:07:21.890
His chosen captains also are drowned in the Red Sea.

01:07:22.590 --> 01:07:24.070
The depths have covered them.

01:07:24.350 --> 01:07:26.550
They sank into the bottom as a stone.

01:07:27.510 --> 01:07:30.670
Thy right hand, O Lord, has become glorious in power.

01:07:31.150 --> 01:07:34.650
Thy right hand, O Lord, hath dashed in pieces the enemy.

01:07:35.330 --> 01:07:40.250
And in the greatness of thine excellency thou hast overthrown them that rose up against

01:07:40.250 --> 01:07:40.730
thee.

01:07:40.730 --> 01:07:45.130
Thou sentest forth thy wrath, which consumed them as stubble.

01:07:45.850 --> 01:07:51.030
And with the blast of thy nostrils the waters were gathered together, the floods stood upright

01:07:51.030 --> 01:07:54.870
as a heap, and the depths were congealed in the heart of the sea.

01:07:55.790 --> 01:08:02.110
The enemy said, I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide the spoil, my lust shall be

01:08:02.110 --> 01:08:06.890
satisfied upon them, I will draw my sword, my hand shall destroy them.

01:08:06.890 --> 01:08:13.430
Thou didst blow with thy wind, the sea covered them, they sank as lead in the mighty waters.

01:08:14.610 --> 01:08:17.530
Who is like unto thee, O Lord, among the gods?

01:08:17.890 --> 01:08:23.270
Who is like thee, glorious in holiness, fearful in praises, doing wonders?

01:08:24.330 --> 01:08:28.290
Thou stretchest out thy right hand, the earth swallowed them.

01:08:29.030 --> 01:08:34.190
Thou in thy mercy hast led forth the people which thou hast redeemed, thou hast guided

01:08:34.190 --> 01:08:37.530
them in thy strength unto thy holy habitation.

01:08:38.350 --> 01:08:44.250
The people shall hear and be afraid, sorrow shall take hold on the inhabitants of Palestine.

01:08:45.130 --> 01:08:50.490
Then the Dukes of Edom shall be amazed, the mighty men of Moab trembling shall take hold

01:08:50.490 --> 01:08:54.210
upon them, all the inhabitants of Canaan shall melt away.

01:08:54.950 --> 01:09:00.210
Fear and dread shall fall upon them, by the greatness of thine arm they shall be as still

01:09:00.210 --> 01:09:06.230
as a stone, till thy people pass over, O Lord, till the people pass over which thou hast

01:09:06.230 --> 01:09:06.930
purchased.

01:09:07.930 --> 01:09:12.410
Thou shalt bring them in and plant them in the mountain of thine inheritance, in the

01:09:12.410 --> 01:09:17.870
place, O Lord, which thou hast made for thee to dwell in, in the sanctuary, O Lord, which

01:09:17.870 --> 01:09:19.430
thy hands have established.

01:09:20.130 --> 01:09:23.090
The Lord shall reign for ever and ever.

01:09:23.570 --> 01:09:29.510
For the horse of Pharaoh went in with his chariots and with his horsemen into the sea, and the

01:09:29.510 --> 01:09:34.670
Lord brought again the waters of the sea upon them, but the children of Israel went on dry

01:09:34.670 --> 01:09:36.470
land in the midst of the sea.

01:09:37.910 --> 01:09:43.370
And Miriam the prophetess, the sister of Aaron, took a timbrel in her hand, and all the women

01:09:43.370 --> 01:09:46.170
went out after her with timbrels and with dances.

01:09:47.050 --> 01:09:53.130
And Miriam answered them, Sing ye to the Lord, for he hath triumphed gloriously, the horse

01:09:53.130 --> 01:09:55.650
and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.

01:09:56.270 --> 01:10:01.610
So Moses brought Israel from the Red Sea, and they went out into the wilderness of Shur,

01:10:02.030 --> 01:10:05.590
and they went three days in the wilderness, and found no water.

01:10:06.830 --> 01:10:11.110
And when they came to Marah, they could not drink of the waters of Marah, for they were

01:10:11.110 --> 01:10:14.210
bitter, therefore the name of it was called Marah.

01:10:15.090 --> 01:10:19.150
And the people murmured against Moses, saying, What shall we drink?

01:10:19.870 --> 01:10:25.290
And he cried unto the Lord, and the Lord showed him a tree, which, when he had cast into the

01:10:25.290 --> 01:10:27.510
waters, the waters were made sweet.

01:10:28.010 --> 01:10:34.430
There he made for them a statute and an ordinance, and there he proved them, and said, If thou

01:10:34.430 --> 01:10:39.630
wilt diligently hearken to the voice of the Lord thy God, and wilt do that which is right

01:10:39.630 --> 01:10:45.890
in his sight, and wilt give ear to his commandments, and keep all his statutes, I will put none

01:10:45.890 --> 01:10:51.990
of these diseases upon thee which I have brought upon the Egyptians, for I am the Lord that

01:10:51.990 --> 01:10:52.770
healeth thee.

01:10:53.750 --> 01:11:00.170
And they came to Elam, where were twelve wells of water, and threescore and ten palm-trees,

01:11:00.270 --> 01:11:02.470
and they encamped there by the waters.

01:11:06.830 --> 01:11:11.150
And they took their journey from Elam, and all the congregation of the children of Israel

01:11:11.150 --> 01:11:17.010
came unto the wilderness of Sin, which is between Elam and Sinai, on the fifteenth day

01:11:17.010 --> 01:11:20.830
after their departing out of the land of Egypt.

01:11:21.850 --> 01:11:26.350
And the whole congregation of the children of Israel murmured against Moses and Aaron

01:11:26.350 --> 01:11:31.930
in the wilderness, and the children of Israel said unto them, Would to God we had died by

01:11:31.930 --> 01:11:36.990
the hand of the Lord in the land of Egypt when we sat by the flesh-pots and when we

01:11:36.990 --> 01:11:41.790
did eat bread to the full, for ye have brought us forth into this wilderness to kill this

01:11:41.790 --> 01:11:43.230
whole assembly with hunger.

01:11:44.290 --> 01:11:50.350
Then said the Lord unto Moses, Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you, and the people

01:11:50.350 --> 01:11:55.630
shall go out and gather a certain rate every day, that I may prove them whether they will

01:11:55.630 --> 01:11:57.490
walk in my law or no.

01:11:58.190 --> 01:12:02.690
And it shall come to pass that on the sixth day they shall prepare that which they bring

01:12:02.690 --> 01:12:05.950
in, and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.

01:12:06.830 --> 01:12:12.670
And Moses and Aaron said unto all the children of Israel, At even, then ye shall know that

01:12:12.670 --> 01:12:17.490
the Lord hath brought you out from the land of Egypt, and in the morning then ye shall

01:12:17.490 --> 01:12:23.070
see the glory of the Lord, for that he heareth your murmurings against the Lord, and what

01:12:23.070 --> 01:12:25.210
are we that ye murmur against us?

01:12:26.170 --> 01:12:31.070
And Moses said, This shall be when the Lord shall give you in the evening flesh to eat,

01:12:31.210 --> 01:12:35.790
and in the morning bread to the full, for that the Lord heareth your murmurings which

01:12:35.790 --> 01:12:41.450
ye murmur against him, and what are we, your murmurings are not against us, but against

01:12:41.450 --> 01:12:41.970
the Lord.

01:12:42.870 --> 01:12:48.710
And Moses spake unto Aaron, Say unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, Come

01:12:48.710 --> 01:12:52.030
near before the Lord, for he hath heard your murmurings.

01:12:52.750 --> 01:12:57.630
And it came to pass, as Aaron spake unto the whole congregation of the children of Israel,

01:12:57.890 --> 01:13:02.390
that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory of the Lord appeared in

01:13:02.390 --> 01:13:02.990
the cloud.

01:13:04.170 --> 01:13:09.530
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel,

01:13:09.970 --> 01:13:14.970
speak unto them, saying, At even ye shall eat flesh, and in the morning ye shall be

01:13:14.970 --> 01:13:18.890
filled with bread, and ye shall know that I am the Lord your God.

01:13:19.790 --> 01:13:25.370
And it came to pass that at even the quails came up and covered the camp, and in the morning

01:13:25.370 --> 01:13:27.450
the dew lay round about the host.

01:13:28.270 --> 01:13:33.030
And when the dew that lay was gone up, behold, upon the face of the wilderness there lay

01:13:33.030 --> 01:13:37.110
a small round thing, as small as the whore-frost on the ground.

01:13:37.730 --> 01:13:43.490
And when the children of Israel saw it, they said one to another, It is manna, for they

01:13:43.490 --> 01:13:44.890
whisked not what it was.

01:13:45.410 --> 01:13:50.090
And Moses said unto them, This is the bread which the Lord hath given you to eat.

01:13:50.790 --> 01:13:53.410
This is the thing which the Lord hath commanded.

01:13:54.090 --> 01:13:59.570
Gather of it every man according to his eating, and omer for every man according to the number

01:13:59.570 --> 01:14:00.510
of your persons.

01:14:01.210 --> 01:14:03.970
Take ye every man for them which are in his tents.

01:14:04.550 --> 01:14:09.330
And the children of Israel did so, and gathered some more, some less.

01:14:10.150 --> 01:14:15.150
And when they did meet it with an omer, he that gathered much had nothing over, and he

01:14:15.150 --> 01:14:16.950
that gathered little had no lack.

01:14:17.410 --> 01:14:19.750
They gathered every man according to his eating.

01:14:20.690 --> 01:14:23.990
And Moses said, Let no man leave of it till the morning.

01:14:25.450 --> 01:14:30.250
Notwithstanding they hearkened not unto Moses, but some of them left of it until the morning,

01:14:30.250 --> 01:14:34.470
and it bred worms and stank, and Moses was wroth with them.

01:14:35.510 --> 01:14:39.850
And they gathered it every morning, every man according to his eating, and when the

01:14:39.850 --> 01:14:41.530
sun waxed hot it melted.

01:14:42.590 --> 01:14:47.630
And it came to pass that on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers

01:14:47.630 --> 01:14:52.130
for one man, and all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.

01:14:52.730 --> 01:14:57.710
And he said unto them, This is that which the Lord hath said, To-morrow is the rest

01:14:57.710 --> 01:14:59.730
of the holy Sabbath unto the Lord.

01:15:00.330 --> 01:15:05.690
Bake that which ye will bake to-day, and seed that which ye will seed, and that which remaineth

01:15:05.690 --> 01:15:08.630
over, lay up for you to be kept until the morning.

01:15:09.510 --> 01:15:14.870
And they laid it up till the morning, as Moses bad, and it did not stink, neither was there

01:15:14.870 --> 01:15:16.150
any worm therein.

01:15:17.350 --> 01:15:23.690
And Moses said, Eat that to-day, for to-day is a Sabbath unto the Lord, to-day ye shall

01:15:23.690 --> 01:15:25.110
not find it in the field.

01:15:25.670 --> 01:15:31.350
Six days shall ye gather it, but on the seventh day, which is the Sabbath, in it there shall

01:15:31.350 --> 01:15:31.970
be none.

01:15:33.010 --> 01:15:37.950
And it came to pass that there went out some of the people on the seventh day for to gather,

01:15:38.250 --> 01:15:39.570
and they found none.

01:15:40.570 --> 01:15:46.070
And the Lord said unto Moses, How long refuse ye to keep my commandments and my laws?

01:15:46.870 --> 01:15:51.930
See for that the Lord hath given you the Sabbath, therefore he giveth you on the sixth day

01:15:51.930 --> 01:15:58.250
the bread of two days, Abigee, every man in his place, let no man go out of his place

01:15:58.250 --> 01:15:59.470
on the seventh day.

01:16:00.310 --> 01:16:02.710
So the people rested on the seventh day.

01:16:03.790 --> 01:16:09.470
And the house of Israel called the name thereof Manna, and it was like coriander seed, white,

01:16:09.790 --> 01:16:12.590
and the taste of it was like wafers made with honey.

01:16:13.590 --> 01:16:18.930
And Moses said, This is the thing which the Lord commandeth, fill an omer of it to be

01:16:18.930 --> 01:16:23.530
kept for your generations, that they may seed the bread wherewith I have fed you in the

01:16:23.530 --> 01:16:26.930
wilderness when I brought you forth from the land of Egypt.

01:16:28.010 --> 01:16:33.390
And Moses said unto Aaron, Take a pot and put an omer full of Manna therein, and lay

01:16:33.390 --> 01:16:36.370
it up before the Lord to be kept for your generations.

01:16:37.490 --> 01:16:42.470
As the Lord commanded Moses, so Aaron laid it up before the testimony to be kept.

01:16:43.130 --> 01:16:48.650
And the children of Israel did eat Manna forty years until they came to a land inhabited.

01:16:49.290 --> 01:16:53.310
They did eat Manna until they came unto the borders of the land of Canaan.

01:16:53.310 --> 01:16:57.110
Now an omer is the tenth part of an ifah.

01:17:28.690 --> 01:17:33.390
And all the congregation of the children of Israel journeyed from the wilderness of Sin

01:17:33.390 --> 01:17:39.090
after their journeys according to the commandment of the LORD, and pitched in Rephidim, and

01:17:39.090 --> 01:17:44.330
there was no water for the people to drink. Wherefore the people did chide with Moses,

01:17:44.450 --> 01:17:50.250
and said, Give us water that we may drink. And Moses said unto them, Why chide ye with

01:17:50.250 --> 01:17:56.570
me? Wherefore do ye tempt the LORD? And the people thirsted there for water, and the people

01:17:56.570 --> 01:18:01.670
murmured against Moses, and said, Wherefore is this that thou hast brought us up out of

01:18:01.670 --> 01:18:07.350
Egypt to kill us and our children and our cattle with thirst? And Moses cried unto

01:18:07.350 --> 01:18:12.670
the LORD, saying, What shall I do unto this people? They be almost ready to stone me.

01:18:13.310 --> 01:18:18.510
And the LORD said unto Moses, Go on before the people, and take with thee of the elders

01:18:18.510 --> 01:18:25.770
of Israel, and thy rod wherewith thou smotest the river, take in thine hand, and go. Behold,

01:18:25.770 --> 01:18:30.870
I will stand before thee there upon the rock in Horeb, and thou shalt smite the rock, and

01:18:30.870 --> 01:18:35.990
there shall come water out of it that the people may drink. And Moses did so in the

01:18:35.990 --> 01:18:42.110
sight of the elders of Israel. And he called the name of the place Massah and Meribah because

01:18:42.110 --> 01:18:46.790
of the chiding of the children of Israel, and because they tempted the LORD, saying,

01:18:47.070 --> 01:18:55.750
Is the LORD among us or not? Then came Amalek, and fought with Israel in Rephidim. And Moses

01:18:55.750 --> 01:19:01.730
said unto Joshua, Choose us out men, and go out, fight with Amalek. To-morrow I will

01:19:01.730 --> 01:19:07.790
stand on the top of the hill with the rod of God in mine hand. So Joshua did as Moses

01:19:07.790 --> 01:19:13.590
had said to him and fought with Amalek, and Moses, Aaron, and Hur went up to the top of

01:19:13.590 --> 01:19:20.330
the hill. And it came to pass when Moses held up his hand that Israel prevailed, and when

01:19:20.330 --> 01:19:26.990
he let down his hand Amalek prevailed. But Moses' hands were heavy, and they took a stone

01:19:26.990 --> 01:19:32.850
and put it under him, and he sat thereon, and Aaron and Hur stayed up his hands, the

01:19:32.850 --> 01:19:37.970
one on the one side and the other on the other side, and his hands were steady until the

01:19:37.970 --> 01:19:43.990
going down of the sun. And Joshua discomfited Amalek and his people with the edge of the

01:19:43.990 --> 01:19:50.310
sword. And the LORD said unto Moses, Write this for a memorial and a book, and rehearse

01:19:50.310 --> 01:19:55.650
it in the years of Joshua, for I will utterly put out the remembrance of Amalek from under

01:19:55.650 --> 01:20:02.330
heaven. And Moses built an altar, and called the name of it Jehovah-Nissai, for he said,

01:20:02.550 --> 01:20:07.550
Because the LORD hath sworn that the LORD will have war with Amalek from generation

01:20:07.550 --> 01:20:08.610
to generation.

01:20:11.910 --> 01:20:17.210
When Jethro, the priest of Midian, Moses' father-in-law, heard of all that God had done

01:20:17.210 --> 01:20:22.650
for Moses and for Israel his people, and that the LORD had brought Israel out of Egypt,

01:20:23.130 --> 01:20:29.530
then Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, took Zipporah, Moses' wife, after he had sent her back, and

01:20:29.530 --> 01:20:35.090
her two sons, of which the name of the one was Gershom, for he said, I have been an alien

01:20:35.090 --> 01:20:41.010
in a strange land. And the name of the other was Eleazar, for the God of my father, said

01:20:41.010 --> 01:20:44.430
he, was mine help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh.

01:20:45.410 --> 01:20:50.790
And Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, came with his sons and his wife unto Moses into the

01:20:50.790 --> 01:20:56.810
wilderness where he encamped to the mount of God. And he said unto Moses, I, thy father-in-law

01:20:56.810 --> 01:21:03.210
Jethro, am come unto thee and thy wife and her two sons with her. And Moses went out

01:21:03.210 --> 01:21:08.030
to meet his father-in-law, and did obeisance, and kissed him, and they asked each other

01:21:08.030 --> 01:21:14.350
of their welfare, and they came into the tent. And Moses told his father-in-law all that

01:21:14.350 --> 01:21:19.190
the Lord had done unto Pharaoh, and to the Egyptians, for Israel's sake, and all the

01:21:19.190 --> 01:21:25.090
travails that had come upon them by the way, and how the Lord delivered them. And Jethro

01:21:25.090 --> 01:21:29.690
rejoiced for all the goodness which the Lord had done to Israel, whom he had delivered

01:21:29.690 --> 01:21:35.550
out of the hand of the Egyptians. And Jethro said, Blessed be the Lord who hath delivered

01:21:35.550 --> 01:21:40.370
you out of the hand of the Egyptians, and out of the hand of Pharaoh, who hath delivered

01:21:40.370 --> 01:21:46.170
the people from under the hand of the Egyptians. Now I know that the Lord is greater than

01:21:46.170 --> 01:21:52.950
all gods, for in the thing wherein they dealt proudly he was above them. And Jethro, Moses's

01:21:52.950 --> 01:21:58.890
father-in-law, took a burnt offering and sacrifices for God, and Aaron came and all the elders

01:21:58.890 --> 01:22:05.930
of Israel to eat bread with Moses's father-in-law before God. And it came to pass on the morrow

01:22:06.370 --> 01:22:11.830
sat to judge the people, and the people stood by Moses from the morning unto the evening.

01:22:12.690 --> 01:22:18.150
And when Moses's father-in-law saw all that he did to the people, he said, What is this

01:22:18.150 --> 01:22:23.490
thing that thou doest to the people? Why sittest thou thyself alone, and all the people stand

01:22:23.490 --> 01:22:29.870
by thee from morning unto even? And Moses said unto his father-in-law, Because the people

01:22:29.870 --> 01:22:35.250
come unto me to inquire of God. When they have a matter, they come unto me, and I judge

01:22:35.250 --> 01:22:41.350
between one and another, and I do make them know the statutes of God and his laws. And

01:22:41.350 --> 01:22:47.010
Moses's father-in-law said unto him, The thing that thou doest is not good. Thou wilt surely

01:22:47.010 --> 01:22:52.070
wear away both thou and this people that is with thee, for this thing is too heavy for

01:22:52.070 --> 01:22:58.770
thee. Thou art not able to perform it thyself alone. Harken thou unto my voice, I will

01:22:58.770 --> 01:23:04.630
give thee counsel, and God shall be with thee. Be thou for the people to Godward, that thou

01:23:04.630 --> 01:23:10.170
mayest bring the causes unto God, and thou shalt teach them ordinances and laws, and

01:23:10.170 --> 01:23:15.750
shalt show them the way wherein they must walk, and the work that they must do. Moreover

01:23:15.750 --> 01:23:21.390
thou shalt provide out of all the people able men, such as fear God, men of truth,

01:23:21.730 --> 01:23:27.790
hating covetousness, and place such over them to be rulers of thousands, and rulers of hundreds,

01:23:28.130 --> 01:23:33.610
rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens, and let them judge the people at all seasons,

01:23:33.950 --> 01:23:38.990
and it shall be that every great matter they shall bring unto thee, but every small matter

01:23:38.990 --> 01:23:44.370
they shall judge, so shall it be easier for thyself, and they shall bear the burden with

01:23:44.370 --> 01:23:50.070
thee. If thou shalt do this thing, and God command thee so, then thou shalt be able

01:23:50.070 --> 01:23:54.690
to endure, and all this people shall also go to their place in peace.

01:23:55.590 --> 01:24:02.390
So Moses harken to the voice of his father-in-law, and did all that he had said. And Moses chose

01:24:02.390 --> 01:24:07.510
the able men out of all Israel, and made them heads over the people, rulers of thousands,

01:24:07.850 --> 01:24:13.490
rulers of hundreds, rulers of fifties, and rulers of tens, and they judged the people

01:24:13.490 --> 01:24:19.390
at all seasons, the hard causes they brought unto Moses, but every small matter they judged

01:24:19.390 --> 01:24:25.950
themselves. Then Moses let his father-in-law depart, and he went his way into his own land.

01:24:28.370 --> 01:24:32.270
In the third month, when the children of Israel

01:24:32.270 --> 01:24:37.130
were gone forth out of the land of Egypt, the same day came they into the wilderness

01:24:37.130 --> 01:24:43.330
of Sinai. For they were departed from Rephidim, and were come to the desert of Sinai, and

01:24:43.330 --> 01:24:49.630
had pitched in the wilderness, and there Israel camped before the mount. And Moses went up

01:24:49.630 --> 01:24:55.130
unto God, and the Lord called unto him out of the mountain, saying, Thus shalt thou say

01:24:55.130 --> 01:25:00.930
unto the house of Jacob, and tell the children of Israel. Ye have seen what I did unto the

01:25:00.930 --> 01:25:07.610
Egyptians, and how I bear you on eagle's wings, and brought you unto myself. Now therefore,

01:25:07.850 --> 01:25:13.770
if ye will obey my voice and deed, and keep my covenant, then ye shall be a peculiar treasure

01:25:13.770 --> 01:25:19.890
unto me above all people, for all the earth is mine. And ye shall be unto me a kingdom

01:25:19.890 --> 01:25:25.250
of priests, and an holy nation. These are the words which thou shalt speak unto the

01:25:25.250 --> 01:25:31.810
children of Israel. And Moses came and called for the elders of the people, and laid before

01:25:31.810 --> 01:25:37.370
their faces all these words which the Lord commanded him. And all the people answered

01:25:37.370 --> 01:25:43.250
together and said, All that the Lord hath spoken we will do. And Moses returned the

01:25:43.250 --> 01:25:49.710
words of the people unto the Lord. And the Lord said unto Moses, Lo, I come unto thee

01:25:49.710 --> 01:25:54.690
in a thick cloud, that the people may hear when I speak with thee, and believe thee forever.

01:25:55.550 --> 01:26:01.870
And Moses told the words of the people unto the Lord. And the Lord said unto Moses, Go

01:26:01.870 --> 01:26:06.870
unto the people, and sanctify them to-day and to-morrow, and let them wash their clothes,

01:26:07.370 --> 01:26:12.610
and be ready against the third day, for the third day the Lord will come down in the sight

01:26:12.610 --> 01:26:19.270
of all the people upon Mount Sinai. And thou shalt set bounds unto the people round about,

01:26:19.270 --> 01:26:24.550
saying, Take heed to yourselves that ye go not up into the mount, or touch the border

01:26:24.550 --> 01:26:30.210
of it. Whosoever toucheth the mount shall be surely put to death. There shall not in

01:26:30.210 --> 01:26:36.070
hand touch it, but he shall surely be stoned or shot through. Whether it be beast or man,

01:26:36.190 --> 01:26:40.990
it shall not live. When the trumpet soundeth long, they shall come up to the mount.

01:26:42.330 --> 01:26:47.230
And Moses went down from the mount unto the people, and sanctified the people, and they

01:26:47.230 --> 01:26:52.990
washed their clothes. And he said unto the people, Be ready against the third day, come

01:26:52.990 --> 01:26:58.630
not at your wives. And it came to pass on the third day and the morning that there were

01:26:58.630 --> 01:27:03.550
thunders and lightnings, and a thick cloud upon the mount, and the voice of the trumpet

01:27:03.550 --> 01:27:10.070
exceeding loud, so that all the people that was in the camp trembled. And Moses brought

01:27:10.070 --> 01:27:14.770
forth the people out of the camp to meet with God, and they stood at the nether part of

01:27:14.770 --> 01:27:20.610
the mount. And Mount Sinai was altogether on a smoke, because the Lord descended upon

01:27:20.610 --> 01:27:26.450
it in fire, and the smoke thereof ascended as the smoke of a furnace, and the whole mount

01:27:26.450 --> 01:27:32.490
quaked greatly. And when the voice of the trumpet sounded long and waxed louder and

01:27:32.490 --> 01:27:39.110
louder, Moses spake, and God answered him by a voice. And the Lord came down upon Mount

01:27:39.110 --> 01:27:44.670
Sinai on the top of the mount, and the Lord called Moses up to the top of the mount, and

01:27:44.670 --> 01:27:51.690
Moses went up. And the Lord said unto Moses, Go down, charge the people, lest they break

01:27:51.690 --> 01:27:57.950
through unto the Lord to gaze, and many of them perish. And let the priests also, which

01:27:57.950 --> 01:28:04.530
come near to the Lord, sanctify themselves, lest the Lord break forth upon them. And Moses

01:28:04.530 --> 01:28:09.750
said unto the Lord, The people cannot come up to Mount Sinai, for thou chargeth thus,

01:28:09.750 --> 01:28:16.870
set bounds about the mount, and sanctify it. And the Lord said unto him, Away, get thee

01:28:16.870 --> 01:28:22.170
down, and thou shalt come up, thou and Aaron with thee, but let not the priests and the

01:28:22.170 --> 01:28:28.090
people break through to come up unto the Lord, lest he break forth upon them. So Moses went

01:28:28.090 --> 01:28:30.890
down unto the people, and spake unto them.

01:28:34.250 --> 01:28:40.230
And God spake all these words, saying, I am the Lord thy God, which have brought thee

01:28:40.230 --> 01:28:45.650
out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage. Thou shalt have no other gods

01:28:45.650 --> 01:28:51.850
before me. Thou shalt not make unto thee any graven image, or any likeness of anything

01:28:51.850 --> 01:28:57.150
that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under

01:28:57.150 --> 01:29:03.330
the earth. Thou shalt not bow down thyself to them, nor serve them. For I, the Lord thy

01:29:03.330 --> 01:29:08.830
God, am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children unto the

01:29:08.830 --> 01:29:14.830
third and fourth generation of them that hate me, and showing mercy unto thousands of them

01:29:14.830 --> 01:29:21.230
that love me, and keep my commandments. Thou shalt not take the name of the Lord thy God

01:29:21.230 --> 01:29:25.910
in vain, for the Lord will not hold him guiltless that taketh his name in vain.

01:29:27.450 --> 01:29:33.390
Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy. Six days shalt thou labor, and do all thy

01:29:33.390 --> 01:29:39.130
work, but the seventh day is the Sabbath of the Lord thy God. In it thou shalt not do

01:29:39.130 --> 01:29:46.130
any work, thou, nor thy son, nor thy daughter, thy manservant, nor thy maidservant, nor thy

01:29:46.950 --> 01:29:53.010
stranger that is within thy gates. For in six days the Lord made heaven and earth, the

01:29:53.010 --> 01:29:58.890
sea, and all that in them is, and rested the seventh day. Wherefore the Lord blessed the

01:29:58.890 --> 01:30:01.070
Sabbath day, and hallowed it.

01:30:02.470 --> 01:30:07.330
Honor thy father and thy mother, that thy days may be long upon the land which the Lord

01:30:07.330 --> 01:30:15.150
thy God giveth thee. Thou shalt not kill, thou shalt not commit adultery, thou shalt

01:30:15.150 --> 01:30:21.490
not steal, thou shalt not bear false witness against thy neighbor, thou shalt not covet

01:30:21.490 --> 01:30:26.690
thy neighbor's house, thou shalt not covet thy neighbor's wife, nor his manservant, nor

01:30:26.690 --> 01:30:32.030
his maidservant, nor his ox, nor his ass, nor anything that is thy neighbor's.

01:30:33.730 --> 01:30:38.510
And all the people saw the thunderings and the lightnings, and the noise of the trumpet

01:30:38.510 --> 01:30:45.570
and the mountains spoking, and when the people saw it they removed and stood afar off. And

01:30:45.570 --> 01:30:50.890
they said unto Moses, Speak thou with us, and we will hear, but let not God speak with

01:30:50.890 --> 01:30:58.090
us lest we die. And Moses said unto the people, Fear not, for God has come to prove you, and

01:30:58.090 --> 01:31:04.330
that his fear may be before your faces, that ye sin not. And the people stood afar off,

01:31:04.330 --> 01:31:07.970
and Moses drew near unto the thick darkness where God was.

01:31:09.510 --> 01:31:14.750
And the Lord said unto Moses, Thus thou shalt say unto the children of Israel, Ye have

01:31:14.750 --> 01:31:20.030
seen that I have talked with you from heaven. Ye shall not make with me gods of silver,

01:31:20.310 --> 01:31:26.410
neither shall ye make unto you gods of gold. An altar of earth thou shalt make unto me,

01:31:26.550 --> 01:31:31.990
and shalt sacrifice thereon thy burnt offerings, and thy peace offerings, thy sheep, and thine

01:31:31.990 --> 01:31:37.830
oxen. In all places where I record my name, I will come unto thee, and I will bless thee.

01:31:38.750 --> 01:31:43.910
And if thou wilt make me an altar of stone, thou shalt not build it of hewn stone, for

01:31:43.910 --> 01:31:49.770
if thou lift up thy tool upon it, thou hast polluted it. Neither shalt thou go up by steps

01:31:49.770 --> 01:31:53.930
unto mine altar, that thy nakedness be not discovered thereon.

01:31:55.910 --> 01:31:59.370
Now these are the judgments which thou shalt

01:31:59.370 --> 01:32:05.930
set before them. If thou buy in Hebrew servant six years he shall serve, and in the seventh

01:32:05.930 --> 01:32:11.750
he shall go out free for nothing. If he came in by himself, he shall go out by himself.

01:32:12.070 --> 01:32:17.150
If he were married, then his wife shall go out with him. If his master have given him

01:32:17.150 --> 01:32:22.570
a wife, and she have borne him sons or daughters, the wife and her children shall be her masters,

01:32:22.930 --> 01:32:28.810
and he shall go out by himself. And if the servant shall plainly say, I love my master,

01:32:28.810 --> 01:32:34.530
my wife, and my children, I will not go out free, then his master shall bring him unto

01:32:34.530 --> 01:32:39.870
the judges, he shall also bring him to the door or unto the door-post, and his master

01:32:39.870 --> 01:32:43.910
shall bore his ear through with an awl, and he shall serve him for ever.

01:32:45.270 --> 01:32:50.690
And if a man sell his daughter to be a maid-servant, she shall not go out as the men-servants do.

01:32:51.330 --> 01:32:57.130
If she please not her master, who hath betrothed her to himself, then shall he let her be redeemed,

01:32:57.130 --> 01:33:02.690
to sell her unto a strange nation, he shall have no power, seeing he hath dealt deceitfully

01:33:02.690 --> 01:33:08.270
with her. And if he hath betrothed her unto his son, he shall deal with her after the

01:33:08.270 --> 01:33:13.830
manner of daughters. If he take him another wife, her food, her raiment, and her duty

01:33:13.830 --> 01:33:19.410
of marriage, shall he not diminish. And if he do not these three unto her, then shall

01:33:19.410 --> 01:33:21.330
she go out free without money.

01:33:22.530 --> 01:33:29.050
He that smiteth a man so that he die shall be surely put to death. And if a man lie not

01:33:29.050 --> 01:33:34.210
in wait, but God deliver him into his hand, then I will appoint thee a place whither he

01:33:34.210 --> 01:33:39.850
shall flee. But if a man come presumptuously upon his neighbor to slay him with guile,

01:33:40.250 --> 01:33:45.910
thou shalt take him from mine altar that he may die. And he that smiteth his father or

01:33:45.910 --> 01:33:51.710
his mother shall be surely put to death. And he that stealeth a man and selleth him,

01:33:52.010 --> 01:33:58.330
or if he be found in his hand, he shall surely be put to death. And he that curseth his father

01:33:58.330 --> 01:34:05.010
or his mother shall surely be put to death. And if men strive together and one smite another

01:34:05.010 --> 01:34:10.990
with a stone or with his fist, and he die not but keepeth his bed, if he rise again

01:34:10.990 --> 01:34:16.630
and walk abroad upon his staff, then shall he that smote him be quit, only he shall pay

01:34:16.630 --> 01:34:22.550
for the loss of his time and shall cause him to be thoroughly healed. And if a man smite

01:34:22.550 --> 01:34:27.950
his servant or his maid with a rod, and he die under his hand, he shall be surely punished.

01:34:29.550 --> 01:34:34.390
Notwithstanding, if he continue a day or two, he shall not be punished, for he is his money.

01:34:35.630 --> 01:34:41.090
If men strive and hurt a woman with child, so that her fruit depart from her, and yet

01:34:41.090 --> 01:34:45.790
no mischief follow, he shall be surely punished according as the woman's husband will lay

01:34:45.790 --> 01:34:52.770
upon him, and he shall pay as the judges determine. And if any mischief follow, then thou shalt

01:34:52.770 --> 01:34:59.410
give life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot, burning

01:34:59.410 --> 01:35:06.950
wound for wound, stripe for stripe. And if a man smite the eye of his servant or the

01:35:06.950 --> 01:35:12.930
eye of his maid that it perish, he shall let him go free for his eyes' sake. And if he

01:35:12.930 --> 01:35:17.730
smite out his manservant's tooth or his maid's servant's tooth, he shall let him go free

01:35:17.730 --> 01:35:25.010
for his tooth's sake. If an ox gore a man or a woman that they die, then the ox shall

01:35:25.010 --> 01:35:30.310
be surely stoned, and his flesh shall not be eaten, but the owner of the ox shall be

01:35:30.310 --> 01:35:36.770
quit. But if the ox were wont to push with his horn in time past, and it hath been testified

01:35:36.770 --> 01:35:41.730
to his owner, and he hath not kept him in, but that he hath killed a man or a woman,

01:35:42.010 --> 01:35:48.050
the ox shall be stoned, and his owner also shall be put to death. If there be laid on

01:35:48.050 --> 01:35:52.830
him a sum of money, then he shall give for the ransom of his life whatsoever as laid

01:35:52.830 --> 01:35:58.830
upon him. Whether he have gored a son or have gored a daughter, according to this judgment

01:35:58.830 --> 01:36:05.010
shall it be done unto him. If the ox shall push a manservant or a maidservant, he shall

01:36:05.010 --> 01:36:11.390
give unto their master thirty shekels of silver, and the ox shall be stoned. And if

01:36:11.390 --> 01:36:16.730
a man shall open a pit, or if a man shall dig a pit and not cover it, and an ox or an

01:36:16.730 --> 01:36:21.830
ass fall therein, the owner of the pit shall make it good and give money unto the owner

01:36:21.830 --> 01:36:27.890
of them, and the dead beast shall be his. And if one man's ox hurt another's that he

01:36:27.890 --> 01:36:33.310
die, then they shall sell the live ox and divide the money of it, and the dead ox also

01:36:33.310 --> 01:36:39.390
they shall divide. Or if it be known that the ox hath used to push in time past, and

01:36:39.390 --> 01:36:44.950
his owner hath not kept him in, he shall surely pay ox for ox, and the dead shall be his

01:36:44.950 --> 01:36:45.270
own.

01:36:49.550 --> 01:36:54.530
If a man shall steal an ox or a sheep, and kill it or sell it, he shall restore five

01:36:54.530 --> 01:37:02.030
oxen for an ox, and four sheep for a sheep. If a thief be found breaking up, and be smitten

01:37:02.030 --> 01:37:07.750
that he die, there shall no blood be shed for him. If the sun be risen upon him, there

01:37:07.750 --> 01:37:12.810
shall be blood shed for him, for he should make full restitution. If he have nothing,

01:37:12.810 --> 01:37:19.590
then he shall be sold for his theft. If the theft be certainly found in his hand alive,

01:37:19.650 --> 01:37:26.650
whether it be ox or ass or sheep, he shall restore double. If a man shall cause a field

01:37:26.650 --> 01:37:31.170
or vineyard to be eaten, and shall put in his beast, and shall feed in another man's

01:37:31.170 --> 01:37:36.210
field, of the best of his own field, and of the best of his own vineyard, shall he make

01:37:36.210 --> 01:37:37.010
restitution.

01:37:38.050 --> 01:37:43.970
If fire break out and catch in thorns, so that the stacks of corn or the standing corn

01:37:43.970 --> 01:37:49.970
or the field be consumed therewith, he that kindled the fire shall surely make restitution.

01:37:51.330 --> 01:37:56.130
If a man shall deliver unto his neighbour money or stuff to keep, and it be stolen out

01:37:56.130 --> 01:38:02.190
of the man's house, if the thief be found let him pay double. If the thief be not found,

01:38:02.310 --> 01:38:06.710
then the master of the house shall be brought unto the judges, to see whether he have put

01:38:06.710 --> 01:38:11.990
his hand unto his neighbour's goods. For all manner of trespass, whether it be for

01:38:11.990 --> 01:38:18.170
ox, for ass, for sheep, for raiment, or for any manner of lost thing, which another challenges

01:38:18.170 --> 01:38:23.910
to be his, the cause of both parties shall come before the judges, and whom the judges

01:38:23.910 --> 01:38:29.770
shall condemn, he shall pay double unto his neighbour. If a man deliver unto his neighbour

01:38:29.770 --> 01:38:36.290
an ass or an ox or a sheep or any beast to keep, and it die or be hurt or driven away,

01:38:36.290 --> 01:38:42.050
no man seeing it, then shall an oath of the Lord be between them both, that he hath not

01:38:42.050 --> 01:38:47.050
put his hand unto his neighbour's goods, and the owner of it shall accept thereof, and

01:38:47.050 --> 01:38:52.570
he shall not make it good. And if it be stolen from him, he shall make restitution unto the

01:38:52.570 --> 01:38:58.370
owner thereof. If it be torn in pieces, then let him bring it for witness, and he shall

01:38:58.370 --> 01:39:04.670
not make good that which was torn. And if a man borrow ought of his neighbour, and it

01:39:04.670 --> 01:39:10.710
be hurt or die, the owner thereof, being not with it, he shall surely make it good. But

01:39:10.710 --> 01:39:15.310
if the owner thereof be with it, he shall not make it good. If it be an hired thing,

01:39:15.650 --> 01:39:21.450
it came for his hire. And if a man entice a maid that is not betrothed, and lie with

01:39:21.450 --> 01:39:27.650
her, he shall surely endow her to be his wife. If her father utterly refused to give her

01:39:27.650 --> 01:39:31.370
unto him, he shall pay money according to the dowry of virgins.

01:39:32.570 --> 01:39:39.770
Thou shalt not suffer a witch to live. Whosoever lieth with a beast shall surely be put to

01:39:39.770 --> 01:39:47.770
death. He that sacrificeth unto any god save unto the Lord only, he shall be utterly destroyed.

01:39:49.590 --> 01:39:54.550
Thou shalt neither vex a stranger nor oppress him, for ye were strangers in the land of

01:39:54.550 --> 01:40:02.250
Egypt. He shall not afflict any widow or fatherless child. If thou afflict them in any wise, and

01:40:02.250 --> 01:40:08.310
they cry at all unto me, I will surely hear their cry, and my wrath shall wax hot, and

01:40:08.310 --> 01:40:13.930
I will kill you with the sword, and your wives shall be widows and your children fatherless.

01:40:15.090 --> 01:40:20.210
If thou lend money to any of my people that is poor by thee, thou shalt not be to him

01:40:20.210 --> 01:40:27.230
as an usurer, neither shalt thou lay upon him usury. If thou at all take thy neighbor's

01:40:27.230 --> 01:40:32.750
raiment to pledge, thou shalt deliver it unto him by that the sun goeth down, for that is

01:40:32.750 --> 01:40:38.350
his covering only, it is his raiment for his skin, wherein shall he sleep, and it shall

01:40:38.350 --> 01:40:42.730
come to pass when he crieth unto me that I will hear, for I am gracious.

01:40:44.130 --> 01:40:50.710
Thou shalt not revile the gods, nor curse the ruler of thy people. Thou shalt not delay

01:40:50.710 --> 01:40:55.910
to offer the first of thy ripe fruits and of thy liquors, the first born of thy sons

01:40:55.910 --> 01:41:02.330
shalt thou give unto me. Likewise shalt thou do with thine oxen and with thy sheep, seven

01:41:02.330 --> 01:41:07.910
days it shall be with his dam, on the eighth day thou shalt give it me. And ye shall be

01:41:07.910 --> 01:41:12.910
holy men unto me, neither shall ye eat any flesh that is torn of beasts in the field,

01:41:13.330 --> 01:41:15.270
ye shall cast it to the dogs.

01:41:47.670 --> 01:41:53.630
Thou shalt not raise a false report, put not thine hand with a wicked to be an unrighteous

01:41:53.630 --> 01:41:54.170
witness.

01:41:55.350 --> 01:42:00.890
Thou shalt not follow a multitude to do evil, neither shalt thou speak in a cause to decline

01:42:00.890 --> 01:42:06.930
after many to rest judgment, neither shalt thou countenance a poor man in his cause.

01:42:08.130 --> 01:42:13.370
If thou meet thine enemy's ox or his ass going astray, thou shalt surely bring it back

01:42:13.370 --> 01:42:14.270
to him again.

01:42:14.870 --> 01:42:20.330
If thou see the ass of him that hateth thee lying under his burden, and wouldest forbear

01:42:20.330 --> 01:42:23.350
to help him, thou shalt surely help with him.

01:42:24.030 --> 01:42:27.410
Thou shalt not rest the judgment of thy poor in his cause.

01:42:28.590 --> 01:42:33.970
Keep thee far from a false matter, and the innocent and righteous slay thou not, for

01:42:33.970 --> 01:42:35.870
I will not justify the wicked.

01:42:36.850 --> 01:42:42.310
And thou shalt take no gift, for the gift blindeth the wise and perverteth the words

01:42:42.310 --> 01:42:43.170
of the righteous.

01:42:44.350 --> 01:42:50.310
Also thou shalt not oppress a stranger, for ye know the heart of a stranger seeing ye

01:42:50.310 --> 01:42:52.370
were strangers in the land of Egypt.

01:42:53.410 --> 01:42:59.090
In six years thou shalt sow thy land and shalt gather in the fruits thereof, but the seventh

01:42:59.090 --> 01:43:05.110
year thou shalt let it rest and lie still, that the poor of thy people may eat, and what

01:43:05.110 --> 01:43:07.510
they leave the beasts of the field shall eat.

01:43:08.090 --> 01:43:12.490
In like manner thou shalt deal with thy vineyard and with thy olive-yard.

01:43:13.870 --> 01:43:19.430
Six days thou shalt do thy work, and on the seventh day thou shalt rest, that thine ox

01:43:19.430 --> 01:43:25.010
and thine ass may rest, and the son of thy handmaid and the stranger may be refreshed.

01:43:25.810 --> 01:43:30.950
And in all things that I have said unto you, be circumspect, and make no mention of the

01:43:30.950 --> 01:43:34.910
name of other gods, neither let it be heard out of thy mouth.

01:43:36.470 --> 01:43:40.110
Three times thou shalt keep a feast unto me in the year.

01:43:40.850 --> 01:43:45.910
Thou shalt keep the feast of unleavened bread, thou shalt eat unleavened bread seven days

01:43:45.910 --> 01:43:51.970
as I commanded thee in the time appointed of the month Abib, for in it thou camest out

01:43:51.970 --> 01:43:55.270
from Egypt, and none shall appear before me empty.

01:43:56.090 --> 01:44:04.310
And the feast of harvest, the first fruits of thy labors, which thou hast sown in the

01:44:04.310 --> 01:44:10.210
year, when thou hast gathered in thy labors out of the field, three times in the year

01:44:10.210 --> 01:44:13.550
all thy males shall appear before the Lord God.

01:44:14.990 --> 01:44:20.290
Thou shalt not offer the blood of my sacrifice with leavened bread, neither shall the fat

01:44:20.290 --> 01:44:22.930
of my sacrifice remain until the morning.

01:44:23.950 --> 01:44:28.350
The first of the first fruits of thy land thou shalt bring into the house of the Lord

01:44:28.350 --> 01:44:29.050
thy God.

01:44:29.790 --> 01:44:32.750
Thou shalt not see the kid in his mother's milk.

01:44:34.610 --> 01:44:39.890
Behold, I send an angel before thee to keep thee in the way, and to bring thee into the

01:44:39.890 --> 01:44:41.390
place which I have prepared.

01:44:42.230 --> 01:44:48.510
Beware of him, and obey his voice, provoke him not, for he will not pardon your transgressions,

01:44:48.910 --> 01:44:50.470
for my name is in him.

01:44:51.150 --> 01:44:57.350
But if thou shalt indeed obey his voice, and do all that I speak, then I will be an enemy

01:44:57.350 --> 01:45:01.430
unto thine enemies, and an adversary unto thine adversaries.

01:45:02.370 --> 01:45:07.530
For mine angel shall go before thee, and bring thee in unto the Amorites, and the Hittites,

01:45:07.550 --> 01:45:12.790
and the Perizzites, and the Canaanites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, and I will

01:45:12.790 --> 01:45:13.750
cut them off.

01:45:14.630 --> 01:45:20.950
Thou shalt not bow down to their gods, nor serve them, nor do after their works, but

01:45:20.950 --> 01:45:25.010
thou shalt utterly overthrow them, and quite break down their images.

01:45:25.570 --> 01:45:31.390
And ye shall serve the Lord your God, and he shall bless thy bread and thy water, and

01:45:31.390 --> 01:45:34.230
I will take sickness away from the midst of thee.

01:45:35.570 --> 01:45:41.230
There shall nothing cast their young nor be barren in thy land the number of thy days

01:45:41.230 --> 01:45:42.350
I will fulfill.

01:45:43.350 --> 01:45:48.330
I will send my fear before thee, and will destroy all the people to whom thou shalt

01:45:48.330 --> 01:45:52.550
come, and I will make all thine enemies turn their backs unto thee.

01:45:53.230 --> 01:45:58.450
And I will send hornets before thee, which shall drive out the Hivite, the Canaanite,

01:45:58.450 --> 01:46:00.510
and the Hittite from before thee.

01:46:01.270 --> 01:46:06.270
I will not drive them out from before thee in one year, lest the land become desolate,

01:46:06.590 --> 01:46:09.390
and the beasts of the field multiply against thee.

01:46:10.170 --> 01:46:15.410
By little and little I will drive them out from before thee, until thou be increased

01:46:15.410 --> 01:46:17.010
and inherit the land.

01:46:17.550 --> 01:46:23.130
And I will set thy bounds from the Red Sea, even unto the Sea of the Philistines, and

01:46:23.130 --> 01:46:25.050
from the desert unto the river.

01:46:25.450 --> 01:46:30.190
For I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and thou shalt drive

01:46:30.190 --> 01:46:31.610
them out before thee.

01:46:32.590 --> 01:46:36.330
Thou shalt make no covenant with them, nor with their gods.

01:46:37.270 --> 01:46:42.510
They shall not dwell in thy land, lest they make thee sin against me, for if thou serve

01:46:42.510 --> 01:46:46.070
their gods, it will surely be a snare unto thee.

01:46:47.330 --> 01:46:52.350
And he said unto Moses, Come up unto the

01:46:52.350 --> 01:46:58.870
Lord, thou and Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and Seventy, of the elders of Israel, and worship

01:46:58.870 --> 01:47:00.010
ye far off.

01:47:00.810 --> 01:47:05.950
And Moses alone shall come near the Lord, but they shall not come nigh, neither shall

01:47:05.950 --> 01:47:07.570
the people go up with him.

01:47:08.930 --> 01:47:14.390
And Moses came and told the people all the words of the Lord, and all the judgments,

01:47:14.690 --> 01:47:20.130
and all the people answered with one voice, and said, All the words which the Lord hath

01:47:20.130 --> 01:47:21.690
said, will we do.

01:47:22.790 --> 01:47:28.190
And Moses wrote all the words of the Lord, and rose up early in the morning, and build

01:47:28.190 --> 01:47:33.790
it an altar under the hill, and twelve pillars according to the twelve tribes of Israel.

01:47:34.670 --> 01:47:40.410
And he sent young men of the children of Israel, which offered burnt offerings, and sacrificed

01:47:40.410 --> 01:47:43.310
peace offerings of oxen unto the Lord.

01:47:44.930 --> 01:47:50.170
And Moses took half of the blood, and put it in basins, and half of the blood he sprinkled

01:47:50.170 --> 01:47:50.950
on the altar.

01:47:51.850 --> 01:47:56.590
And he took the book of the covenant, and read in the audience of the people, and they

01:47:56.590 --> 01:48:01.050
said, All that the Lord hath said, will we do, and be obedient.

01:48:02.190 --> 01:48:07.730
And Moses took the blood, and sprinkled it on the people, and said, Behold the blood

01:48:07.730 --> 01:48:12.190
of the covenant, which the Lord hath made with you concerning all these words.

01:48:13.570 --> 01:48:20.070
Then went up Moses and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel, and they

01:48:20.070 --> 01:48:25.650
saw the God of Israel, and there was under his feet, as it were, a paved work of a sapphire

01:48:25.650 --> 01:48:29.530
stone, and as it were, the body of heaven in his clearness.

01:48:30.770 --> 01:48:37.070
And upon the nobles of the children of Israel he laid not his hand, also they saw God, and

01:48:37.070 --> 01:48:38.490
did eat and drink.

01:48:39.790 --> 01:48:45.710
And the Lord said unto Moses, Come up to me into the mount, and be there, and I will

01:48:45.710 --> 01:48:51.650
give thee tables of stone, and a law and commandments which I have written, that thou mayest teach

01:48:51.650 --> 01:48:52.070
them.

01:48:52.770 --> 01:48:58.870
And Moses rose up, and his minister Joshua, and Moses went up into the mount of God.

01:48:59.630 --> 01:49:05.410
And he said unto the elders, Terry ye here for us, until we come again unto you, and

01:49:05.410 --> 01:49:11.450
behold Aaron and her are with you, if any man have any matters to do, let him come unto

01:49:11.450 --> 01:49:11.910
them.

01:49:13.110 --> 01:49:16.990
And Moses went up into the mount, and a cloud covered the mount.

01:49:17.670 --> 01:49:23.530
And the glory of the Lord abode upon Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it six days,

01:49:23.810 --> 01:49:27.810
and the seventh day he called unto Moses out of the midst of the cloud.

01:49:29.030 --> 01:49:33.850
And the sight of the glory of the Lord was like devouring fire on the top of the mount

01:49:33.850 --> 01:49:36.310
in the eyes of the children of Israel.

01:49:37.350 --> 01:49:42.950
And Moses went into the midst of the cloud, and got him up into the mount, and Moses was

01:49:42.950 --> 01:49:45.870
in the mount forty days and forty nights.

01:49:48.190 --> 01:49:53.650
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Speak

01:49:53.650 --> 01:49:58.590
unto the children of Israel that they bring me an offering, of every man that giveth it

01:49:58.590 --> 01:50:01.270
willingly with his heart he shall take my offering.

01:50:02.030 --> 01:50:08.110
And this is the offering which he shall take of them, gold and silver and brass, and blue

01:50:08.110 --> 01:50:15.510
and purple and scarlet and fine linen and goat's hair and ram's skins dyed red and badger's

01:50:15.850 --> 01:50:23.050
skins and shittim wood, oil for the light, spices for anointing oil and for sweet incense,

01:50:23.890 --> 01:50:29.650
onyx stones and stones to be set in the ephod and in the breastplate, and let them make

01:50:29.650 --> 01:50:32.670
me a sanctuary that I may dwell among them.

01:50:33.750 --> 01:50:39.010
According to all that I show thee, after the pattern of the tabernacle, and the pattern

01:50:39.010 --> 01:50:43.350
of all the instruments thereof, even so shall ye make it.

01:50:45.450 --> 01:50:50.570
And they shall make an ark of shittim wood, two cubits and a half shall be the length

01:50:50.570 --> 01:50:55.610
thereof, and a cubit and a half the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height

01:50:55.610 --> 01:50:56.330
thereof.

01:50:56.330 --> 01:51:02.030
And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, within and without shalt thou overlay it,

01:51:02.410 --> 01:51:05.450
and shalt make upon it a crown of gold round about.

01:51:06.330 --> 01:51:11.430
And thou shalt cast four rings of gold for it, and put them in the four corners thereof,

01:51:11.810 --> 01:51:16.290
and two rings shall be in the one side of it, and two rings in the other side of it.

01:51:17.270 --> 01:51:21.530
And thou shalt make staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.

01:51:22.150 --> 01:51:27.150
And thou shalt put the staves into the rings by the sides of the ark that the ark may be

01:51:27.150 --> 01:51:28.130
borne with them.

01:51:28.810 --> 01:51:33.270
The staves shall be in the rings of the ark, they shall not be taken from it.

01:51:33.930 --> 01:51:37.750
And thou shalt put into the ark the testimony which I shall give thee.

01:51:38.650 --> 01:51:43.890
And thou shalt make a mercy-seat of pure gold, two cubits and a half shall be the length

01:51:43.890 --> 01:51:47.270
thereof, and a cubit and a half the breadth thereof.

01:51:47.950 --> 01:51:53.330
And thou shalt make two cherubims of gold, of beaten work, shalt thou make them in the

01:51:53.330 --> 01:51:54.870
two ends of the mercy-seat.

01:51:55.790 --> 01:52:00.810
And make one cherub on the one end, and the other cherub on the other end, even of the

01:52:00.810 --> 01:52:04.470
mercy-seat shall ye make the cherubims on the two ends thereof.

01:52:05.450 --> 01:52:10.370
And the cherubims shall stretch forth their wings on high, covering the mercy-seat with

01:52:10.370 --> 01:52:15.790
their wings, and their faces shall look one to another, toward the mercy-seat shall the

01:52:15.790 --> 01:52:17.710
faces of the cherubims be.

01:52:18.730 --> 01:52:23.930
And thou shalt put the mercy-seat above upon the ark, and in the ark thou shalt put the

01:52:23.930 --> 01:52:25.750
testimony that I shall give thee.

01:52:26.470 --> 01:52:31.370
And there I will meet with thee, and I will commune with thee from above the mercy-seat,

01:52:31.650 --> 01:52:37.050
from between the two cherubims which are upon the ark of the testimony of all things which

01:52:37.050 --> 01:52:40.450
I will give thee in commandment unto the children of Israel.

01:52:42.050 --> 01:52:47.770
Thou shalt also make a table of shittim wood, two cubits shall be the length thereof, and

01:52:47.770 --> 01:52:51.850
a cubit the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height thereof.

01:52:52.770 --> 01:52:58.230
And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, and make thereto a crown of gold round about.

01:52:59.150 --> 01:53:03.930
And thou shalt make unto it a border of an hand-breadth round about, and thou shalt make

01:53:03.930 --> 01:53:06.790
a golden crown to the border thereof round about.

01:53:07.350 --> 01:53:12.650
And thou shalt make for it four rings of gold, and put the rings in the four corners that

01:53:12.650 --> 01:53:14.390
are on the four feet thereof.

01:53:15.350 --> 01:53:20.230
Over against the border shall the rings be for places of the staves to bear the table.

01:53:21.170 --> 01:53:25.670
And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold that the

01:53:25.670 --> 01:53:27.390
table may be borne with them.

01:53:28.010 --> 01:53:33.590
And thou shalt make the dishes thereof, and spoons thereof, and covers thereof, and bowls

01:53:33.590 --> 01:53:38.010
thereof, to cover with all, of pure gold shalt thou make them.

01:53:38.630 --> 01:53:42.390
And thou shalt set upon the table showbread before me all way.

01:53:43.450 --> 01:53:48.310
And thou shalt make a candlestick of pure gold, of beaten work shall the candlestick

01:53:48.310 --> 01:53:54.810
be made, his shaft and his branches, his bowls, his knops, and his flowers shall be of the

01:53:54.810 --> 01:53:55.130
same.

01:53:56.250 --> 01:54:01.410
And six branches shall come out of the sides of it, three branches of the candlestick out

01:54:01.410 --> 01:54:05.870
of the one side, and three branches of the candlestick out of the other side.

01:54:06.230 --> 01:54:11.810
Three bowls made like unto almonds, with a knop and a flower in one branch, and three

01:54:11.810 --> 01:54:15.610
bowls made like almonds in the other branch, with a knop and a flower.

01:54:16.150 --> 01:54:19.410
So in the six branches that come out of the candlestick.

01:54:20.490 --> 01:54:25.290
And in the candlestick shall be four bowls made like unto almonds, with their knops and

01:54:25.290 --> 01:54:26.090
their flowers.

01:54:26.090 --> 01:54:31.470
And there shall be a knop under two branches of the same, and a knop under two branches

01:54:31.470 --> 01:54:36.610
of the same, and a knop under two branches of the same, according to the six branches

01:54:36.610 --> 01:54:38.690
that proceed out of the candlestick.

01:54:39.330 --> 01:54:42.310
Their knops and their branches shall be of the same.

01:54:42.950 --> 01:54:45.810
All it shall be one beaten work of pure gold.

01:54:46.570 --> 01:54:51.430
And thou shalt make the seven lamps thereof, and they shall light the lamps thereof, that

01:54:51.430 --> 01:54:53.630
they may give light over against it.

01:54:54.140 --> 01:54:58.770
And the tongs thereof, and the snuff-dishes thereof, shall be of pure gold.

01:54:59.810 --> 01:55:03.750
Of a talent of pure gold shall he make it with all these vessels.

01:55:04.650 --> 01:55:09.310
And look that thou maketh them after their pattern which was shewed thee in the mount.

01:55:14.110 --> 01:55:19.310
Moreover thou shalt make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine twined linen, and blue

01:55:19.310 --> 01:55:24.290
and purple and scarlet, with cherubims of cunning work shalt thou make them.

01:55:25.430 --> 01:55:30.130
The length of one curtain shall be eight and twenty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain

01:55:30.130 --> 01:55:33.970
four cubits, and every one of the curtains shall have one measure.

01:55:35.190 --> 01:55:40.490
The five curtains shall be coupled together one to another, and other five curtains shall

01:55:40.490 --> 01:55:42.030
be coupled one to another.

01:55:42.770 --> 01:55:47.410
And thou shalt make loops of blue upon the edge of the one curtain from the selvedge

01:55:47.410 --> 01:55:52.750
in the coupling, and likewise shalt thou make in the uttermost edge of another curtain in

01:55:52.750 --> 01:55:54.010
the coupling of the second.

01:55:55.190 --> 01:56:00.410
Fifty loops shalt thou make in the one curtain, and fifty loops shalt thou make in the edge

01:56:00.410 --> 01:56:05.330
of the curtain that is in the coupling of the second, that the loops may take hold one

01:56:05.330 --> 01:56:05.910
of another.

01:56:07.050 --> 01:56:12.030
And thou shalt make fifty tashes of gold, and couple the curtains together with the

01:56:12.030 --> 01:56:14.890
tashes, and it shall be one tabernacle.

01:56:16.050 --> 01:56:21.350
And thou shalt make curtains of goat's hair to be a covering upon the tabernacle, eleven

01:56:21.350 --> 01:56:23.050
curtains shalt thou make.

01:56:23.930 --> 01:56:28.590
The length of one curtain shall be thirty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four

01:56:28.590 --> 01:56:32.190
cubits, and the eleven curtains shall be all of one measure.

01:56:33.450 --> 01:56:39.070
And thou shalt couple five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves, and shalt

01:56:39.070 --> 01:56:42.250
double the sixth curtain in the forefront of the tabernacle.

01:56:43.170 --> 01:56:47.910
And thou shalt make fifty loops on the edge of the one curtain that is outmost in the

01:56:47.910 --> 01:56:52.310
coupling, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain which coupleth the second.

01:56:53.190 --> 01:56:58.550
And thou shalt make fifty tashes of brass, and put the tashes into the loops, and couple

01:56:58.550 --> 01:57:00.930
the tent together, that it may be one.

01:57:03.250 --> 01:57:07.710
And the remnant of that remaineth that the curtains of the tent, the half-curtain that

01:57:07.710 --> 01:57:10.930
remaineth, shall hang over the backside of the tabernacle.

01:57:11.470 --> 01:57:16.530
And a cubit on the one side, and a cubit on the other side, of that which remaineth in

01:57:16.530 --> 01:57:21.130
the length of the curtains of the tent, it shall hang over the sides of the tabernacle,

01:57:21.450 --> 01:57:24.350
on this side, and on that side, to cover it.

01:57:25.470 --> 01:57:30.670
And thou shalt make a covering for the tent of ram-skins dyed red, and a covering above

01:57:30.670 --> 01:57:31.930
of badger's skins.

01:57:32.750 --> 01:57:37.110
And thou shalt make boards for the tabernacle of shittim wood standing up.

01:57:37.830 --> 01:57:42.230
Ten cubits shall be the length of a board, and a cubit and a half shall be the breadth

01:57:42.230 --> 01:57:43.090
of one board.

01:57:44.130 --> 01:57:50.050
Two tenons shall there be in one board, set in order one against another, thus shalt thou

01:57:50.050 --> 01:57:52.390
make for all the boards of the tabernacle.

01:57:53.190 --> 01:57:58.330
And thou shalt make the boards for the tabernacle twenty boards on the south side southward.

01:57:58.830 --> 01:58:04.350
And thou shalt make forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards, two sockets under

01:58:04.350 --> 01:58:09.610
one board for his two tenons, and two sockets under another board for his two tenons.

01:58:10.310 --> 01:58:14.990
And for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, there shall be twenty boards.

01:58:15.470 --> 01:58:21.590
And there are forty sockets of silver, two sockets under one board, and two sockets under

01:58:21.590 --> 01:58:22.430
another board.

01:58:23.130 --> 01:58:27.350
And for the sides of the tabernacle westward, thou shalt make six boards.

01:58:27.830 --> 01:58:32.390
And two boards shalt thou make for the corners of the tabernacle and the two sides.

01:58:32.990 --> 01:58:37.070
And they shall be coupled together beneath, and they shall be coupled together above the

01:58:37.070 --> 01:58:42.930
head of it onto one ring, thus shall it be for them both, they shall be for the two corners.

01:58:43.710 --> 01:58:49.270
And they shall be eight boards, and their sockets of silver sixteen sockets, two sockets

01:58:49.270 --> 01:58:52.750
under one board, and two sockets under another board.

01:58:53.790 --> 01:59:01.910
And thou shalt make bars of shittim wood, five for the boards of the one side of the

01:59:01.910 --> 01:59:07.170
tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle for the two sides

01:59:07.170 --> 01:59:07.890
westward.

01:59:08.450 --> 01:59:12.650
And the middle bar in the midst of the boards shall reach from end to end.

01:59:13.330 --> 01:59:18.330
And thou shalt overlay the boards with gold, and make their rings of gold for places for

01:59:18.330 --> 01:59:21.810
the bars, and thou shalt overlay the bars with gold.

01:59:22.470 --> 01:59:27.010
And thou shalt rear up the tabernacle according to the fashion thereof which was shewed thee

01:59:27.010 --> 01:59:27.690
in the mount.

01:59:28.630 --> 01:59:34.510
And thou shalt make a veil of blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen of cunning

01:59:34.510 --> 01:59:37.430
work with cherubims shall it be made.

01:59:37.990 --> 01:59:43.170
And thou shalt hang it upon four pillars of shittim wood overlaid with gold, their hooks

01:59:43.170 --> 01:59:46.090
shall be of gold upon the four sockets of silver.

01:59:47.030 --> 01:59:51.950
And thou shalt hang up the veil under the tashes that thou mayest bring in thither within

01:59:51.950 --> 01:59:57.090
the veil the ark of the testimony, and the veil shall divide unto you between the holy

01:59:57.090 --> 01:59:58.590
place and the most holy.

01:59:59.450 --> 02:00:04.310
And thou shalt put the mercy seat upon the ark of the testimony in the most holy place.

02:00:05.010 --> 02:00:10.150
And thou shalt set the table without the veil and the candlestick over against the table

02:00:10.150 --> 02:00:12.850
on the side of the tabernacle toward the south.

02:00:13.410 --> 02:00:15.750
And thou shalt put the table on the north side.

02:00:16.630 --> 02:00:21.810
And thou shalt make an hanging for the door of the tent of blue and purple and scarlet

02:00:21.810 --> 02:00:24.850
and fine twined linen wrought with needlework.

02:00:25.500 --> 02:00:30.790
And thou shalt make for the hanging five pillars of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold,

02:00:31.110 --> 02:00:32.850
and their hooks shall be of gold.

02:00:33.190 --> 02:00:36.250
And thou shalt cast five sockets of brass for them.

02:00:40.010 --> 02:00:44.950
And thou shalt make an altar of shittim wood, five cubits long and five cubits broad.

02:00:45.410 --> 02:00:49.650
The altar shall be four square, and the height thereof shall be three cubits.

02:00:50.350 --> 02:00:54.110
And thou shalt make the horns of it upon the four corners thereof.

02:00:54.450 --> 02:00:58.570
His horns shall be of the same, and thou shalt overlay it with brass.

02:00:59.410 --> 02:01:04.630
And thou shalt make his pans to receive his ashes, and his shovels, and his basins, and

02:01:04.630 --> 02:01:10.190
his flesh-hooks, and his fire-pans, all the vessels thereof thou shalt make of brass.

02:01:11.190 --> 02:01:16.430
And thou shalt make for it a great of network of brass, and upon the net shalt thou make

02:01:16.430 --> 02:01:19.590
four brazen rings, in the four corners thereof.

02:01:20.190 --> 02:01:24.910
And thou shalt put it under the compass of the altar beneath, that the net may be even

02:01:24.910 --> 02:01:26.330
to the midst of the altar.

02:01:27.190 --> 02:01:32.110
And thou shalt make staves for the altar, staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with

02:01:32.110 --> 02:01:32.670
brass.

02:01:33.230 --> 02:01:38.030
And the staves shall be put into the rings, and the staves shall be upon the two sides

02:01:38.030 --> 02:01:39.610
of the altar, to bear it.

02:01:40.770 --> 02:01:42.730
Hollow with boards shalt thou make it.

02:01:42.730 --> 02:01:46.370
As it was shewed thee in the mount, so shall they make it.

02:01:47.070 --> 02:01:52.250
And thou shalt make the court of the tabernacle, for the south side southward there shall be

02:01:52.250 --> 02:01:58.210
hangings for the court of fine twine linen of an hundred cubits long for one side, and

02:01:58.210 --> 02:02:03.270
the twenty pillars thereof and their twenty sockets shall be of brass, the hooks of the

02:02:03.270 --> 02:02:05.630
pillars and their fillets shall be of silver.

02:02:06.710 --> 02:02:11.490
And likewise for the north side in length there shall be hangings of an hundred cubits

02:02:11.490 --> 02:02:17.210
long, and his twenty pillars and their twenty sockets of brass, the hooks of the pillars

02:02:17.210 --> 02:02:18.750
and their fillets of silver.

02:02:19.870 --> 02:02:24.950
And for the breadth of the court on the west side shall be hangings of fifty cubits, their

02:02:24.950 --> 02:02:27.190
pillars ten and their sockets ten.

02:02:28.070 --> 02:02:32.470
And the breadth of the court on the east side eastward shall be fifty cubits.

02:02:32.930 --> 02:02:38.150
The hangings of one side of the gate shall be fifteen cubits, their pillars three and

02:02:38.150 --> 02:02:39.410
their sockets three.

02:02:40.210 --> 02:02:46.050
And on the other side shall be hangings fifteen cubits, their pillars three and their sockets

02:02:46.050 --> 02:02:46.550
three.

02:02:47.430 --> 02:02:52.490
And for the gate of the court shall be in hanging of twenty cubits of blue and purple

02:02:52.490 --> 02:02:58.530
and scarlet and fine twine linen wrought with needlework, and their pillars shall be four

02:02:58.530 --> 02:02:59.970
and their sockets four.

02:03:01.030 --> 02:03:05.810
All the pillars round about the court shall be filleted with silver, their hooks shall

02:03:05.810 --> 02:03:08.270
be of silver and their sockets of brass.

02:03:09.690 --> 02:03:15.030
The length of the court shall be in hundred cubits and the breadth fifty everywhere and

02:03:15.030 --> 02:03:19.470
the height five cubits of fine twine linen and their sockets of brass.

02:03:20.510 --> 02:03:25.770
All the vessels of the tabernacle and all the service thereof and all the pins thereof

02:03:25.770 --> 02:03:28.890
and all the pins of the court shall be of brass.

02:03:29.990 --> 02:03:35.190
And thou shalt command the children of Israel that they bring the pure oil olive beaten

02:03:35.190 --> 02:03:38.590
for the light, to cause the lamp to burn always.

02:03:39.610 --> 02:03:45.330
In the tabernacle of the congregation, without the veil which is before the testimony, Aaron

02:03:45.330 --> 02:03:49.410
and his sons shall order it from evening to morning before the Lord.

02:03:49.890 --> 02:03:54.990
It shall be a statute for ever unto their generations on the behalf of the children

02:03:54.990 --> 02:03:55.630
of Israel.

02:04:28.670 --> 02:04:34.050
And take thou unto thee Aaron thy brother, and his sons with him, from among the children

02:04:34.050 --> 02:04:39.770
of Israel, that he may minister unto me in the priest's office, even Aaron, Nadab, and

02:04:39.770 --> 02:04:43.430
Abihu, Eliezer, and Ithamar, Aaron's sons.

02:04:44.330 --> 02:04:48.770
And thou shalt make holy garments for Aaron thy brother, for glory, and for beauty.

02:04:49.510 --> 02:04:54.830
And thou shalt speak unto all that are wise-hearted, whom I have filled with the spirit of wisdom

02:04:54.830 --> 02:05:00.670
that they may make Aaron's garments to consecrate him, that he may minister unto me in the priest's

02:05:00.670 --> 02:05:01.170
office.

02:05:02.230 --> 02:05:07.390
And these are the garments which they shall make, a breast-plate, and an ephod, and a

02:05:07.390 --> 02:05:10.750
robe, and a broidered coat, a mitre, and a girdle.

02:05:11.090 --> 02:05:16.230
And they shall make holy garments for Aaron thy brother, and his sons, that he may minister

02:05:16.230 --> 02:05:18.190
unto me in the priest's office.

02:05:19.030 --> 02:05:23.770
And they shall take gold, and blue, and purple, and scarlet, and fine linen.

02:05:24.450 --> 02:05:30.250
And they shall make the ephod of gold, of blue, and of purple, and of scarlet, and fine-twined

02:05:30.250 --> 02:05:32.090
linen, with cunning work.

02:05:32.850 --> 02:05:37.990
It shall have the two shoulder-pieces thereof joined at the two edges thereof, and so it

02:05:37.990 --> 02:05:39.150
shall be joined together.

02:05:40.170 --> 02:05:45.270
And the curious girdle of the ephod which is upon it shall be of the same according

02:05:45.270 --> 02:05:51.770
to the work thereof, even of gold, of blue, and purple, and scarlet, and fine-twined linen.

02:05:53.090 --> 02:05:58.070
And thou shalt take two onyx stones, and engrave on them the names of the children of Israel,

02:05:58.790 --> 02:06:04.770
six of their names on one stone, and the other six names of the rest on the other stone according

02:06:04.770 --> 02:06:05.710
to their birth.

02:06:06.810 --> 02:06:11.890
With the work of an engraver and stone, like the engravings of a signet, shalt thou engrave

02:06:11.890 --> 02:06:16.910
the two stones with the names of the children of Israel, thou shalt make them to be set

02:06:16.910 --> 02:06:18.210
in ushahs of gold.

02:06:19.730 --> 02:06:24.550
And thou shalt put the two stones upon the shoulders of the ephod for stones of memorial

02:06:24.550 --> 02:06:29.990
unto the children of Israel, and Aaron shall bear their names before the Lord upon his

02:06:29.990 --> 02:06:31.850
two shoulders for a memorial.

02:06:33.430 --> 02:06:38.990
And thou shalt make ushahs of gold and two chains of pure gold at the ends, of wreath

02:06:38.990 --> 02:06:43.690
and work, shalt thou make them and fasten the wreath and chains to the ushahs.

02:06:44.830 --> 02:06:50.170
And thou shalt make the breastplate of judgment with cunning work, after the work of the ephod

02:06:50.170 --> 02:06:56.230
thou shalt make it, of gold, of blue, and of purple, and of scarlet, and of fine-twined

02:06:56.230 --> 02:06:58.010
linen shalt thou make it.

02:06:58.810 --> 02:07:04.110
Four square it shall be being doubled, a span shall be the length thereof, and a span shall

02:07:04.110 --> 02:07:05.510
be the breadth thereof.

02:07:05.970 --> 02:07:11.950
And thou shalt set in it settings of stones, even four rows of stones, the first row shall

02:07:11.950 --> 02:07:18.630
be a sardius, a topaz, and a carvokal, this shall be the first row, and the second row

02:07:18.630 --> 02:07:24.930
shall be an emerald, a sapphire, and a diamond, and the third row a ligure, an agate, and

02:07:24.930 --> 02:07:31.570
an amethyst, and the fourth row a burl, and an onyx, and a jasper, they shall be set in

02:07:31.570 --> 02:07:33.210
their enclosings.

02:07:34.090 --> 02:07:38.550
And the stones shall be with the names of the children of Israel, twelve, according

02:07:38.550 --> 02:07:44.290
to their names, like the engravings of a signet, every one with his name shall they be according

02:07:44.290 --> 02:07:45.550
to the twelve tribes.

02:07:46.730 --> 02:07:51.710
And thou shalt make upon the breastplate chains at the ends of wreath and work of pure gold.

02:07:52.490 --> 02:07:57.390
And thou shalt make upon the breastplate two rings of gold, and shalt put the two rings

02:07:57.390 --> 02:07:59.170
on the two ends of the breastplate.

02:07:59.770 --> 02:08:04.430
And thou shalt put the two wreath and chains of gold in the two rings which are on the

02:08:04.430 --> 02:08:05.650
ends of the breastplate.

02:08:06.370 --> 02:08:11.170
And the other two ends of the two wreath and chains thou shalt fasten in the two ooshes,

02:08:11.610 --> 02:08:14.750
and put them on the shoulder-pieces of the ephod before it.

02:08:15.470 --> 02:08:20.070
And thou shalt make two rings of gold, and thou shalt put them upon the two ends of the

02:08:20.070 --> 02:08:24.550
breastplate in the border thereof, which is in the side of the ephod inward.

02:08:25.170 --> 02:08:30.590
And two other rings of gold thou shalt make, and shalt put them on the two sides of the

02:08:30.590 --> 02:08:37.010
ephod underneath, toward the fore-part thereof, over against the other coupling thereof, above

02:08:37.010 --> 02:08:39.150
the curius girdle of the ephod.

02:08:40.130 --> 02:08:44.710
And they shall bind the breastplate by the rings thereof, unto the rings of the ephod,

02:08:44.730 --> 02:08:50.170
with a lace of blue, that it may be above the curius girdle of the ephod, and that the

02:08:50.170 --> 02:08:52.710
breastplate be not loosed from the ephod.

02:08:53.630 --> 02:08:58.170
And Aaron shall bear the names of the children of Israel, and the breastplate of judgment,

02:08:58.350 --> 02:09:04.150
upon his heart, when he goeth in unto the holy place, for a memorial before the Lord

02:09:04.150 --> 02:09:04.910
continually.

02:09:06.210 --> 02:09:11.950
And thou shalt put in the breastplate of judgment the Urim and the Thummim, and they shall be

02:09:11.950 --> 02:09:16.750
upon Aaron's heart, when he goeth in before the Lord, and Aaron shall bear the judgment

02:09:16.750 --> 02:09:20.810
of the children of Israel, upon his heart, before the Lord continually.

02:09:22.110 --> 02:09:27.470
And thou shalt make the robe of the ephod all of blue, and there shall be a hole in

02:09:27.470 --> 02:09:32.850
the top of it, in the midst thereof, it shall have a binding of woven work round about the

02:09:32.850 --> 02:09:37.430
hole of it, as it were the hole of an hebergen, that it be not rent.

02:09:38.350 --> 02:09:42.990
And beneath upon the hem of it, thou shalt make pomegranates of blue, and of purple,

02:09:43.230 --> 02:09:49.130
and of scarlet, round about the hem thereof, and bells of gold between them round about,

02:09:49.130 --> 02:09:55.250
a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, upon the hem of the

02:09:55.250 --> 02:09:56.310
robe round about.

02:09:57.310 --> 02:10:02.190
And it shall be upon Aaron to minister, and his sound shall be heard, when he goeth in

02:10:02.190 --> 02:10:07.490
unto the holy place before the Lord, and when he cometh out, that he die not.

02:10:08.750 --> 02:10:13.790
And thou shalt make a plate of pure gold, and grave upon it, like the engravings of

02:10:13.790 --> 02:10:16.550
a signet, holiness to the Lord.

02:10:17.410 --> 02:10:22.810
And thou shalt put it on a blue lace, that it may be upon the mitre, upon the forefront

02:10:22.810 --> 02:10:24.530
of the mitre it shall be.

02:10:25.470 --> 02:10:30.650
And it shall be upon Aaron's forehead, that Aaron may bear the iniquity of the holy things

02:10:30.650 --> 02:10:34.570
which the children of Israel shall hallow in all their holy gifts.

02:10:35.070 --> 02:10:39.970
And it shall be always upon his forehead, that they may be accepted before the Lord.

02:10:40.950 --> 02:10:45.850
And thou shalt embroider the coat of fine linen, and thou shalt make the mitre of fine

02:10:45.850 --> 02:10:49.010
linen, and thou shalt make the girdle of needlework.

02:10:49.850 --> 02:10:55.010
And for Aaron's sons thou shalt make coats, and thou shalt make for them girdles, and

02:10:55.010 --> 02:10:58.550
bonnets shalt thou make for them, for glory and for beauty.

02:10:59.370 --> 02:11:05.330
And thou shalt put them upon Aaron thy brother, and his sons with him, and shalt anoint them,

02:11:05.790 --> 02:11:10.650
and consecrate them, and sanctify them, that they may minister unto me in the priest's

02:11:10.650 --> 02:11:11.090
office.

02:11:11.850 --> 02:11:16.730
And thou shalt make them linen breeches to cover their nakedness, for in the loins even

02:11:16.730 --> 02:11:18.650
unto the thighs they shall reach.

02:11:19.110 --> 02:11:23.810
And they shall be upon Aaron, and upon his sons, when they come in unto the tabernacle

02:11:23.810 --> 02:11:29.470
of the congregation, or when they come near unto the altar to minister in the holy place,

02:11:29.990 --> 02:11:32.270
that they bear not iniquity and die.

02:11:32.790 --> 02:11:36.990
It shall be a statute for ever unto him and his seed after him.

02:11:40.840 --> 02:11:45.770
And this is the thing that thou shalt do unto them to hallow them to minister unto me in

02:11:45.770 --> 02:11:46.930
the priest's office.

02:11:47.410 --> 02:11:53.730
Take one young bullock and two rams without blemish, and unleavened bread and cakes unleavened,

02:11:53.830 --> 02:11:59.870
tempered with oil, and wafers unleavened anointed with oil, of wheat and flour shalt thou make

02:11:59.870 --> 02:12:00.290
them.

02:12:00.930 --> 02:12:05.410
And thou shalt put them into one basket, and bring them in the basket with the bullock

02:12:05.410 --> 02:12:06.690
and the two rams.

02:12:07.470 --> 02:12:12.390
And Aaron and his sons thou shalt bring unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation,

02:12:12.790 --> 02:12:14.430
and shalt wash them with water.

02:12:15.370 --> 02:12:20.390
And thou shalt take the garments, and put upon Aaron the coat and the robe of the ephod

02:12:20.390 --> 02:12:25.890
and the ephod and the breastplate, and guard him with the curious girdle of the ephod.

02:12:26.390 --> 02:12:31.410
And thou shalt put the mitre upon his head, and put the holy crown upon the mitre.

02:12:32.050 --> 02:12:37.210
Then shalt thou take the anointing oil, and pour it upon his head, and anoint him.

02:12:37.670 --> 02:12:40.710
And thou shalt bring his sons, and put coats upon them.

02:12:41.190 --> 02:12:46.130
And thou shalt gird them with girdles, Aaron and his sons, and put the bonnets on them.

02:12:46.390 --> 02:12:49.950
And the priest's office shall be theirs for a perpetual statute.

02:12:50.610 --> 02:12:53.150
And thou shalt consecrate Aaron and his sons.

02:12:54.150 --> 02:12:58.490
And thou shalt cause a bullock to be brought before the tabernacle of the congregation,

02:12:58.990 --> 02:13:03.130
and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands upon the head of the bullock.

02:13:03.710 --> 02:13:08.170
And thou shalt kill the bullock before the Lord by the door of the tabernacle of the

02:13:08.170 --> 02:13:08.810
congregation.

02:13:09.710 --> 02:13:14.150
And thou shalt take the blood of the bullock, and put it upon the horns of the altar with

02:13:14.150 --> 02:13:18.210
thy finger, and pour all the blood beside the bottom of the altar.

02:13:19.210 --> 02:13:24.330
And thou shalt take all the fat that covereth thee inwards, and the caul that is above the

02:13:24.790 --> 02:13:29.830
and the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon them, and burn them upon the altar.

02:13:30.690 --> 02:13:36.010
But the flesh of the bullock, and his skin, and his dung, shalt thou burn with fire without

02:13:36.010 --> 02:13:36.610
the camp.

02:13:37.090 --> 02:13:38.250
It is a sin offering.

02:13:39.450 --> 02:13:44.630
Thou shalt also take one ram, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands upon the head

02:13:44.630 --> 02:13:45.410
of the ram.

02:13:46.090 --> 02:13:51.510
And thou shalt slay the ram, and shalt take his blood, and sprinkle it round about upon

02:13:51.510 --> 02:13:52.110
the altar.

02:13:53.130 --> 02:13:58.910
And thou shalt cut the ram in pieces, and wash the inwards of him, and his legs, and

02:13:58.910 --> 02:14:01.790
put them under his pieces, and unto his head.

02:14:02.570 --> 02:14:05.250
And thou shalt burn the whole ram upon the altar.

02:14:05.730 --> 02:14:07.750
It is a burnt offering unto the Lord.

02:14:08.150 --> 02:14:12.430
It is a sweet savor, an offering made by fire, unto the Lord.

02:14:13.570 --> 02:14:18.490
And thou shalt take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands upon the

02:14:18.490 --> 02:14:19.410
head of the ram.

02:14:20.250 --> 02:14:25.270
Then shalt thou kill the ram, and take of his blood, and put it upon the tip of the

02:14:25.270 --> 02:14:30.510
right ear of Aaron, and upon the tip of the right ear of his sons, and upon the thumb

02:14:30.510 --> 02:14:35.890
of their right hand, and upon the great toe of their right foot, and sprinkle the blood

02:14:35.890 --> 02:14:37.690
upon the altar round about.

02:14:38.630 --> 02:14:43.970
And thou shalt take of the blood that is upon the altar, and of the anointing oil, and sprinkle

02:14:43.970 --> 02:14:49.970
Aaron, and upon his garments, and upon his sons, and upon the garments of his sons with

02:14:49.970 --> 02:14:50.390
him.

02:14:50.670 --> 02:14:55.650
And he shall be hallowed, and his garments, and his sons, and his sons' garments with

02:14:55.650 --> 02:14:56.070
him.

02:14:57.310 --> 02:15:02.850
Also thou shalt take of the ram the fat, and the rump, and the fat that covereth the inwards,

02:15:03.230 --> 02:15:08.030
and the call above the liver, and the two kidneys, and the fat that is upon them, and

02:15:08.030 --> 02:15:11.190
the right shoulder, for it is a ram of consecration.

02:15:11.930 --> 02:15:17.370
And one loaf of bread, and one cake of oiled bread, and one wafer out of the basket of

02:15:17.370 --> 02:15:19.850
the unleavened bread that is before the Lord.

02:15:20.550 --> 02:15:25.950
And thou shalt put all in the hands of Aaron, and in the hands of his sons, and shalt waive

02:15:25.950 --> 02:15:28.350
them for a wave offering before the Lord.

02:15:29.110 --> 02:15:34.570
And thou shalt receive them of their hands, and burn them upon the altar for a burnt offering,

02:15:34.970 --> 02:15:37.210
for a sweet savor before the Lord.

02:15:37.510 --> 02:15:40.770
It is an offering made by fire under the Lord.

02:15:41.870 --> 02:15:46.350
And thou shalt take the breast of the ram of Aaron's consecration, and waive it for

02:15:46.350 --> 02:15:50.090
a wave offering before the Lord, and it shall be thy part.

02:15:50.910 --> 02:15:55.450
And thou shalt sanctify the breast of the wave offering, and the shoulder of the heave

02:15:55.450 --> 02:16:00.890
offering, which is waived, and which is heaved up, of the ram of the consecration, even of

02:16:00.890 --> 02:16:04.130
that which is for Aaron, and of that which is for his sons.

02:16:04.650 --> 02:16:09.670
And it shall be Aaron's and his sons by a statute forever from the children of Israel,

02:16:10.050 --> 02:16:14.370
for it is an heave offering, and it shall be an heave offering from the children of

02:16:14.370 --> 02:16:20.390
Israel of the sacrifice of their peace offerings, even their heave offering, unto the Lord.

02:16:22.130 --> 02:16:27.650
And the holy garments of Aaron shall be his sons after him, to be anointed therein, and

02:16:27.650 --> 02:16:29.310
to be consecrated in them.

02:16:29.310 --> 02:16:35.110
And that son that is priest in his stead shall put them all in seven days, when he cometh

02:16:35.110 --> 02:16:39.430
into the tabernacle of the congregation, to minister in the holy place.

02:16:40.510 --> 02:16:45.530
And thou shalt take the ram of the consecration, and seeth his flesh in the holy place.

02:16:46.530 --> 02:16:51.430
And Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram, and the bread that is in the basket,

02:16:51.730 --> 02:16:54.330
by the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.

02:16:54.950 --> 02:16:59.850
And they shall eat those things wherewith the atonement was made, to consecrate and

02:16:59.850 --> 02:17:01.010
to sanctify them.

02:17:01.390 --> 02:17:05.290
But a stranger shall not eat thereof, because they are holy.

02:17:06.530 --> 02:17:11.370
And if aught of the flesh of the consecrations, or of the bread, remain unto the morning,

02:17:11.790 --> 02:17:14.270
then thou shalt burn the remainder with fire.

02:17:14.590 --> 02:17:17.090
It shall not be eaten, because it is holy.

02:17:18.150 --> 02:17:23.750
And thus shalt thou do unto Aaron, and to his sons, according to all things which I

02:17:23.750 --> 02:17:27.370
have commanded thee, seven days shalt thou consecrate them.

02:17:28.210 --> 02:17:32.370
And thou shalt offer every day a bullock for a sin offering, for atonement.

02:17:32.950 --> 02:17:37.010
And thou shalt cleanse the altar, when thou hast made an atonement for it.

02:17:37.330 --> 02:17:39.790
And thou shalt anoint it, to sanctify it.

02:17:40.790 --> 02:17:45.250
Seven days thou shalt make an atonement for the altar, and sanctify it.

02:17:45.430 --> 02:17:47.430
And it shall be an altar most holy.

02:17:47.990 --> 02:17:50.390
Whatsoever toucheth the altar, shall be holy.

02:17:51.470 --> 02:17:57.210
Now this is that which thou shalt offer upon the altar, two lambs of the first year, day

02:17:57.210 --> 02:17:58.590
by day, continually.

02:17:59.470 --> 02:18:04.450
The one lamb thou shalt offer in the morning, and the other lamb thou shalt offer at even.

02:18:05.250 --> 02:18:10.270
And with the one lamb a tenth theel of flour mingled with the fourth part of an hen of

02:18:10.270 --> 02:18:14.830
beaten oil, and the fourth part of an hen of wine for a drink offering.

02:18:16.010 --> 02:18:21.690
And the other lamb thou shalt offer at even, and shalt do thereto according to the meat

02:18:21.690 --> 02:18:27.010
offering of the morning, and according to the drink offering thereof, for a sweet savour,

02:18:27.250 --> 02:18:29.930
an offering made by fire unto the Lord.

02:18:31.130 --> 02:18:36.830
This shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the door of the tabernacle

02:18:36.830 --> 02:18:42.130
of the congregation before the Lord, where I will meet you to speak there unto thee.

02:18:42.830 --> 02:18:47.970
And there I will meet with the children of Israel, and the tabernacle shall be sanctified

02:18:47.970 --> 02:18:49.010
by my glory.

02:18:49.510 --> 02:18:53.510
And I will sanctify the tabernacle of the congregation and the altar.

02:18:53.910 --> 02:18:59.810
I will sanctify also both Aaron and his sons, to minister to me in the priest's office.

02:19:00.310 --> 02:19:04.270
And I will dwell among the children of Israel, and will be their God.

02:19:04.870 --> 02:19:09.870
And they shall know that I am the Lord their God, that brought them forth out of the land

02:19:09.870 --> 02:19:12.210
of Egypt, that I may dwell among them.

02:19:12.530 --> 02:19:14.470
I am the Lord their God.

02:19:18.610 --> 02:19:21.350
And thou shalt make an altar to burn incense upon.

02:19:21.750 --> 02:19:23.790
Of shittim wood shalt thou make it.

02:19:24.470 --> 02:19:28.310
A cubit shall be the length thereof, and a cubit the breadth thereof.

02:19:28.650 --> 02:19:34.130
Four square shall it be, and two cubits shall be the height thereof, the horns thereof shall

02:19:34.130 --> 02:19:35.030
be of the same.

02:19:35.730 --> 02:19:41.250
And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, the top thereof, and the sides thereof round

02:19:41.250 --> 02:19:43.290
about, and the horns thereof.

02:19:43.690 --> 02:19:47.330
And thou shalt make unto it a crown of gold round about.

02:19:48.690 --> 02:19:53.450
And two golden rings shalt thou make to it under the crown of it, by the two corners

02:19:53.450 --> 02:19:56.790
thereof, upon the two sides of it shalt thou make it.

02:19:57.030 --> 02:20:00.350
And they shall be for places for the staves to bear it withal.

02:20:01.110 --> 02:20:05.270
And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.

02:20:05.850 --> 02:20:10.570
And thou shalt put it before the veil that is by the ark of the testimony, before the

02:20:10.570 --> 02:20:14.310
mercy-seat that is over the testimony, where I will meet with thee.

02:20:15.110 --> 02:20:18.690
And Aaron shall burn thereon sweet incense every morning.

02:20:19.030 --> 02:20:22.510
When he dresseth the lamps he shall burn incense upon it.

02:20:23.110 --> 02:20:28.430
And when Aaron lighteth the lamps at even he shall burn incense upon it, a perpetual

02:20:28.430 --> 02:20:31.850
incense before the Lord throughout your generations.

02:20:32.650 --> 02:20:39.390
He shall offer no strange incense thereon, nor burnt sacrifice, nor meat offering, neither

02:20:39.390 --> 02:20:41.690
shall ye pour drink offering thereon.

02:20:42.470 --> 02:20:46.950
And Aaron shall make an atonement upon the horns of it once in a year with the blood

02:20:46.950 --> 02:20:48.770
of the sin-offering of atonements.

02:20:49.410 --> 02:20:53.690
Once in the year shall he make atonement upon it throughout your generations.

02:20:54.030 --> 02:20:56.330
It is most holy unto the Lord.

02:20:57.770 --> 02:21:03.550
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel

02:21:03.550 --> 02:21:09.470
after their number, then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord when

02:21:09.470 --> 02:21:14.170
thou numberest them, that there be no plague among them when thou numberest them.

02:21:14.950 --> 02:21:19.870
This they shall give every one that passeth among them that are numbered half a shekel

02:21:19.870 --> 02:21:25.830
after the shekel of the sanctuary, a shekel is twenty girahs, and half shekel shall be

02:21:25.830 --> 02:21:27.110
the offering of the Lord.

02:21:28.450 --> 02:21:33.490
Every one that passeth among them that are numbered from twenty years old and above shall

02:21:33.490 --> 02:21:35.430
give an offering unto the Lord.

02:21:36.310 --> 02:21:41.750
The rich shall not give more, and the poor shall not give less than half a shekel when

02:21:41.750 --> 02:21:45.730
they give an offering unto the Lord to make an atonement for your souls.

02:21:46.550 --> 02:21:50.870
And thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel, and shalt appoint

02:21:50.870 --> 02:21:55.930
it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation, that it may be a memorial unto

02:21:55.930 --> 02:22:00.590
the children of Israel before the Lord to make an atonement for your souls.

02:22:02.190 --> 02:22:08.350
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Thou shalt also make a laver of brass and his foot

02:22:08.350 --> 02:22:14.450
also of brass to wash withal, and thou shalt put it between the tabernacle of the congregation

02:22:14.450 --> 02:22:17.590
and the altar, and thou shalt put water therein.

02:22:18.370 --> 02:22:22.410
For Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet thereat.

02:22:22.870 --> 02:22:28.230
When they go into the tabernacle of the congregation they shall wash with water that they die not,

02:22:28.750 --> 02:22:34.530
or when they come near to the altar to minister to burn offering made by fire unto the Lord.

02:22:35.310 --> 02:22:40.630
So they shall wash their hands and their feet that they die not, and it shall be a statute

02:22:40.630 --> 02:22:45.430
for ever to them, even to him and to his seed, throughout their generations.

02:22:47.030 --> 02:22:53.650
Moreover the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Take thou also unto the principal spices of

02:22:53.650 --> 02:23:01.290
pure myrrh 500 shekels, and of sweet cinnamon half so much, even 250 shekels, and of sweet

02:23:01.290 --> 02:23:08.850
calamus 250 shekels, and of castia 500 shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, and of

02:23:08.850 --> 02:23:14.990
oil olive and hyn, and thou shalt make it an oil of holy ointment and ointment compound

02:23:14.990 --> 02:23:21.350
after the ark of the apothecary, it shall be in holy anointing oil, and thou shalt anoint

02:23:21.350 --> 02:23:26.470
the tabernacle of the congregation therewith, and the ark of the testimony, and the table

02:23:26.470 --> 02:23:31.790
and all his vessels, and the candlestick and his vessels, and the altar of incense, and

02:23:31.790 --> 02:23:37.730
the altar of burnt offering with all his vessels, and the laver and his foot, and thou shalt

02:23:37.730 --> 02:23:44.110
sanctify them that they may be most holy, whatsoever toucheth them shall be holy, and

02:23:44.110 --> 02:23:48.770
thou shalt anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them that they may minister unto

02:23:48.770 --> 02:23:53.830
me in the priest's office, and thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying,

02:23:54.070 --> 02:23:58.470
This shall be in holy anointing oil unto me throughout your generations.

02:23:59.430 --> 02:24:05.330
Upon man's flesh shall it not be poured, neither shall ye make any other like it after the

02:24:05.330 --> 02:24:12.210
composition of it, it is holy, and it shall be holy unto you. Whosoever compoundeth any

02:24:12.210 --> 02:24:18.050
like it, or whosoever putteth any of it upon a stranger, shall even be cut off from his

02:24:18.050 --> 02:24:18.550
people.

02:24:19.970 --> 02:24:27.110
And the Lord said unto Moses, Take unto these sweet spices Stacti and Onica and Galbanum,

02:24:27.410 --> 02:24:33.330
these sweet spices with pure frankincense, of each shall there be a like weight, and

02:24:33.330 --> 02:24:38.950
thou shalt make it a perfume, a confection, after the art of the apothecary, tempered

02:24:38.950 --> 02:24:44.870
together, pure and holy, and thou shalt beat some of it very small, and put of it before

02:24:44.870 --> 02:24:50.570
the testimony and the tabernacle of the congregation, where I will meet with thee, it shall be unto

02:24:50.570 --> 02:24:51.910
you most holy.

02:24:53.010 --> 02:24:58.050
And as for the perfume which thou shalt make, ye shall not make to yourselves according

02:24:58.050 --> 02:25:04.090
unto the composition thereof, it shall be unto thee holy for the Lord. Whosoever shall

02:25:04.090 --> 02:25:09.070
make like unto that, to smell thereto, shall even be cut off from his people.

02:25:13.350 --> 02:25:20.050
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, See, I have called by name Bezalel the son of Uri,

02:25:20.390 --> 02:25:25.170
the son of Her of the tribe of Judah, and I have filled him with the Spirit of God,

02:25:25.170 --> 02:25:30.250
and in wisdom, and in understanding, and in knowledge, and in all manner of workmanship,

02:25:30.710 --> 02:25:36.490
to devise cunning works, to work in gold, and in silver, and in brass, and in cutting

02:25:36.490 --> 02:25:42.450
of stones, to set them, and in carving of timber, to work in all manner of workmanship.

02:25:43.350 --> 02:25:49.250
And I, behold, I have given with him a Holy Ab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of

02:25:49.250 --> 02:25:55.130
Dan, and in the hearts of all that are wise-hearted I have put wisdom that they may make all that

02:25:55.130 --> 02:26:00.370
I have commanded thee. The tabernacle of the congregation, and the ark of the testimony,

02:26:00.890 --> 02:26:06.030
and the mercy seat that is thereupon, and all the furniture of the tabernacle, and the

02:26:06.030 --> 02:26:12.090
table and his furniture, and the pure candlestick with all his furniture, and the altar of incense,

02:26:12.530 --> 02:26:17.710
and the altar of burnt offering with all his furniture, and the laver and his foot, and

02:26:17.710 --> 02:26:22.570
the cloths of service, and the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of

02:26:22.570 --> 02:26:28.270
his sons to minister in the priest's office, and the anointing oil and sweet incense for

02:26:28.270 --> 02:26:32.810
the holy place, according to all that I have commanded thee, shall they do.

02:26:33.950 --> 02:26:39.870
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, Speak thou also unto the children of Israel, saying,

02:26:40.410 --> 02:26:45.830
Verily my Sabbaths ye shall keep, for it is a sign between me and you throughout your

02:26:45.830 --> 02:26:52.170
generations that ye may know that I am the Lord that doth sanctify you. He shall keep

02:26:52.170 --> 02:26:57.470
the Sabbath therefore, for it is holy unto you. Every one that defile it shall surely

02:26:57.470 --> 02:27:03.550
be put to death, for whosoever doeth any work therein, that soul shall be cut off from among

02:27:03.550 --> 02:27:10.930
his people. Six days may work be done, but in the seventh is the Sabbath of rest, holy

02:27:10.930 --> 02:27:17.110
to the Lord. Whosoever doeth any work in the Sabbath day, he shall surely be put to death.

02:27:17.890 --> 02:27:22.810
Wherefore the children of Israel shall keep the Sabbath to observe the Sabbath throughout

02:27:22.810 --> 02:27:29.070
their generations for a perpetual covenant. It is a sign between me and the children of

02:27:29.070 --> 02:27:35.490
Israel forever, for in six days the Lord made heaven and earth, and on the seventh day he

02:27:35.490 --> 02:27:41.770
rested and was refreshed. And he gave unto Moses, when he had made an end of communing

02:27:41.770 --> 02:27:49.390
with him upon Mount Sinai, two tables of testimony, tables of stone, written with the finger of God.

02:28:21.830 --> 02:28:25.550
And when the people saw that Moses delayed to come down out of the

02:28:25.550 --> 02:28:29.110
mount, the people gathered themselves together unto Aaron, and said

02:28:29.110 --> 02:28:34.010
unto him, Up, make us gods, which shall go before us. For as for this

02:28:34.010 --> 02:28:37.750
Moses, the man that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we want

02:28:37.750 --> 02:28:42.550
not what has become of him. And Aaron said unto them, Break off the

02:28:42.550 --> 02:28:45.890
golden earrings, which are in the ears of your wives, of your sons,

02:28:45.910 --> 02:28:49.970
and of your daughters, and bring them unto me. And all the people

02:28:49.970 --> 02:28:53.210
broke off the golden earrings which were in their ears, and brought

02:28:53.210 --> 02:28:57.990
them unto Aaron. And he received them at their hand, and fashioned it

02:28:57.990 --> 02:29:02.510
with a graving-tool, after he had made it a molten calf. And they

02:29:02.510 --> 02:29:07.010
said, These be thy gods, O Israel, which brought thee up out of the

02:29:07.010 --> 02:29:12.710
land of Egypt. And when Aaron saw it, he built an altar before it, and

02:29:12.710 --> 02:29:17.290
Aaron made proclamation, and said, Tomorrow is a feast to the Lord.

02:29:17.950 --> 02:29:22.010
And they rose up early on the morrow, and offered burnt offerings, and

02:29:22.010 --> 02:29:26.190
brought peace offerings. And the people sat down to eat and to drink,

02:29:26.490 --> 02:29:27.790
and rose up to play.

02:29:29.230 --> 02:29:33.970
And the Lord said unto Moses, Go, get thee down, for thy people which

02:29:33.970 --> 02:29:37.590
thou broughtest out of the land of Egypt have corrupted themselves.

02:29:37.910 --> 02:29:41.590
They have turned aside quickly out of the way which I commanded them.

02:29:41.870 --> 02:29:45.870
They have made them a molten calf, and have worshipped it, and have

02:29:46.170 --> 02:29:50.770
sacrificed thereunto, and said, These be thy gods, O Israel, which have

02:29:50.770 --> 02:29:52.830
brought thee up out of the land of Egypt.

02:29:53.770 --> 02:29:58.150
And the Lord said unto Moses, I have seen this people, and behold, it

02:29:58.150 --> 02:30:02.610
is a stiff-necked people. Now, therefore, let me alone that my wrath

02:30:02.610 --> 02:30:07.330
may wax hot against them, and that I may consume them, and I will make

02:30:07.330 --> 02:30:08.810
of thee a great nation.

02:30:10.030 --> 02:30:15.170
And Moses besought the Lord his God, and said, Lord, why doth thy wrath

02:30:15.170 --> 02:30:19.210
wax hot against thy people which thou hast brought forth out of the

02:30:19.210 --> 02:30:24.230
land of Egypt with great power, and with a mighty hand? Wherefore

02:30:24.230 --> 02:30:28.230
should the Egyptians speak, and say, For mischief did he bring them

02:30:28.230 --> 02:30:31.990
out, to slay them in the mountains, and to consume them from the face

02:30:31.990 --> 02:30:36.710
of the earth? Turn from thy fierce wrath, and repent of this evil

02:30:36.710 --> 02:30:41.730
against thy people. Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, thy servants,

02:30:41.730 --> 02:30:46.710
to whom thou swearst by thine own self, and saidst unto them, I will

02:30:46.710 --> 02:30:50.970
multiply your seed as the stars of heaven, and all this land that I

02:30:50.970 --> 02:30:55.350
have spoken of will I give unto your seed, and they shall inherit it

02:30:55.350 --> 02:30:56.010
for ever.

02:30:57.170 --> 02:31:00.650
And the Lord repented of the evil which he thought to do unto his

02:31:00.650 --> 02:31:01.130
people.

02:31:02.570 --> 02:31:06.490
Then Moses turned and went down from the mount, and the two tables of

02:31:06.490 --> 02:31:10.370
the testimony were in his hand. The tables were written on both their

02:31:10.370 --> 02:31:15.350
sides, on the one side and on the other were they written. And the

02:31:15.350 --> 02:31:19.050
tables were the work of God, and the writing was the writing of God,

02:31:19.270 --> 02:31:23.870
graven upon the tables. And when Joshua heard the noise of the people

02:31:23.870 --> 02:31:28.190
as they shouted, he said unto Moses, There is a noise of war in the

02:31:28.190 --> 02:31:32.410
camp. And he said, It is not the voice of them that shout for

02:31:32.410 --> 02:31:36.610
mastery, neither is it the voice of them that cry for being overcome,

02:31:36.610 --> 02:31:39.750
but the noise of them that sing do I hear.

02:31:40.690 --> 02:31:44.770
And it came to pass, as soon as he came nigh unto the camp, that he

02:31:44.770 --> 02:31:49.830
saw the calf and the dancing, and Moses' anger waxed hot, and he cast

02:31:49.830 --> 02:31:54.730
the tables out of his hands and break them beneath the mount. And he

02:31:54.730 --> 02:31:58.690
took the calf which they had made and burnt it in the fire and ground

02:31:58.690 --> 02:32:02.870
it to powder and strawed it upon the water and made the children of

02:32:02.870 --> 02:32:04.470
Israel drink of it.

02:32:05.910 --> 02:32:10.230
And Moses said unto Aaron, What did this people unto thee that thou

02:32:10.230 --> 02:32:15.230
hast brought so great a sin upon them? And Aaron said, Let not the

02:32:15.230 --> 02:32:19.270
anger of my Lord wax hot. Thou knowest the people that they are set

02:32:19.270 --> 02:32:23.470
on mischief. For they said unto me, Make us gods which shall go

02:32:23.470 --> 02:32:27.170
before us, for as for this Moses, the man that brought us up out of

02:32:27.170 --> 02:32:31.570
the land of Egypt, we want not what has become of him. And I said

02:32:31.570 --> 02:32:36.010
unto them, Whosoever hath any gold, let them break it off. So they

02:32:36.010 --> 02:32:40.310
gave it me. Then I cast it into the fire, and there came out this

02:32:40.310 --> 02:32:40.670
calf.

02:32:42.090 --> 02:32:45.510
And when Moses saw that the people were naked, for Aaron had made

02:32:45.510 --> 02:32:49.950
them naked unto their shame among their enemies, then Moses stood in

02:32:49.950 --> 02:32:54.430
the cate of the camp and said, Who is on the Lord's side? Let him come

02:32:54.430 --> 02:32:59.010
unto me. And all the sons of Levi gathered themselves together unto

02:32:59.010 --> 02:33:04.010
him. And he said unto them, Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Put

02:33:04.010 --> 02:33:08.390
every man his sword by his side, and go in and out from gate to gate

02:33:08.390 --> 02:33:12.590
throughout the camp, and slay every man his brother, and every man his

02:33:12.590 --> 02:33:14.950
companion, and every man his neighbor.

02:33:16.130 --> 02:33:20.010
And the children of Levi did according to the word of Moses, and

02:33:20.010 --> 02:33:24.810
there fell of the people that day about three thousand men. For Moses

02:33:24.810 --> 02:33:29.110
had said, Consecrate yourselves today to the Lord even every man

02:33:29.110 --> 02:33:33.470
upon his son and upon his brother, that he may bestow upon you a

02:33:33.470 --> 02:33:34.690
blessing this day.

02:33:35.870 --> 02:33:40.010
And it came to pass on the morrow that Moses said unto the people, Ye

02:33:40.010 --> 02:33:44.930
have sinned a great sin, and now I will go up unto the Lord. Per

02:33:44.930 --> 02:33:47.650
adventure I shall make an atonement for your sin.

02:33:48.610 --> 02:33:53.070
And Moses returned unto the Lord, and said, O this people have sinned

02:33:53.070 --> 02:33:58.070
a great sin, and have made them gods of gold. Yet now if thou wilt

02:33:58.070 --> 02:34:03.130
forgive their sin, and if not blot me, I pray thee, out of thy book

02:34:03.130 --> 02:34:04.310
which thou hast written.

02:34:05.330 --> 02:34:09.910
And the Lord said unto Moses, Whosoever hath sinned against me, him

02:34:09.910 --> 02:34:14.810
will I blot out of my book. Therefore now go, lead the people unto

02:34:14.810 --> 02:34:19.370
the place of which I have spoken unto thee. Behold, mine angel shall

02:34:19.370 --> 02:34:23.970
go before thee. Nevertheless, in the day when I visit, I will visit

02:34:23.970 --> 02:34:25.330
their sin upon them.

02:34:26.330 --> 02:34:29.830
And the Lord plagued the people, because they made the calf which

02:34:29.830 --> 02:34:30.790
Aaron made.

02:34:34.250 --> 02:34:38.830
And the Lord said unto Moses, Depart, and go up hence, thou and the

02:34:38.830 --> 02:34:42.650
people which thou hast brought up out of the land of Egypt, unto the

02:34:42.650 --> 02:34:47.770
land which I swear unto Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, saying, unto

02:34:47.770 --> 02:34:52.490
thy seed will I give it. And I will send an angel before thee, and I

02:34:52.490 --> 02:34:56.790
will drive out the Canaanite, the Amorite, and the Hittite, and the

02:34:56.790 --> 02:35:01.750
Perizzite, the Hibite, and the Jebusite, unto a land flowing with milk

02:35:01.750 --> 02:35:06.110
and honey. For I will not go up in the midst of thee, for thou art a

02:35:06.110 --> 02:35:09.610
stiff-necked people, lest I consume thee in the way.

02:35:10.570 --> 02:35:14.990
And when the people heard these evil tidings, they mourned, and no man

02:35:14.990 --> 02:35:20.150
did put on him his ornaments. For the Lord had said unto Moses, Say unto

02:35:20.150 --> 02:35:24.470
the children of Israel, Ye are a stiff-necked people, I will come up

02:35:24.470 --> 02:35:28.950
into the midst of thee in a moment, and consume thee. Therefore now put

02:35:28.950 --> 02:35:33.150
off thy ornaments from thee, that I may know what to do unto thee.

02:35:34.050 --> 02:35:37.630
And the children of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments by

02:35:37.630 --> 02:35:42.450
the Mount Horeb. And Moses took the tabernacle, and pitched it without

02:35:42.450 --> 02:35:46.970
the camp, afar off from the camp, and called it the tabernacle of the

02:35:46.970 --> 02:35:51.410
congregation. And it came to pass that every one which sought the Lord

02:35:51.410 --> 02:35:55.570
went out unto the tabernacle of the congregation, which was without the

02:35:55.570 --> 02:36:00.670
camp. And it came to pass when Moses went out unto the tabernacle that

02:36:00.670 --> 02:36:05.150
all the people rose up, and stood every man at his tent-door, and looked

02:36:05.150 --> 02:36:10.990
after Moses until he was gone into the tabernacle. And it came to pass

02:36:10.990 --> 02:36:15.470
as Moses entered into the tabernacle the cloudy pillar descended and

02:36:15.470 --> 02:36:21.230
stood at the door of the tabernacle, and the Lord talked with Moses. And

02:36:21.230 --> 02:36:25.490
all the people saw the cloudy pillar stand at the tabernacle door, and

02:36:25.490 --> 02:36:31.230
all the people rose up and worshipped every man in his tent-door. And the

02:36:31.230 --> 02:36:35.590
Lord spake unto Moses face to face as a man speaketh unto his friend.

02:36:36.210 --> 02:36:40.430
And he turned again into the camp, but his servant Joshua, the son of

02:36:40.430 --> 02:36:44.230
John, a young man, departed not out of the tabernacle.

02:36:45.450 --> 02:36:49.990
And Moses said unto the Lord, See, thou sayest unto me, Bring up this

02:36:49.990 --> 02:36:55.030
people, and thou hast not let me know whom thou wilt send with me. Yet

02:36:55.030 --> 02:36:59.450
thou hast said, I know thee by name, and thou hast also found grace in

02:36:59.450 --> 02:37:04.770
my sight. Now therefore I pray thee, if I have found grace in thy sight,

02:37:05.170 --> 02:37:09.690
show me now thy way, that I may know thee, that I may find grace in

02:37:09.690 --> 02:37:14.950
thy sight, and consider that this nation is thy people. And he said,

02:37:15.350 --> 02:37:20.210
My presence shall go with thee, and I will give thee rest. And he said

02:37:20.210 --> 02:37:25.870
unto him, If thy presence go not with me, carryest not a pence. For

02:37:25.870 --> 02:37:29.950
wherein shall it be known here that I and thy people have found grace

02:37:29.950 --> 02:37:35.270
in thy sight? Is it not in that thou goest with us? So shall we be

02:37:35.270 --> 02:37:39.450
separated, I and thy people, from all the people that are upon the face

02:37:39.450 --> 02:37:44.630
of the earth. And the Lord said unto Moses, I will do this thing also

02:37:44.630 --> 02:37:49.210
that thou hast spoken, for thou hast found grace in my sight, and I

02:37:49.210 --> 02:37:56.470
know thee by name. And he said, I beseech thee, show me thy glory. And

02:37:56.470 --> 02:38:00.750
he said, I will make all my goodness pass before thee, and I will

02:38:00.750 --> 02:38:04.930
proclaim the name of the Lord before thee, and will be gracious to whom

02:38:04.930 --> 02:38:09.150
I will be gracious, and will show mercy on whom I will show mercy.

02:38:10.110 --> 02:38:15.330
And he said, thou canst not see my face, for there shall no man see me

02:38:15.330 --> 02:38:20.670
and live. And the Lord said, Behold, there is a place by me, and thou

02:38:20.670 --> 02:38:24.810
shalt stand upon a rock, and it shall come to pass, while my glory

02:38:24.810 --> 02:38:29.310
passeth by, that I will put thee in a clift of the rock, and will cover

02:38:29.310 --> 02:38:34.310
thee with my hand while I pass by, and I will take away mine hand, and

02:38:34.310 --> 02:38:38.490
thou shalt see my back parts, but my face shall not be seen.

02:38:40.170 --> 02:38:44.930
And the Lord said unto Moses, Hew thee two

02:38:44.930 --> 02:38:48.990
tables of stone like unto the first, and I will write upon these

02:38:48.990 --> 02:38:54.010
tables the words that were in the first tables which thou breakest. And

02:38:54.010 --> 02:38:57.970
be ready in the morning, and come up in the morning unto Mount Sinai,

02:38:58.250 --> 02:39:02.670
and present thyself there to me in the top of the mount. And no man

02:39:02.670 --> 02:39:06.370
shall come up with thee, neither let any man be seen throughout all

02:39:06.370 --> 02:39:10.670
the mount, neither let the flocks nor herds feed before that mount.

02:39:11.870 --> 02:39:16.770
And he hewed two tables of stone like unto the first, and Moses rose

02:39:16.770 --> 02:39:21.330
up early in the morning, and went up unto Mount Sinai as the Lord had

02:39:21.330 --> 02:39:26.970
commanded him, and took in his hand the two tables of stone. And the

02:39:26.970 --> 02:39:30.790
Lord descended in the cloud, and stood with him there, and proclaimed

02:39:30.790 --> 02:39:35.890
the name of the Lord. And the Lord passed by before him, and proclaimed,

02:39:36.250 --> 02:39:41.390
The Lord, the Lord God, merciful and gracious, long-suffering and

02:39:41.390 --> 02:39:46.390
abundant in goodness and truth, keeping mercy for thousands, forgiving

02:39:46.390 --> 02:39:51.410
iniquity and transgression and sin, and that will by no means clear the

02:39:51.410 --> 02:39:56.210
guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children, and

02:39:56.210 --> 02:40:00.950
the children's children unto the third and to the fourth generation.

02:40:02.650 --> 02:40:06.890
And Moses made haste and bowed his head toward the earth and worshipped,

02:40:07.490 --> 02:40:12.390
and he said, If now I have found grace in thy sight, O Lord, let my

02:40:12.390 --> 02:40:17.110
Lord, I pray thee, go among us, for it is a stiff-necked people, and

02:40:17.110 --> 02:40:21.430
pardon our iniquity and our sin, and take us for thine inheritance.

02:40:22.510 --> 02:40:27.910
And he said, Behold, I make a covenant, before all thy people I will do

02:40:27.910 --> 02:40:32.550
marvels such as have not been done in all the earth nor in any nation,

02:40:33.150 --> 02:40:37.270
and all the people among which thou art shall see the work of the Lord,

02:40:37.630 --> 02:40:42.550
for it is a terrible thing that I will do with thee. Observe thou that

02:40:42.550 --> 02:40:47.330
which I command thee this day, behold, I drive out before thee the

02:40:47.330 --> 02:40:51.250
the Samarite, and the Canaanite, and the Hittite, and the Perizzite,

02:40:51.350 --> 02:40:53.550
and the Hivite, and the Jebusite.

02:40:54.550 --> 02:40:58.370
Take heed to thyself, lest thou make a covenant with the inhabitants

02:40:58.370 --> 02:41:03.110
of the land whither thou goest, lest it be for a snare in the midst of

02:41:03.110 --> 02:41:07.510
thee. But ye shall destroy their altars, break their images, and cut

02:41:07.510 --> 02:41:12.570
down their groves, for thou shalt worship no other God, for the Lord

02:41:12.570 --> 02:41:17.550
whose name is Jealous is a Jealous God, lest thou make a covenant with

02:41:17.550 --> 02:41:21.590
the inhabitants of the land, and they go a-whoring after their gods,

02:41:21.990 --> 02:41:26.470
and do sacrifice unto their gods, and one call thee, and thou eat his

02:41:26.470 --> 02:41:31.150
sacrifice, and thou take of their daughters unto thy sons, and their

02:41:31.150 --> 02:41:35.650
daughters go a-whoring after their gods, and make thy sons go a-whoring

02:41:35.650 --> 02:41:40.650
after their gods. Thou shalt make thee no molten gods.

02:41:42.190 --> 02:41:46.950
The feast of unleavened bread shalt thou keep. Seven days thou shalt eat

02:41:46.950 --> 02:41:50.990
unleavened bread, as I commanded thee in the time of the month Abib,

02:41:51.410 --> 02:41:56.790
for in the month Abib thou camest out from Egypt. All that openeth the

02:41:56.790 --> 02:42:01.130
matrix is mine, and every firstling among thy cattle, whether ox or

02:42:01.130 --> 02:42:06.110
sheep, that is male. But the firstling of an ass thou shalt redeem with

02:42:06.110 --> 02:42:11.410
a lamb, and if thou redeem him not, then thou shalt break his neck. All

02:42:11.410 --> 02:42:15.590
the firstborn of thy sons thou shalt redeem, and none shall appear

02:42:15.590 --> 02:42:21.730
before me empty. Six days thou shalt labor, but on the seventh day

02:42:21.730 --> 02:42:27.730
thou shalt rest, in earring-time and in harvest thou shalt rest. And

02:42:27.730 --> 02:42:31.330
thou shalt observe the feast of weeks of the firstfruits of wheat

02:42:31.330 --> 02:42:36.750
harvest, and the feast of ingathering at the year's end. Thrice in the

02:42:36.750 --> 02:42:40.830
year shall all your men-children appear before the Lord God, the God

02:42:40.830 --> 02:42:45.870
of Israel. For I will cast out the nations before thee, and enlarge

02:42:45.870 --> 02:42:50.590
thy borders. Neither shall any man desire thy land, when thou shalt go

02:42:50.590 --> 02:42:55.970
up to appear before the Lord thy God thrice in the year. Thou shalt not

02:42:55.970 --> 02:43:00.490
offer the blood of my sacrifice with leaven. Neither shall the sacrifice

02:43:00.490 --> 02:43:05.770
of the feast of the Passover be left unto the morning. The first of the

02:43:05.770 --> 02:43:09.450
firstfruits of thy land thou shalt bring unto the house of the Lord thy

02:43:09.450 --> 02:43:13.390
God. Thou shalt not see the kid in his mother's milk.

02:43:14.190 --> 02:43:18.610
And the Lord said unto Moses, Write thou these words, for after the

02:43:18.610 --> 02:43:22.590
tenor of these words I have made a covenant with thee and with Israel.

02:43:23.270 --> 02:43:27.610
And he was there with the Lord forty days and forty nights. He did

02:43:27.610 --> 02:43:32.210
neither eat bread nor drink water. And he wrote upon the tables the

02:43:32.210 --> 02:43:37.550
words of the covenant the Ten Commandments. And it came to pass when

02:43:37.550 --> 02:43:41.550
Moses came down from Mount Sinai with the two tables of testimony in

02:43:41.550 --> 02:43:46.170
Moses's hand, when he came down from the mount, that Moses whist not

02:43:46.170 --> 02:43:50.950
that the skin of his face shone while he talked with him. And when

02:43:50.950 --> 02:43:55.310
Aaron and all the children of Israel saw Moses, behold, the skin of

02:43:55.310 --> 02:44:00.810
his face shone, and they were afraid to come nigh him. And Moses

02:44:00.810 --> 02:44:04.370
called unto them, and Aaron and all the rulers of the congregation

02:44:04.370 --> 02:44:09.470
returned unto him, and Moses talked with them. And afterward all the

02:44:09.470 --> 02:44:13.930
children of Israel came nigh, and he gave them in commandment all that

02:44:13.930 --> 02:44:18.990
the Lord had spoken with him in Mount Sinai. Until Moses had done

02:44:18.990 --> 02:44:23.870
speaking with them, he put a veil on his face. But when Moses went in

02:44:23.870 --> 02:44:27.870
for the Lord to speak with him, he took the veil off until he came

02:44:27.870 --> 02:44:32.250
out. And he came out and spake unto the children of Israel that which

02:44:32.250 --> 02:44:36.890
he was commanded. And the children of Israel saw the face of Moses

02:44:36.890 --> 02:44:41.870
that the skin of Moses's face shone. And Moses put the veil upon his

02:44:41.870 --> 02:44:44.810
face again until he went in to speak with him.

02:44:48.900 --> 02:44:52.270
And Moses gathered all the congregation of the children of Israel

02:44:52.270 --> 02:44:56.390
together, and said unto them, These are the words which the Lord hath

02:44:56.390 --> 02:45:01.770
commanded that ye should do them. Six days shall work be done, but on

02:45:01.770 --> 02:45:06.250
the seventh day there shall be to you an holy day, a Sabbath of rest

02:45:06.250 --> 02:45:11.950
to the Lord. Whosoever doeth work therein shall be put to death. Ye

02:45:11.950 --> 02:45:16.170
shall kindle no fire throughout your habitations upon the Sabbath day.

02:45:17.590 --> 02:45:21.330
And Moses spake unto all the congregation of the children of Israel,

02:45:21.330 --> 02:45:26.270
saying, This is the thing which the Lord commanded, saying, Take ye from

02:45:26.270 --> 02:45:30.910
among you an offering unto the Lord. Whosoever is of a willing heart,

02:45:31.230 --> 02:45:36.190
let him bring it, an offering of the Lord. Gold and silver and brass

02:45:36.190 --> 02:45:41.910
and blue and purple and scarlet and fine linen and goat's hair and

02:45:41.910 --> 02:45:47.510
ram's skins dyed red and badger's skins and shittim wood and oil for

02:45:47.510 --> 02:45:52.950
light and spices for anointing oil and for the sweet incense and onyx

02:45:52.950 --> 02:45:57.990
stones and stones to be set for the ephod and for the breastplate. And

02:45:57.990 --> 02:46:01.970
every wise heart that among you shall come and make all that the Lord

02:46:01.970 --> 02:46:07.210
hath commanded, the tabernacle, his tent and his covering, his tashes

02:46:07.210 --> 02:46:12.970
and his boards, his bars, his pillars and his sockets, the ark and the

02:46:12.970 --> 02:46:17.410
staves thereof with the mercy seat and the veil of the covering, the

02:46:17.410 --> 02:46:21.930
table and his staves and all his vessels and the showbread, the

02:46:21.930 --> 02:46:26.390
candlestick also for the light and his furniture and his lamps with

02:46:26.390 --> 02:46:30.830
the oil for the light, and the incense altar and his staves and the

02:46:30.830 --> 02:46:35.370
anointing oil and the sweet incense and the hanging for the door at the

02:46:35.370 --> 02:46:39.610
entering inn of the tabernacle, the altar of burnt offering with his

02:46:39.610 --> 02:46:45.790
and all his vessels, the laver and his foot, the hangings for the

02:46:45.790 --> 02:46:49.990
court, his pillars and their sockets, and the hanging for the door of

02:46:49.990 --> 02:46:54.330
the court, the pins of the tabernacle and the pins of the court and

02:46:54.330 --> 02:46:59.910
their cords, the cloths of service to do service in the holy place, the

02:46:59.910 --> 02:47:03.890
holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons to

02:47:03.890 --> 02:47:05.790
minister in the priest's office.

02:47:06.790 --> 02:47:10.570
And all the congregation of the children of Israel departed from the

02:47:10.570 --> 02:47:15.910
presence of Moses. And they came, every one whose heart stirred him

02:47:15.910 --> 02:47:19.890
up, and every one whom his spirit made willing, and they brought the

02:47:19.890 --> 02:47:23.950
Lord's offering to the work of the tabernacle of the congregation and

02:47:23.950 --> 02:47:28.910
for all his service and for the holy garments. And they came, both men

02:47:28.910 --> 02:47:32.890
and women, as many as were willing-hearted, and brought bracelets and

02:47:32.890 --> 02:47:38.410
earrings and rings and tablets, all jewels of gold, and every man that

02:47:38.410 --> 02:47:43.550
offered offered an offering of gold unto the Lord. And every man with

02:47:43.550 --> 02:47:47.950
whom was found blue and purple and scarlet and fine linen and goats'

02:47:48.130 --> 02:47:54.090
hair and red skins of rams and badger's skins brought them. Everyone

02:47:54.090 --> 02:47:57.810
that did offer an offering of silver and brass brought the Lord's

02:47:57.810 --> 02:48:01.890
offering, and every man with whom was found shittim wood for any work

02:48:01.890 --> 02:48:06.510
of the service brought it. And all the women that were wise-hearted

02:48:06.510 --> 02:48:10.670
did spin with their hands and brought that which they had spun, both

02:48:10.670 --> 02:48:15.930
of blue and of purple and of scarlet and of fine linen. And all the

02:48:15.930 --> 02:48:21.290
women whose hearts stirred them up in wisdom spun goats' hair. And the

02:48:21.290 --> 02:48:25.550
rulers brought onyx stones and stones to be set for the ephod and for

02:48:25.550 --> 02:48:30.130
the breastplate, and spice and oil for the light and for the anointing

02:48:30.130 --> 02:48:35.030
oil, and for the sweet incense. The children of Israel brought a

02:48:35.030 --> 02:48:39.390
willing offering unto the Lord, every man and woman whose heart made

02:48:39.390 --> 02:48:43.010
them willing to bring for all manner of work which the Lord had

02:48:43.010 --> 02:48:45.650
commanded to be made by the hand of Moses.

02:48:47.130 --> 02:48:51.350
And Moses said unto the children of Israel, See, the Lord hath called

02:48:51.350 --> 02:48:56.310
by name Bezalel the son of Uriah the son of Her of the tribe of Judah,

02:48:56.870 --> 02:49:00.930
and he hath filled him with the Spirit of God in wisdom, in understanding

02:49:00.930 --> 02:49:05.650
and in knowledge, and in all manner of workmanship, and to devise

02:49:05.650 --> 02:49:10.950
curious works, to work in gold and in silver and in brass, and in the

02:49:10.950 --> 02:49:15.750
cutting of stones, to set them, and in carving of wood, to make any

02:49:15.750 --> 02:49:20.690
manner of cunning work. And he hath put in his heart that he may teach

02:49:20.690 --> 02:49:27.230
both he and Aholiab the son of Hisamach of the tribe of Dan. Them hath

02:49:27.230 --> 02:49:31.690
he filled with wisdom of heart to work all manner of work, of the

02:49:31.690 --> 02:49:36.010
engraver and of the cunning workman, and of the embroiderer, and blue

02:49:36.010 --> 02:49:40.830
and in purple, and in scarlet and in fine linen, and of the weaver,

02:49:40.990 --> 02:49:45.690
even of them that do any work, and of those that devise cunning work.

02:49:51.090 --> 02:50:05.110
The Lord hath called by name Bezalel the son of Her of the tribe of Judah,

02:50:38.390 --> 02:50:44.590
Then wrought Bezalel and Aholiab, and every wise-hearted man, in whom the Lord put wisdom

02:50:44.590 --> 02:50:49.870
and understanding to know how to work all manner of work for the service of the sanctuary,

02:50:50.350 --> 02:50:52.550
according to all that the Lord had commanded.

02:50:53.330 --> 02:50:59.090
And Moses called Bezalel and Aholiab, and every wise-hearted man, in whose heart the

02:50:59.090 --> 02:51:04.170
Lord had put wisdom, even every one whose heart stirred him up to come unto the work

02:51:04.170 --> 02:51:04.990
to do it.

02:51:05.430 --> 02:51:10.050
And they received of Moses all the offering which the children of Israel had brought for

02:51:10.050 --> 02:51:13.610
the work of the service of the sanctuary to make it withal.

02:51:14.330 --> 02:51:17.590
And they brought yet unto him free offerings every morning.

02:51:18.350 --> 02:51:23.130
And all the wise men that wrought all the work of the sanctuary came every man from

02:51:23.130 --> 02:51:24.530
his work which they made.

02:51:25.150 --> 02:51:30.410
And they spake unto Moses, saying, The people bring much more than enough for the service

02:51:30.410 --> 02:51:33.250
of the work which the Lord commanded to make.

02:51:34.290 --> 02:51:39.150
And Moses gave commandment, and they caused it to be proclaimed throughout the cap, saying,

02:51:39.610 --> 02:51:43.990
Let neither man nor woman make any more work for the offering of the sanctuary.

02:51:44.650 --> 02:51:49.630
So the people were restrained from bringing, for the stuff they had was sufficient for

02:51:49.630 --> 02:51:52.350
all the work to make it, and too much.

02:51:53.550 --> 02:51:58.590
And every wise-hearted man among them that wrought the work of the tabernacle made ten

02:51:58.590 --> 02:52:04.850
curtains of fine twine linen, and blue, and purple, and scarlet, with cherubims of cunning

02:52:04.850 --> 02:52:06.290
work made he them.

02:52:07.570 --> 02:52:12.530
The length of one curtain was twenty and eight cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four

02:52:12.530 --> 02:52:15.610
The curtains were all of one size.

02:52:16.450 --> 02:52:21.470
And he coupled the five curtains one unto another, and the other five curtains he coupled

02:52:21.470 --> 02:52:22.730
one unto another.

02:52:23.430 --> 02:52:27.810
And he made loops of blue on the edge of one curtain from the selvedge in the coupling,

02:52:28.550 --> 02:52:33.410
likewise he made in the uttermost side of another curtain in the coupling of the second.

02:52:34.470 --> 02:52:39.710
Fifty loops made he in one curtain, and fifty loops made he in the edge of the curtain which

02:52:39.710 --> 02:52:43.970
was in the coupling of the second, the loops held one curtain to another.

02:52:45.070 --> 02:52:50.950
And he made fifty tashes of gold, and coupled the curtains one unto another with the tashes,

02:52:51.390 --> 02:52:53.490
so it became one tabernacle.

02:52:54.750 --> 02:53:00.370
And he made curtains of goat's hair for the tent over the tabernacle, eleven curtains

02:53:00.370 --> 02:53:01.390
he made them.

02:53:02.590 --> 02:53:07.970
The length of one curtain was thirty cubits, and four cubits was the breadth of one curtain,

02:53:08.330 --> 02:53:10.850
the eleven curtains were of one size.

02:53:11.730 --> 02:53:16.130
And he coupled five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves.

02:53:16.790 --> 02:53:21.730
And he made fifty loops upon the uttermost edge of the curtain in the coupling, and fifty

02:53:21.730 --> 02:53:25.190
loops made he upon the edge of the curtain which coupleth the second.

02:53:26.130 --> 02:53:30.970
And he made fifty tashes of brass to couple the tent together, that it might be one.

02:53:31.710 --> 02:53:37.090
And he made a covering for the tent of ram's skins dyed red, and a covering of badger's

02:53:37.090 --> 02:53:38.330
skins above that.

02:53:38.950 --> 02:53:42.730
And he made boards for the tabernacle of shittim wood standing up.

02:53:43.450 --> 02:53:48.550
The length of a board was ten cubits, and the breadth of a board one cubit and a half.

02:53:49.450 --> 02:53:55.050
One board had two tenons equally distant one from another, thus did he make for all the

02:53:55.050 --> 02:53:56.410
boards of the tabernacle.

02:53:57.150 --> 02:54:02.990
And he made boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards for the south side southward, and forty

02:54:02.990 --> 02:54:08.370
sockets of silver he made under the twenty boards, two sockets under one board for his

02:54:08.370 --> 02:54:12.690
two tenons and two sockets under another board for his two tenons.

02:54:13.470 --> 02:54:18.150
And for the other side of the tabernacle which is toward the north corner, he made twenty

02:54:18.150 --> 02:54:24.350
boards, and their forty sockets of silver, two sockets under one board and two sockets

02:54:24.350 --> 02:54:25.510
under another board.

02:54:26.230 --> 02:54:30.030
And for the sides of the tabernacle westward, he made six boards.

02:54:30.030 --> 02:54:36.050
and two boards made he for the corners of the tabernacle in the two sides, and they

02:54:36.050 --> 02:54:41.350
were coupled beneath and coupled together at the head thereof to one ring, thus he did

02:54:41.350 --> 02:54:46.630
to both of them in both the corners. And there were eight boards, and their sockets were

02:54:46.630 --> 02:54:53.410
sixteen sockets of silver under every board two sockets. And he made bars of shittim wood,

02:54:53.810 --> 02:54:58.590
five for the boards of the one side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of

02:54:58.590 --> 02:55:03.490
the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the tabernacle for

02:55:03.490 --> 02:55:09.110
the sides westward. And he made the middle bar to shoot through the boards from the one

02:55:09.110 --> 02:55:14.830
end to the other. And he overlaid the boards with gold, and made their rings of gold to

02:55:14.830 --> 02:55:21.430
be places for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold. And he made a veil of blue and

02:55:21.430 --> 02:55:27.330
purple and scarlet and fine twined linen, with cherubims made he it of cunning work.

02:55:27.330 --> 02:55:33.790
And he made thereunto four pillars of shittim wood, and overlaid them with gold, their hooks

02:55:33.790 --> 02:55:40.110
were of gold, and he cast for them four sockets of silver. And he made an hanging for the

02:55:40.110 --> 02:55:47.170
tabernacle door of blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen of needlework, and the

02:55:47.170 --> 02:55:51.910
five pillars of it with their hooks, and he overlaid their chapiters and their fillets

02:55:51.910 --> 02:55:55.370
with gold, but their five sockets were of brass.

02:55:57.370 --> 02:56:03.710
And Bezalil made the ark of shittim wood. Two cubits and a half was the length

02:56:03.710 --> 02:56:08.350
of it, and a cubit and a half the breadth of it, and a cubit and a half the height of

02:56:08.350 --> 02:56:14.650
it. And he overlaid it with pure gold within and without, and made a crown of gold to it

02:56:14.650 --> 02:56:20.910
round about. And he cast for it four rings of gold to be set by the four corners of it,

02:56:20.910 --> 02:56:27.070
even two rings upon the one side of it and two rings upon the other side of it. And he

02:56:27.070 --> 02:56:32.450
made staves of shittim wood and overlaid them with gold, and he put the staves into the

02:56:32.450 --> 02:56:38.730
rings by the sides of the ark to bear the ark. And he made the mercy seat of pure gold,

02:56:39.070 --> 02:56:44.770
two cubits and a half was the length thereof, and one cubit and a half the breadth thereof.

02:56:45.370 --> 02:56:51.190
And he made two cherubims of gold, beaten out of one piece made he them, on the two

02:56:51.190 --> 02:56:56.770
ends of the mercy seat, one cherub on the end on this side, and another cherub on the

02:56:56.770 --> 02:57:02.810
other end on that side, how to the mercy seat made he the cherubims on the two ends thereof.

02:57:03.650 --> 02:57:08.590
And the cherubims spread out their wings on high and covered with their wings over the

02:57:08.590 --> 02:57:14.090
mercy seat with their faces one to another, even to the mercy seatward were the faces

02:57:14.090 --> 02:57:20.310
of the cherubims. And he made the table of shittim wood, two cubits was the length thereof,

02:57:20.570 --> 02:57:26.050
and a cubit the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height thereof. And he overlaid

02:57:26.050 --> 02:57:32.690
it with pure gold, and made thereunto a crown of gold round about. Also he made thereunto

02:57:32.690 --> 02:57:37.850
a border of an hand breadth round about, and made a crown of gold for the border thereof

02:57:37.850 --> 02:57:44.070
round about. And he cast for it four rings of gold, and put the rings upon the four corners

02:57:44.070 --> 02:57:49.370
that were in the four feet thereof. Over against the border were the rings, the places

02:57:49.370 --> 02:57:55.230
for the staves to bear the table. And he made the staves of shittim wood and overlaid them

02:57:55.230 --> 02:58:01.010
with gold to bear the table. And he made the vessels which were upon the table, his dishes

02:58:01.010 --> 02:58:08.190
and his spoons and his bowls and his covers to cover with all, of pure gold. And he made

02:58:08.190 --> 02:58:13.930
the candlestick of pure gold, of beaten work made he the candlestick, his shaft and his

02:58:13.930 --> 02:58:20.490
branch, his bowls, his knops and his flowers, were of the same. And six branches going out

02:58:20.490 --> 02:58:25.510
of the sides thereof, three branches of the candlestick out of the one side thereof, and

02:58:25.510 --> 02:58:30.850
three branches of the candlestick out of the other side thereof. Three bowls made after

02:58:30.850 --> 02:58:36.690
the fashion of almonds in one branch, a knop and a flower. And three bowls made like almonds

02:58:36.690 --> 02:58:42.530
in another branch, a knop and a flower. So throughout the six branches going out of the

02:58:42.530 --> 02:58:48.750
candlestick. And in the candlestick were four bowls made like almonds, his knops and his

02:58:48.750 --> 02:58:54.010
flowers. And a knop under two branches of the same, and a knop under two branches of

02:58:54.010 --> 02:58:59.430
the same, and a knop under two branches of the same, according to the six branches going

02:58:59.430 --> 02:59:05.070
out of it. Their knops and their branches were of the same. All of it was one beaten

02:59:05.070 --> 02:59:11.770
work of pure gold. And he made his seven lamps and his snuffers and his snuff-dishes of pure

02:59:11.770 --> 02:59:19.550
gold. Of a talent of pure gold made he at all the vessels thereof. And he made the incense

02:59:19.550 --> 02:59:24.970
altar of shittim wood. The length of it was a cubit, and the breadth of it a cubit. It

02:59:24.970 --> 02:59:31.050
was four square, and two cubits was the height of it. The horns thereof were of the same.

02:59:31.810 --> 02:59:37.230
And he overlaid it with pure gold, both the top of it and the sides thereof round about,

02:59:37.230 --> 02:59:44.370
and the horns of it. Also he made unto it a crown of gold round about. And he made two

02:59:44.370 --> 02:59:49.970
rings of gold for it under the crown thereof, by the two corners of it, upon the two sides

02:59:49.970 --> 02:59:55.890
thereof, to be places for the staves to bear it withal. And he made the staves of shittim

02:59:55.890 --> 03:00:02.250
wood and overlaid them with gold. And he made the holy anointing oil and the pure incense

03:00:02.250 --> 03:00:06.090
of sweet spices according to the work of the apothecary.

03:00:07.950 --> 03:00:12.010
And he made the altar of burnt offering of

03:00:12.010 --> 03:00:17.810
shittim wood. Five cubits was the length thereof, and five cubits the breadth thereof. It was

03:00:17.810 --> 03:00:24.130
four square, and three cubits the height thereof. And he made the horns thereof on the four

03:00:24.130 --> 03:00:30.510
corners of it. The horns thereof were of the same. And he overlaid it with brass. And he

03:00:30.510 --> 03:00:35.550
made all the vessels of the altar, the pots and the shovels and the basins and the flesh

03:00:35.550 --> 03:00:42.670
hooks and the firepans, all the vessels thereof made he of brass. And he made for the altar

03:00:42.670 --> 03:00:48.730
a brazen grate of net work under the compass thereof beneath unto the midst of it. And

03:00:48.730 --> 03:00:54.210
he cast four rings for the four ends of the grate of brass to be places for the staves.

03:00:54.810 --> 03:01:00.590
And he made the staves of shittim wood and overlaid them with brass. And he put the staves

03:01:00.590 --> 03:01:06.090
into the rings on the sides of the altar to bear it withal. He made the altar hollow with

03:01:06.090 --> 03:01:12.290
boards. And he made the laver of brass and the foot of it of brass of the looking-glasses

03:01:12.290 --> 03:01:17.010
of the women assembling which assembled at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.

03:01:18.350 --> 03:01:23.870
And he made the court. On the south side southward the hangings of the court were of fine twine

03:01:23.870 --> 03:01:30.130
linen and a hundred cubits. Their pillars were 20 and their brazen sockets 20. The hooks

03:01:30.130 --> 03:01:35.670
of the pillars and their fillets were of silver. And for the north side the hangings were a

03:01:35.670 --> 03:01:41.550
hundred cubits. Their pillars were 20 and their sockets of brass 20. The hooks of the

03:01:41.550 --> 03:01:47.650
pillars and their fillets of silver. And for the west side were hangings of 50 cubits,

03:01:47.650 --> 03:01:52.590
their pillars ten, and their sockets ten, the hooks of the pillars and their fillets

03:01:52.590 --> 03:01:59.010
of silver, and for the east side eastward fifty cubits. The hangings of the one side

03:01:59.010 --> 03:02:04.730
of the gate were fifteen cubits, their pillars three, and their sockets three, and for the

03:02:04.730 --> 03:02:09.550
other side of the court gate on this hand and on that hand were hangings of fifteen

03:02:09.550 --> 03:02:15.690
cubits, their pillars three, and their sockets three. All the hangings of the court round

03:02:15.690 --> 03:02:21.710
about were of fine twined linen, and the sockets for the pillars were of brass, the hooks of

03:02:21.710 --> 03:02:26.810
the pillars and their fillets of silver, and the overlaying of their chapiters of silver,

03:02:27.250 --> 03:02:32.730
and all the pillars of the court were filleted with silver. And the hanging for the gate

03:02:32.730 --> 03:02:39.650
of the court was needlework of blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen, and twenty

03:02:39.650 --> 03:02:44.390
cubits was the length, and the height and the breadth was five cubits answerable to

03:02:44.390 --> 03:02:49.990
the hangings of the court. And their pillars were four, and their sockets of brass four,

03:02:50.330 --> 03:02:55.250
their hooks of silver, and the overlaying of their chapiters and their fillets of silver.

03:02:55.770 --> 03:03:00.650
And all the pins of the tabernacle and of the court round about were of brass.

03:03:01.810 --> 03:03:07.290
This is the sum of the tabernacle even of the tabernacle of testimony as it was counted

03:03:07.290 --> 03:03:12.290
according to the commandment of Moses for the service of the Levites by the hand of

03:03:12.950 --> 03:03:19.650
son to Aaron the priest. And Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Her, of the tribe of Judah,

03:03:19.910 --> 03:03:26.070
made all that the Lord commanded Moses. And with him was a holy Ab, son of Ahisamach,

03:03:26.410 --> 03:03:32.170
of the tribe of Dan, an engraver and a cunning workman, and an embroiderer in blue and in

03:03:32.170 --> 03:03:38.630
purple and in scarlet and fine linen. All the gold that was occupied for the work and

03:03:38.630 --> 03:03:44.110
all the work of the holy place, even the gold of the offering, was twenty and nine talents

03:03:44.110 --> 03:03:50.310
and seven hundred and thirty shekels after the shekel of the sanctuary. And the silver

03:03:50.310 --> 03:03:55.090
of them that were numbered of the congregation was an hundred talents and a thousand seven

03:03:55.090 --> 03:04:01.190
hundred and three score and fifteen shekels after the shekel of the sanctuary. A becca

03:04:01.190 --> 03:04:06.630
for every man, that is, half a shekel after the shekel of the sanctuary, for every one

03:04:06.630 --> 03:04:11.590
that went to be numbered, from twenty years old and upward, for six hundred thousand

03:04:11.590 --> 03:04:17.450
and three thousand and five hundred and fifty men. And of the hundred talents of silver

03:04:17.450 --> 03:04:22.870
were cast the sockets of the sanctuary and the sockets of the veil, and hundred sockets

03:04:22.870 --> 03:04:28.910
of the hundred talents a talent for a socket. And of the thousand seven hundred seventy

03:04:28.910 --> 03:04:33.970
and five shekels he made hooks for the pillars and overlaid their chapiters and filleted

03:04:33.970 --> 03:04:39.570
them. And the brass of the offering was seventy talents and two thousand and four hundred

03:04:39.570 --> 03:04:45.030
shekels. And therewith he made the sockets to the door of the tabernacle of the congregation

03:04:45.030 --> 03:04:51.150
and the brazen altar and the brazen grate for it and all the vessels of the altar, and

03:04:51.150 --> 03:04:56.030
the sockets of the court round about and the sockets of the court-gate and all the pins

03:04:56.030 --> 03:04:59.730
of the tabernacle and all the pins of the court round about.

03:05:02.210 --> 03:05:06.450
And of the blue and purple and scarlet they

03:05:06.450 --> 03:05:11.870
made cloths of service to do service in the holy place and made the holy garments for

03:05:11.870 --> 03:05:18.250
Aaron as the Lord commanded Moses. And he made the ephod of gold, blue and purple and

03:05:18.250 --> 03:05:24.250
scarlet and fine twined linen. And they did beat the gold into thin plates and cut it

03:05:24.250 --> 03:05:29.650
into wires to work it in the blue and in the purple and in the scarlet and in the fine

03:05:29.650 --> 03:05:36.650
linen with cunning work. They made shoulder-pieces for it to couple it together, by the two edges

03:05:36.650 --> 03:05:42.590
was it coupled together. And the curious girdle of his ephod that was upon it was of the same,

03:05:42.830 --> 03:05:49.030
according to the work thereof, of gold, blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen

03:05:49.030 --> 03:05:56.230
as the Lord commanded Moses. And they wrought onyx stones enclosed in ooshes of gold graven

03:05:56.230 --> 03:06:02.090
as signets are graven with the names of the children of Israel. And he put them on the

03:06:02.090 --> 03:06:06.870
shoulders of the ephod that they should be stones for a memorial to the children of Israel

03:06:06.870 --> 03:06:12.550
as the Lord commanded Moses. And he made the breast-plate of cunning work like the work

03:06:12.550 --> 03:06:19.710
of the ephod of gold, blue and purple and scarlet and fine twined linen. It was four

03:06:19.710 --> 03:06:24.970
square they made the breast-plate double, a span was the length thereof and a span the

03:06:24.970 --> 03:06:31.410
length thereof being doubled. And they set in at four rows of stones. The first row was

03:06:31.410 --> 03:06:37.750
a sardius, a topaz and a carbuncle. This was the first row. And the second row an emerald,

03:06:37.930 --> 03:06:44.930
a sapphire and a diamond. And the third row a ligure, an agate and an amethyst. And the

03:06:44.930 --> 03:06:51.390
fourth row a burl, an onyx and a jasper. They were enclosed in ooshes of gold in their enclosings.

03:06:51.950 --> 03:06:56.850
And the stones were according to the names of the children of Israel, twelve, according

03:06:56.850 --> 03:07:02.130
to their names, like the engravings of a signet, every one with his name, according to the

03:07:02.130 --> 03:07:08.430
twelve tribes. And they made upon the breast-plate chains at the ends of wreathen work of pure

03:07:08.430 --> 03:07:14.730
gold. And they made two ooshes of gold and two gold rings and put the two rings in the

03:07:14.730 --> 03:07:19.530
two ends of the breast-plate. And they put the two wreathen chains of gold in the two

03:07:19.530 --> 03:07:24.730
rings on the ends of the breast-plate. And the two ends of the two wreathen chains they

03:07:24.730 --> 03:07:30.010
fastened in the two ooshes and put them on the shoulder-pieces of the ephod before it.

03:07:30.730 --> 03:07:35.670
And they made two rings of gold and put them on the two ends of the breast-plate upon the

03:07:35.670 --> 03:07:41.090
border of it which was on the side of the ephod inward. And they made two other golden

03:07:41.090 --> 03:07:46.450
rings and put them on the two sides of the ephod underneath toward the fore-part of it

03:07:46.450 --> 03:07:52.750
over against the other coupling thereof above the curious girdle of the ephod. And they

03:07:52.750 --> 03:07:57.290
did bind the breast-plate by his rings under the rings of the ephod with a lace of blue

03:07:57.290 --> 03:08:02.250
that it might be above the curious girdle of the ephod and that the breast-plate might

03:08:02.250 --> 03:08:08.930
not be loosed from the ephod as the Lord commanded Moses. And he made the robe of the ephod of

03:08:08.930 --> 03:08:14.870
woven work all of blue. And there was a hole in the midst of the robe as the hole of an

03:08:14.870 --> 03:08:20.290
ephod was a virgin with a band round about the hole that it should not rend. And they

03:08:20.290 --> 03:08:25.870
made upon the hems of the robe pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet and twined

03:08:25.870 --> 03:08:31.810
linen. And they made bells of pure gold and put the bells between the pomegranates upon

03:08:31.810 --> 03:08:37.470
the hem of the robe round about between the pomegranates, a bell and a pomegranate, a

03:08:37.470 --> 03:08:43.350
bell and a pomegranate round about the hem of the robe to minister in as the Lord commanded

03:08:43.350 --> 03:08:50.250
Moses. And they made coats of fine linen of woven work for Aaron and for his sons and

03:08:50.250 --> 03:08:55.970
a mitre of fine linen and goodly bonnets of fine linen and linen breeches of fine twined

03:08:55.970 --> 03:09:02.030
linen and a girdle of fine twined linen and blue and purple and scarlet of needlework

03:09:02.030 --> 03:09:08.850
as the Lord commanded Moses. And they made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold and

03:09:08.850 --> 03:09:16.010
wrote upon it a writing like to the engravings of a signet, Holiness to the Lord. And they

03:09:16.010 --> 03:09:21.550
tied unto it a lace of blue to fasten it on high upon the mitre as the Lord commanded

03:09:21.550 --> 03:09:28.150
Moses. Thus was all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of the congregation finished and

03:09:28.150 --> 03:09:33.350
the children of Israel did according to all that the Lord commanded Moses, so did they.

03:09:34.130 --> 03:09:39.290
And they brought the tabernacle unto Moses, the tent and all his furniture, his tashes,

03:09:39.410 --> 03:09:44.890
his boards, his bars, and his pillars, and his sockets. And the covering of ram skins

03:09:44.890 --> 03:09:50.430
dyed red, and the covering of badger's skins, and the veil of the covering, the ark of the

03:09:50.430 --> 03:09:56.010
testimony and the staves thereof and the mercy seat, the table and all the vessels thereof

03:09:56.010 --> 03:10:01.750
and the showbread, the pure candlestick with the lamps thereof even with the lamps to be

03:10:01.750 --> 03:10:07.530
set in order and all the vessels thereof and the oil for light and the golden altar and

03:10:07.530 --> 03:10:13.290
the anointing oil and the sweet incense and the hanging for the tabernacle door, the brazen

03:10:13.290 --> 03:10:19.750
altar and his grate of brass, his staves and all his vessels, the laver and his foot, the

03:10:19.750 --> 03:10:24.290
hangings of the court, his pillars and his sockets, and the hanging for the court-gate,

03:10:24.430 --> 03:10:29.750
his cords and his pins, and all the vessels of the service of the tabernacle for the tent

03:10:29.750 --> 03:10:35.330
of the congregation, the cloths of service to do service in the holy place, and the holy

03:10:35.330 --> 03:10:40.690
garments for Aaron the priest and his son's garments to minister in the priest's office.

03:10:41.450 --> 03:10:47.210
According to all that the Lord commanded Moses, so the children of Israel made all the work.

03:10:47.850 --> 03:10:53.150
And Moses did look upon all the work, and behold, they had done it as the Lord had commanded.

03:10:53.570 --> 03:10:57.110
Even so had they done it, and Moses blessed them.

03:11:00.030 --> 03:11:05.290
And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, On the first day of the first month shalt thou

03:11:05.290 --> 03:11:10.870
set up the tabernacle of the tent of the congregation, and thou shalt put therein the ark of the

03:11:10.870 --> 03:11:16.470
testimony and cover the ark with a veil, and thou shalt bring in the table and set in order

03:11:16.470 --> 03:11:21.690
the things that are to be set in order upon it, and thou shalt bring in the candlestick

03:11:21.690 --> 03:11:27.090
and light the lamps thereof, and thou shalt set the altar of gold for the incense before

03:11:27.090 --> 03:11:33.030
the ark of the testimony and put the hanging of the door to the tabernacle, and thou shalt

03:11:33.030 --> 03:11:37.410
set the altar of the burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle of the tent of

03:11:37.410 --> 03:11:42.490
the congregation, and thou shalt set the laver between the tent of the congregation and

03:11:42.490 --> 03:11:48.410
the altar and shalt put water therein, and thou shalt set up the court round about and

03:11:48.410 --> 03:11:53.430
hang up the hanging at the court gate, and thou shalt take the anointing oil and anoint

03:11:53.430 --> 03:11:59.110
the tabernacle and all that is therein, and shalt hallow it and all the vessels thereof,

03:11:59.370 --> 03:12:04.990
and it shall be holy, and thou shalt anoint the altar of the burnt offering and all his

03:12:04.990 --> 03:12:11.410
vessels and sanctify the altar, and it shall be an altar most holy, and thou shalt anoint

03:12:11.410 --> 03:12:16.890
the laver and his foot and sanctify it, and thou shalt bring Aaron and his sons unto the

03:12:16.890 --> 03:12:22.550
door of the tabernacle of the congregation and wash them with water, and thou shalt put

03:12:22.550 --> 03:12:27.930
upon Aaron the holy garments and anoint him and sanctify him that he may minister unto

03:12:27.930 --> 03:12:33.350
me in the priest's office, and thou shalt bring his sons and clothe them with coats,

03:12:33.730 --> 03:12:38.770
and thou shalt anoint them as thou didst anoint their father that they may minister unto me

03:12:38.770 --> 03:12:43.810
in the priest's office, for their anointing shall surely be an everlasting priesthood

03:12:43.810 --> 03:12:50.410
throughout their generations. Thus did Moses, according to all that the Lord commanded him,

03:12:50.410 --> 03:12:51.550
so did he.

03:12:52.790 --> 03:12:57.570
And it came to pass in the first month and the second year on the first day of the month

03:12:57.570 --> 03:13:03.410
that the tabernacle was reared up, and Moses reared up the tabernacle and fastened his

03:13:03.410 --> 03:13:08.830
sockets and set up the boards thereof and put in the bars thereof and reared up his

03:13:08.830 --> 03:13:14.290
pillars, and he spread abroad the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the

03:13:14.290 --> 03:13:20.710
tent above upon it as the Lord commanded Moses, and he took and put the testimony into

03:13:20.710 --> 03:13:26.530
the ark and set the staves on the ark and put the mercy seat above upon the ark, and

03:13:26.530 --> 03:13:31.310
he brought the ark into the tabernacle and set up the veil of the covering and covered

03:13:31.310 --> 03:13:37.230
the ark of the testimony as the Lord commanded Moses, and he put the table in the tent of

03:13:37.230 --> 03:13:43.190
the congregation upon the side of the tabernacle northward without the veil, and he set the

03:13:43.190 --> 03:13:49.870
bed in order upon it before the Lord as the Lord had commanded Moses, and he put the candlestick

03:13:49.870 --> 03:13:55.710
in the tent of the congregation over against the table on the side of the tabernacle southward,

03:13:56.210 --> 03:14:02.290
and he lighted the lamps before the Lord as the Lord commanded Moses, and he put the golden

03:14:02.290 --> 03:14:07.990
altar in the tent of the congregation before the veil, and he burnt sweet incense thereon

03:14:08.710 --> 03:14:14.390
commanded Moses, and he set up the hanging at the door of the tabernacle, and he put

03:14:14.390 --> 03:14:18.950
the altar of burnt offering by the door of the tabernacle of the tent of the congregation

03:14:18.950 --> 03:14:24.950
and offered upon it the burnt offering and the meat offering as the Lord commanded Moses,

03:14:25.450 --> 03:14:30.850
and he set the laver between the tent of the congregation and the altar and put water there

03:14:30.850 --> 03:14:37.370
to wash withal, and Moses and Aaron and his sons washed their hands and their feet thereat

03:14:37.650 --> 03:14:42.570
when they went into the tent of the congregation and when they came near under the altar they

03:14:42.570 --> 03:14:48.950
washed as the Lord commanded Moses, and he reared up the court round about the tabernacle

03:14:48.950 --> 03:14:55.990
and the altar and set up the hanging of the court gate, so Moses finished the work. Then

03:14:55.990 --> 03:15:01.350
a cloud covered the tent of the congregation and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle,

03:15:01.690 --> 03:15:07.170
and Moses was not able to enter into the tent of the congregation because the cloud abode

03:15:07.170 --> 03:15:13.150
thereon and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle, and when the cloud was taken

03:15:13.150 --> 03:15:17.910
up from over the tabernacle the children of Israel went onward in all their journeys,

03:15:18.630 --> 03:15:23.450
but if the cloud were not taken up then they journeyed not till the day that it was taken

03:15:23.450 --> 03:15:29.990
up, for the cloud of the Lord was upon the tabernacle by day and fire was on it by night

03:15:29.990 --> 03:15:34.610
in the sight of all the house of Israel throughout all their journeys.
